(19, 'Bangladesh Rice Research Institute', 'Plant Pathology Division', 'Project', 'Pyramiding bacterial blight resistant genes into the genetic background of BR 11-derived submergence tolerant rice lines ', 'Laboratory and field of BRRI', '', '', '', '01-02-2010', '31-12-2012', '25-02-2010', '', '1.Enhancing wider adaptability of newly developed submergence tolerant rice genotypes through introgression of bacterial blight resistant genes\r\n2.Strengthening capacity of newly established marker-assisted selection laboratory of plant breeding division of Bangladesh Rice Research Institute\r\n3.Exploration of new sources of rice germplasm tolerant to bacterial blight disease and identification of races of rice bacterial blight disease specific to tolerant parents\r\n4.Deployment of marker-assisted backcross breeding technique in the pyramiding of multiple disease resistant genes\r\n5.Introgression of Bacterial Blight Resistant genes into the genetic background of BR11-derived submergence tolerant lines\r\n6.Strengthening collaboration among multiple disciplines for the development of rice varieties\r\n', '', '', 'Pyramiding bacterial blight, Genes, BR 11, Submergence, Introgression', 'SPGR', 7678670, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
