(63, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Council', 'Fisheries Division', 'Project', 'Coordinated project on addressing climate change on fisheries sector through community based technology identification and adoption in the fragile aqua ecosystems of Bangladesh: BARC Component (318)', 'Patuakhali, Barguna, Rangpur and Nilphamari in Bangladesh', '', '', '', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2013', '09-06-2011', '', '1.Identify climate change related major vulnerable issues of fishers'' and small aquaculture communities,\r\n2.Strengthen local community coping capacity through developing community based aquaculture/ fisheries technology management plan, \r\n3.Pilot the identified technology options within the targeted communities. \r\n4.Develop guidelines for climate change  adaptation framework in similar communities\r\n', '', '', 'Fisheries, Adoption, Fragile aqua ecosystems, Framework, Aquaculture, Pilot     ', 'SPGR', 15018260, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(64, 'Sher-e-Bangla Agricultural University', 'Agricultural Economics Division', 'Project', 'Coordinated project on addressing climate change on fisheries sector through community based technology identification and adoption in the fragile aqua ecosystems of Bangladesh: SAU Component  (346)', 'Rangpur and Nilphamari districts of Bangladesh', '', '', '', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2013', '09-06-2011', '', 'The proposed project is designed to identify the need for community based technologies to address climate change impacts among the Fishers'' and Small Aquaculture Communities in the drought and river bank erosion prone areas of Bangladesh. As a pilot project, it anticipates to test community based fisheries/ aquaculture technologies with different resource bases, centered upon a participatory approach. On the basis of lessons learnt, it is then expected to prepare a guideline for adaptation processes and technologies relevant to similar communities. ', '', '', 'Climate change, Community based technology , Fragile aqua ecosystems', 'SPGR', 14253410, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(65, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Council', 'Fisheries Division', 'Project', 'Coordinated project on contaminants and adulterants in food chain and their mitigation: BARC Component (319)', 'All over the Country', '', '', '', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2013', '09-06-2011', '', '1.Collect and collate the information derived through the component sub-project activities.\r\n2.Development of Communicative material for wide awareness building\r\n3.Organisation of disseminating workshop/seminar and capacity building on food safety and   quality. \r\n4.Co-ordination and monitoring of the component activities to facilitate smooth implementation.\r\n', '', '', 'Component, Adulterants, Chain', 'SPGR', 4403800, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(66, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Food Technology and Rural Industries Department', 'Project', 'Coordinated project on contaminants and adulterants in food chain and their mitigation: BAU Component (347)', 'Dhaka City, Savar, Norshingdi and Mymensingh Municipalities', '', '', '', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2013', '09-06-2011', '', '1.Current issues, status, challenges and constraints of quality control in processed food products summarized.\r\n2.An exclusive list of harmful chemicals and adulterants used in processed food products prepared.\r\n3.Resources (or Methods, skills and facilities) for detection, identification and mitigation of hazardous contaminants and adulterants in processed foods strengthened.\r\n4.Hazardous adulterants used in selected processed foods assessed\r\n', '', '', 'Contaminants, Adulterants , Food chain, Hazardous ', 'SPGR', 6611200, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(67, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Postharvest Technology Division ', 'Project', 'Coordinated project on contaminants and adulterants in food chain and their mitigation: BARI Component (348)', 'Chapai Nawabgonj, Bogra, Jessore, Jamalpur, Tangail, Norsindi, Comilla and Gazipur', '', '', '', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2013', '09-06-2011', '', '1.To assess the various chemicals/pesticides and their dosages used to accelerate the ripening process of selected fruits (mango, banana, pineapple, papaya) and vegetables (tomato, brinjal, country bean, bitter gourd)\r\n2.To standardize the proper application method and dosages of safe ripening chemicals to artificially  ripe of selected fruits and vegetables\r\n3.To evaluate the effect of ripening chemicals/pesticides on the nutritional quality of selected fruits and vegetables and to determine their residual effect in the produces\r\n4.To disseminate information among the growers, traders, interested agency personnel, extension and NGO personnel for the improvement of post harvest management of fruits and vegetables\r\n', '', '', 'Contaminants, Adulterants, Food chain, Mitigation, Dosages, Ripening, Pesticides  ', 'SPGR', 13189000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(68, 'Bangladesh Fisheries Research Institute', '', 'Project', 'Coordinated project on contaminants and adulterants in food chain and their mitigation: BFRI Component (349)', 'Mymensingh, Dhaka, Khulna, Chittagong, Coxs Bazar', '', '', '', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2013', '09-06-2011', '', '1.To investigate potential hazards for fish and fish products\r\n2.To investigate the pathway of adulteration of fish and fish products To investigate potential hazards for fish and fish products\r\n3.To investigate the pathway of adulteration of fish and fish products through sensory, biochemical and microbiological analysis;\r\n4.To monitoring aquaculture input i.e. fish feed and farm water quality and their relevance to food (fish) safety;\r\n5.To formulate guidelines for environmentally sound aqua-business which can help prevent the adulteration.\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Contaminants, Adulterants, Food chain, Mitigation, Pathway, Microbiological, Aquaculture  ', 'SPGR', 5729000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(69, 'Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute', 'Animal Production Research Division', 'Project', 'Coordinated project on contaminants and adulterants in food chain and their mitigation: BLRI Component (350)', 'Locations: Pabna, Sirajgonj, Rangpur, Joypurhat, Munshigonj, and Jessore), and Super markets in Dhaka, Chittagong cities', '', '', '', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2013', '09-06-2011', '', '1.Identify the presence of adulterants in feeds &amp; fodders, milk, meat and eggs and their products available in the market of selected locations.\r\n2.Investigate the potential adulterants and/or hazardous materials in milk &amp; meat including eggs and their products available in the country.\r\n3.Standardization of guidelines of safe food of animal origin in the context of animal and public health concern.\r\n4.Analyses of potentials hazards in dairy, meat and poultry products \r\n', '', '', 'Contaminants, Adulterants , Food chain, Mitigation, Dairy', 'SPGR', 5454520, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(70, 'Bangladesh Rice Research Institute', 'Grain quality and Nutrition Laboratory', 'Project', 'Coordinated project on contaminants and adulterants in food chain and their mitigation: BRRI Component (351)', 'Dhaka, Narayangang Gazipur, Chittagong, Jessore, Khulna and Bogra covering industrial and non-industrial rice fields', '', '', '', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2013', '09-06-2011', '', '1.Understanding the status of rice grain and food contamination as well as grain quality to focus its impact on human health.\r\n2.Determination of the contamination of rice grain/foods and its influence on grain/food quality in different conditions or parts of the country.\r\n3.Estimation of the presence of heavy metal contamination in rice\r\n4.Determining residual effect of pesticides in rice grain\r\n5.Determining the fungal association, toxin production level and grain quality at storage\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Contaminants, Adulterants , Food chain, Grain,  Residual, Toxin , Fungal ', 'SPGR', 7773000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(71, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Agril. Economics Division', 'Project', 'Assessment of Socio-economic Impacts of Oilseeds Research and Development in Bangladesh (310)', 'Dhaka,Rajshahi,Dinajpur,Noakhali, Pabna, Tangail,Jessore, Faridpur, Comilla,Noakahli, Comilla and Mymensingh\r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2013', '09-06-2011', '', '1. To assess variety-wise adoption of improved oilseed technologies at farm level and to find out the factors affecting their adoptions, dis-adoptions, non-adoptions and sustainability.\r\n2. To study the economics of improved oilseed crop production in Bangladesh along with its impact on the livelihood of the farmers.\r\n3. To estimate the returns to investment (IRR, NPV, BCR) in oilseeds research and development in Bangladesh through ex-post evaluation method.\r\n', '', '', 'Socio-economic Impacts, Oilseeds, Ex-post', 'SPGR', 3666480, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(72, 'Bangladesh Fisheries Research Institute', 'Riverine Sub-station', 'Project', 'Coordinated project on addressing climate change on fisheries sector through community based technology identification and adoption in the fragile aqua ecosystems of Bangladesh (345)', 'The proposed project aims to work in four environmentally fragile districts, namely Patuakhali and Barguna in southern coastal areas, while Rangpur and Nilphamari in drought and river bank erosion prone areas in northwest Bangladesh', '', '', '', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2013', '09-06-2011', '', 'The overall objective of the project is to enhance the capacity of the rural poor fishing and aquaculture communities/households in coastal, draught and river bank erosion region of Bangladesh to address the impacts of climate change related hazards on their lives and livelihoods as well as to reduce poverty.\r\n', '', '', 'Climate change, Aqua ecosystems, Aquaculture, Households, Coastal, River Bank', 'SPGR', 10147640, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
