(92, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Agronomy Division', 'Project', 'Evaluation of short duration high yielding rapeseed- mustard varieties/lines for cultivation between T.Aman and Boro rice ', '', '', '', 'New', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2014', '', '', '1.To evaluate and selection of rapeseed-mustard lines suitable for growing between T.Aman and Boro rice.\r\n2.To replace local Tori-7 variety by high yielding short duration variety(s) and to provide an opportunity to the farmers to select appropriate varieties/lines adapted to their local condition.\r\n3.To increase production and area of rapeseed- mustard.\r\n', '1.On station screening of rapeseed-mustard varieties/lines ( 1st Cycle)\r\n2.Cropping Pattern of T.Aman Mustard-Boro (2nd Cycle)\r\n3.Cultivation of T.Aman Mustard (in the Cropping pattern of T.Aman Mustard-Boro (3rd  Cycle):\r\n', 'Increase area and production of rapeseed mustard.', 'Rapeseed, Mustard,  T.Aman,Boro rice,  Tori-7 ', 'BARC', 700000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(93, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Plant Pathology Section', 'Project', 'Integrated Management of Banana Diseases caused by Fungi and Nematode', 'Jessore, Bogra, Rangpur, Tangail, and laboratory and pot experiments in Gazipur.', '', '', 'New', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2014   ', '', '', '1.To identify the disease incidence and damage for panama in major banana growing areas in the country \r\n2.To isolate, purify and preservation of the panama causing fungus\r\n3.To find out the effective control measure against panama disease in Lab and pot \r\n4.To adopt the most effective control measure for panama, sigatoka and nematode in farmers orchard\r\n5.To develop a IPM package technology for banana production\r\n', '', '1.Increase banana production by controlling banana diseases\r\n2.Reduction of health hazards and increase yield of banana\r\n3.Income of the farmers cultivating banana with IPM technology will be increase\r\n', 'Banana, Diseases, Fungi, Nematode, Panama, Fungus, Sigatoka, IPM', 'BARC', 900000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(94, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'On-Farm Research Division', 'Project', 'Adaptation of Matured Technologies on Crop Variety in Southern Char Lands of Bangladesh', 'Char lands adjacent to RARS, Rahmatpur, Barisal (Muladi) and MLT site Bhola', '', '', 'New', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2014', '', '', '1.To disseminate matured technologies on crops variety in char areas\r\n2.To utilize the unfavorable char lands during Rabi and Kharif-1 season\r\n3.To enhance national crop production for secure the country on food. \r\n', '1.An extensive survey program will be done to find out farmers knowledge, crops and cropping patterns of char lands. \r\n2.Motivational farmers training will be arranged to know the matured agril. Technologies and production practices of crops.  \r\n3.On-farm adaptive trials: 09 adaptive trials in two locations will be conducted\r\n', '', 'Matured, Technologies, Southern, Char Land', 'BARC', 750000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(95, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'On-Farm Research Division', 'Project', 'Up Scaling of Summer Onion Bulb and Seed Production Technology at Farm Level      ', 'Faridpur and Rajbari\r\n', '', '', 'New', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2014', '', '', '1. To disseminate knowledge among the selected growers about summer onion varieties and their production technology on summer onion bulb and  seed production. \r\n2. To develop post harvest technology like bulb storage for use in true seed production\r\n3. To identify the constrains for dissemination this technology.\r\n', '1. Farmer selection: Farmers will be selected on the basis of farm size (Small and marginal), elevation of land, experience and existing resources. Each year new farmers will be selected. \r\n2. Training programme: \r\nFarmers training- 9 farmers training programme (each training programme 30 participants will be included) on production technology on summer onion will be arranged for participating farmers during the entire project period. From this, each year three training programme will be conducted (one training programme for kharif II, rabi and kharif II season each).\r\n3. Field trial/demonstration/activities: During the project time, 75 farmers will be selected from the project area. Two types of activities will be conducted.     \r\n   a) Summer onion bulb production: 60 farmers will be selected for onion bulb production during total project period. Each year 10 farmers for kharif I and 10 farmers for kharif II for bulb production will be included. \r\nb) Summer onion seed production: Summer onion seed will be produced in fifteen (15) farmers field during project period. Each year, five (5) farmers for rabi season for seed production will be selected. \r\n4. Field Day: Field days will be arranged two times: \r\n   a) 1st field day will be arranged at the time of bulb maturity stage with 75 participants   (50 farmers and 25 concerned scientists, local extension personnel and NGO workers).\r\n   b) 2nd field day will be arranged at the time of seed harvesting stage with 75 participants (50 farmers and 25 concerned scientists, local extension personnel and NGO workers).\r\n5. Documentation: Booklets (in Bengali) will publish on summer onion technologies and adoption constrains. The final project report will also be published. \r\n', '', 'Summer Onion Bulb, Seed Production Technology', 'BARC', 700000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(96, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Regional Wheat Research Centre', 'Project', 'Development and dissemination of a low cost power tiller operated potato planter ', 'Potato planter fabrication: Engineering workshop of Regional Wheat  Research Centre, BARI, Shyampur, Rajshahi and Farm Machinery Division, BARI, Joydebpur, Gazipur.\r\nOn farm evaluation: Farmers field of potato growing area of Poba, Rajshahi\r\n', '', '', 'New', '01-10-2011', '30-09-2014', '', '', '1.To develop a cup type potato planter cum fertilizer applicator matching with power tiller\r\n2.To evaluate machine performance and disseminate among the farmers field.\r\n3.To compare the economic benefit of the potato planter with conventional manual planting\r\n', 'This power tiller operated potato planter will act as tilling, fertilizing, potato seed placing in a regular interval and earthing up simultaneously in a one operation. The followings are the step of fabrication of potato planter.\r\nStep 1: Rotary tilling part of the power tiller to be modified for rearranging the cutting blades of bed formation. Normally there are 18 blades, the number of blades to be increased 24 for smooth tilling operation.\r\nStep 2: Seed box with fertilizer and cup type potato planting mechanism to be introduced and set on  the rotary tilling part of the tiller. The whole unit to be assembled with power tiller. The planting mechanism to be operated by chain sprockets mechanism from power tiller wheel base power.\r\nStep 3: The roller type bed former cum shaper to be attached behind the tilling part formation of bed. The depth control arrangement to be fixed with bed former.\r\nStep 4: Local machinery manufacturer to be involved for final proto type of potato planter making. \r\n', '', 'power tiller, cup type potato, fertilizer applicator', 'BARC', 1192000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(97, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Postharvest Technology Division', 'Project', 'Development of packages for fruits (mango, banana) and vegetables (yard long bean, pointed gourd, okra) ', 'Chapai Nawabgonj, Bogra, Jessore, Tangail, Norsindi,  Comilla, Chittagong, Rangamati and Gazipur\r\n', '', '', 'New', '01-10-2011', '30-09-2014', '', '', '1.To standardize the packages of selected fruits (mango, banana) and vegetables (yard long bean, pointed gourd, okra) at farmers, traders and retailers level.\r\n2.Quality evaluation of fruits and vegetables in the packages \r\n', '1. Benchmark survey\r\n2. Input collection\r\n3. Collection of fresh fruits and vegetables\r\n4. Conducting experiments \r\n5. Experimental data recording, compilation and analysis\r\n6. Standardization of packages and packaging materials\r\n7. Publication of booklets/leaflets\r\n8. Statistical analysis of collected data and final report preparation\r\n', 'To find out the appropriate packaging materials and packages for reducing postharvest losses, increasing shelf life as well as value addition to selected fruits and vegetables. ', 'packages, fruits, postharvest, vegetables', 'BARC', 1187000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', '');
