(1139, 'Bangladesh Academy for Rural Development', 'PRC, Ishurdi, Pabna', 'Project', 'Developmemnt of Integrated Management Package for Stemphylium blight and Rust disease of lentil.', 'Pulse Research Centre, Ishurdi, Pabna', 'High', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-07-2005', '30-06-2006', '', '30-06-2006', '1.	To find out resistant germplasm against stemphylium blight of lentil.\r\n2.	To find out integrated management package in controlling stemphylium blight of lentil.\r\n', 'The experiment was carried out at the experimental field of Pulses Research Center (PRC), Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute (BARI), Ishurdi, Pabna to screening of lentil germplasm against stemphylium blight and rust diseases and an integrated management package to controlling stemphylium blight of lentil by using different fungicides available in the market. A total of five (5) experiments were conducted to achieve the project objectives. The conducted experiments were:\r\nExperiment 1. Efficacy of fungicides in controlling Stemphylium blight of lentil (In-vitro).\r\n \r\nExperiment 2. Efficacy of fungicides in controlling Stemphylium blight disease of lentil in-vivo.\r\nExperiment 3. Screening of Lentil genotypes for resistance to Stemphylium blight disease.\r\nExperiment 4. Screening of Lentil genotypes for resistance of rust [(Uromyces fabae (Pers.) de Bary] disease.\r\nExperiment 5. Control of Lentil Rust by use of fungicides.\r\n', 'Lentil (Lins culinaris L.), an important source of protein for human diet in every day dish, occupied the top position with consumers preference in Bangladesh. The crop faced a lot of production constraints regularly in the country. At least sixteen diseases were found to attack the crop, of which stemphylium blight disease caused by the fungus Stemphylium sarciniformis was most important. Resistant variety of lentil against this disease remain unexplored, therefore, the alternate method of disease management was the chemical control through fungicide. To combat the disease by using fungicide the present investigation was under taken. The result of the present investigation revealed that Acmicop were able to combat the disease Stemphylium blight of lentil thereby increased seed yield of lentil though the combined effect of Rovral 80WP + Tilt 250EC was best among 21 entries. Seven entries showed resistant reaction against rust disease of lentil. The yield varied significantly from 656.25 to 1882.82 kg ha-1. The result of the present investigation also revealed that Dithen M 45 and Force were able to combat the disease rust of lentil thereby increased seed yield of lentil.', 'stemphylium, Stemphylium, Stemphylium sarciniformis, Disease Stemphylium, ', '', 800000, 800000, 0, 'Publication', '', 0, 'Pulse Crop', 'Stemphylium blight, Rust disease of Lentil', '', '', ''),
(1167, 'Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute', 'Biotechnology Division', 'Project', 'Strengthening Biotechnological Research of Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute', 'Ishurdi, Rajshahi Sadar, Joypurhat Sadar, Thakurgaon Sadar, Joydebpur, Jamalpur Sadar, Chunarughat, Damurhuda, Babuganj', 'High', 'Adaptive', 'On-going', '01-07-2010', '31-12-2013', '', '', '1.Development of high sufar, high yielding ono-flowering, self-detrashing, erect, water-logging, flood, drought, salinity tolerant and diseases and pest resistance varieties of sugarcane for sugar, gur, chewing and juice purpose using bio-technological tools.\r\n2.Micropropagation of high sugar, high yielding sugarcane varieties, stevia-an elite sweetening herb, Palmyra palm and date palm for rapid multiplication and clean seed production.\r\n3.Variety identification and protection using DNA Fingerprinting, molecular characterisation of varieties, active germplasm and development of Market assisted Selection (MAS) for sugarcane variety selection.\r\n4.Genitic transformation of biotic and abiotic stress resistance trait(s) through agrobacterium mediated method of gene transformation.\r\n', ' The Challenges of improving global food security, nutritional adequacy, for sustainable agricultural development to cater for global demand. It is clean that the plant breeders have been practiced genetic manipulation for many hundred of years with great success. Breeders have developed elegant schemes for crossing plants to introduce and maintain desirable traits in inbred lines. and yield of crops like cereals as well as other crops including sugarcane has steadily increased over the past century. However this traditional method of genetic manipulation is slow, uncertain, time consuming and laborious. Side by side the advent of genetic engineering techniques as well as plant cell and tissue culture techniques augmented traditional breeding method and accelerate the production of new plant varieties with desirable traits. Modern scientists have been successful in applying these new acquired techniques in many crops to produce plant variates/lines with favourable traits such as resistance to disease, pest insect, virus, fungi herbicide, drought tolerant, water logging tolerant as well as instances where metabolism of plant are to regulate early or late flowering plant as well as maturity behaviour. ', 'Biotechnology and genetic engineering is a modern field of research offering great promise in the field development of improved of improved varieties with desired characters. Nowadays, a large number of scientists throughout the world have drawn their attention on genetic engineering research, because genetic engineering is a step ahead of research for challenging global demand. It holds considerable promise to meet the challenges of improving global food security, nutritional adequacy, for sustainable agricultural development to cater for global demand. It is clear that the plant breeders have been practiced genetic manipulation for many hundreds of years with great success.\r\nBangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute using conventional method of breeding through hybridization and selection for variety development. Hybridizatin is, of course, an effective method for development improved variety(s) by incorporating desired character(s). But the obstacles are that many varieties do not flower and some flower sparsely. Those flowered do not flower at athe same time of the year, some flower early while some are very late. Among the 980 gremplasms now available in the germplasm bank of BSRI, only 242 are flowering in nature. This insufficient number of flowering germplasms strictly reduce the scope of hybridization. Moreover, all the germplasms are more or less susceptible to red rot, the most serious disease of sugarcane in Bangladesh. However, sugarcane breeding should be further strengthened to evolve a variety(s) tolerant to abiotic and biotic stress, such as drought, water-logging flood, salinity, pest and diseases.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nDevelopment of sugarcane using biotechnological tools and for the enhancement of research sophistication for the purpose modern equipment, chemicals laboratory construction and modefications, hardening shade construction and trained manpower development. Micropropagation for rapid multiplication, clean seed production and distribution of sugarcane as well as stevia, plam and date palm is needed.\r\n', 'Biotechnology, Strengthening, BSRI', 'GOB', 88362000, 52382000, 0, 'Publication', 'Workshops', 1680, 'Biotechnology', 'Sugarcane, Stevia-an elite Sweetening herb', '', '', ''),
