(1138, 'Bangladesh Rice Research Institute', 'Soil Science Division', 'Project', 'Carbon Sequestration in soils of Bangladesh', 'BRRI, Gazipur', 'High', 'Basic', 'On-going', '01-05-2010', '31-05-2013', '', '31-05-2013', '1. To quantify the present status of carbon in soils in thirty agro-ecological zones of Bangladesh.\r\n2. To determine the effects of different cropping systems and management practices on soil carbon stocks.\r\n3. To evaluate the degree of carbon sequestration using integrated nutrient management.\r\n4. To derermine the degree of carbon sequestration in soils using 14C.\r\n5. To establish the relationshp  among cropping systems and management practices with the soil carbon stock and systems productivity.', 'The project is being implementing in BRRI, Gazipur to quantify carbon sequestration in soils of Bangladesh. To achieve the project objectives, Soil pH will be measured by grall electrode pH meter method, organic carbon content of soil samples will be estimated by wet oxidation methnod, total N of soil sample will be determined following micro-Kjeldahl method, available soil phosphorus will be measured by Olsen method and available Zn will be determined by DTPA extration method. Exchangeable K of soiols will be determined ny flame photometer, collected grain and straw samples will be chemically analysed for N, P and K following diacid digestion procedure. Carbon fractions will be determined by either simple titrimetric method or by Calcimeter method. During field experimentation, green house gases CH4 &amp; CO2 and respirated O2 will be determined by Infra red gas analyser. ', 'Carbon sequestration in soils of Bangladesh, a sponsored public goods research project, received funding from the NATP of Bangladesh Agricultural Research Council. The Carbon sequestration in soils of Bangladesh project has officially launched on 13 May 2010 through the signing of letter of agreement. The project received an approval of budget Tk. 63,14,440/- for a period of three years. Aiming to quantify the present status of carbon in soils in ten agro-ecological zones of Bangladesh zones of Bangladesh and to evaluate the degree of carbon sequestration using integrated nutrient and tillage management the project has a provision to two scientific officers and an technical assistant. The objectives will be achieved through survey, laboratory and field experiments. Survey on soil organic carbon storage in soils of 10 AEZ will be started in November 2010. Laboratory and field experiments will be started immediately after personnel recruitment. The recruitment process is underway. Procurement plan of the project including goods, work and services  is included in this inception report.  ', 'Soil Carbon, CO2 emmission, Paddy soil', '', 6316440, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Soil Science', 'Carbon Stock in soil', '', '', ''),
