(1113, 'Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute', 'AERS', 'Project', 'A study on policy, management and constraints to processing of hides and skins in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-05-2000', '30-06-2001', '01-05-2000', '30-06-2001', 'a)	To review the Government development plans policies on procurement, processing, preservation and trading of hides and skins in the country.\r\n\r\nb)	To review the management systems of hides and skins production in Bangladesh.\r\n\r\nc)	To determine the present methods of procurement, processing and preservation of hides and skins for producing leather and leather products.\r\n\r\nd)	To identify the constraints responsible for hindering the overall production and trading of hides and skins.\r\n\r\ne)	To suggest policy implications for the future processing and production of hides and skins in Bangladesh.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 488000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Socio Economics', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(1317, 'Padakhep Manabik Unnayan Kendra', 'Rice-duck farming', 'Project', 'Up-Scaling of Integrated rice-duck farming in Bangladesh: Improvement of Rural livelihood through community approach.', 'Kendua Upazila of Netrakona district and Kotiadi upazila of Kishoegonj district.', 'High', 'Adaptive', 'completed', '01-05- 2009', '30-05-2011', '01-05-2009', '30-05- 2011', '1)To adapt and up-scaling of rice-Duck farming system in some specific ecological conditions.\r\n2) To reduce production cost by less use of chemical fertilizers and pesticides in rice production and\r\n3) To improve farmer&amp;#39;s income and livelihood.', '', '', '', 'Krishi Gobeshona Foundation (KGF)', 0, 1734740, 0, '', '', 0, 'Integrated crops', 'Rice-Duck Farming', '1.	A community approach in rice-duck farming has been established.\r\n2.	Insect pests and weeds were effectively controlled by duck and reduced production cost.\r\n3.	Rice yield increased by about 25% in rice duck field than rice field alone.\r\n4.	Net income is more in rice duck system than rice alone.\r\n', '1.	Higher productively, reduced production cost and more net income are the potential outcome of the project. Large scale adoption of rice duck technology will improve the livelihood of the resource poor small and marginal farmers of Kendua and Kotihadi upazilas of Netrokuna nad Kishorrganj district. ', ''),
(1318, 'Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Agricultural University', 'Department of Agronomy', 'Project', 'Impact of rice-Wheat/potato-Mungbean cropping system on farmers employment opportunity, food security and livelihood in selected monga prone areas in nothern districts of Bangladesh. ', 'Rangpur region; (Gaibandha, Nilphamari, Lalmonirhat and Kurigram)', '', 'Adaptive', '', '01-05-2009', '31-07-2011', '01-05-2009', '31-07-2011', '1) To assess the present status of socio-economy, cropping system, crop productivity and livelihood of monga-affected small farmers.\r\n2) To evaluate the potentiality of a new cropping system with respect to yield, system productivity and employment opportunity; and&lt;\r\n3) To assess the contribution of improved cropping system on income generation, employment opportunity, improving food security, nutritional status and livelihood of small farmers of the monga prone area.', '', '', '', 'Krishi Gobeshona Foundation (KGF)', 1979252, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '1.	Improved crop0ping system developed enhanced system productivity and economic return over the farmers conventional cropping system.\r\n2.	Inclusion of mungbean in the improved cropping system produced 887 kg /ha additional pulse.\r\n3.	Harvesting of aman rice in October allowed timely planting of potato and wheat that increase potato yield by 19.2% and wheat yield by 13% over the farmers. Cropping system. Additional grows return of Tk 43,626/ha was obtained from mungbean.\r\n4.	Besides mungbean cultivation and harvesting cmployed 122 labour /ha during 2 month of joblessness time in April-May.\r\n5.	System productivity,  gross return and BCR value was 20.1%, 101% and 51, 8% higher than farmers cropping system respectively. \r\n', '1.	Improved cropping system after adoption by the large number of farmers would mitigate suffering or seasonal distress of a large number of poor agriculture labour through generation of more labor employment opportunity enhancing productivity and profitability.\r\n2.	The higher emplo6yemnt opportune for jobless agricultural labors and increased productivity profitability of small holders would help generated more income and improve livelihood of rural poor in the monga prone areas.\r\n', ''),
(1110, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'AERS', 'Project', 'A policy study on the dairy industry in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-04-1999', '30-05-2000', '01-06-1999', '30-09-2000', 'a)	To evaluate government plans, programme, policies and strategies for dairy development in Bangladesh.\r\n\r\nb)	To evaluate Non-government organisations, Local Institutions and Private Sector Policy Programmes for dairy development.\r\n\r\nc)	To develop methodologies for impact study of those objectives both in public and private sectors.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 323000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Socio Economics', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(1108, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Determination of pesticide level in the environmental samples and their residual effect on animal bodies.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-02-2000', '31-07-2001', '14-02-2000', '30-06-2001', 'i) Collection of environmental samples i.e. water, soil, plants, grasses and food stuff from different areas of at least 3 selected districts (densely pesticide used) of Bangladesh and detection of pesticide level in the collected samples;\r\nii) Collection of blood, urine &amp; milk from cattle &amp; goats of above mentioned 3 selected districts and detection of pesticide level in those samples.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 539000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Toxicology', '', '', '', ''),
(1107, 'Khulna University', 'Forestry', 'Project', 'Studies of the top dying of sundari in Sundarbans : pathological, ecological silvicultural and soil aspects.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-06-2000', '31-05-2001', '01-06-2000', '', 'a) Pathological aspects:\r\n    - To find out the causal agent of top dying of sundri.\r\n    - To determine the infection biology and etiology of the causal factor (pathogen) for top dying of sundri.,\r\n    - To find out the biotic and abiotic factors responsible for aggravating the top dying of sundri.\r\n    - To find out ways how the knowledge of the causal pathogen and factors aggravating the disease can be used to develop appropriate       \r\nmanagement strategy for top dying affected sundri in the Sundarbans.\r\n\r\nb) Ecological aspects:\r\n    - To determine relationship between environmental factors (geomorphology, rate of sedimentation, smothering of pneumatophore and level of salinity) and development of top dying of sundri.\r\n    - To determine relationship between damage to the tree (by natural and anthropogenic causes) and development of top dying of sundri.\r\n    - To determine impact of salvage and sanitation felling of sundri on vegetation structure in the Sundarbans.\r\n\r\nc) Sivicultural aspects:\r\n   - To determine the relationship between top dying of sundri and age, density and associated tree crops.\r\n   - To determine impact of top dying on natural   regeneration.\r\n   - To determine the impact of sanitation and salvage felling on natural  regeneration of sundri \r\n\r\nd) Soil aspects:\r\n   - To determine physico-chemical properties of selected top dying affected and healthy sundri areas in order to find out whether there exists any relationship between site condition (i.e. including soil properties) and the development of top dying of sundri.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Forest Management', 'Sundri', '', '', ''),
(1104, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Studies on integrated farming.', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-07-2000', '31-12-2001', '01-07-2000', '', 'General Objective:\r\na)	To study the effect of integrated farming systems on productivity, sustainability and welfare of rural farms.\r\n\r\nb)	To develop a methodology for the dissemination of integrated technology under farmers'' environment.\r\n\r\n	3)	To document the outcome of integrated farming systems to enrich the agricultural education.\r\n\r\n	Working Objective:\r\na)	Help attain household food security though diverse food production, consumption and nutrition through enterprise diversification.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 7799000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'FSRD', 'Farming Systems', '', '', ''),
