(1316, 'Agrarian Research Foundation (ARF)', 'Yield gap reduction.', 'Project', 'Wider Adaptation of modern rapeseed, mustard and sesame varieties with production technology for yield gap reduction.', 'Manikganj, Faridpur, Rajbari', '', 'Adaptive', '', '01-05-2009', '31-05-2011', '01-05-2009', '31-05-2011', '1) To adapt modern short duration rapeseed-mustard and sesame in the farmers field of the selected locations for replacing the traditional cultivars.\r\n2) To motivate farmers for adoption varieties and improved production technologies to increase yield in farmers field.', '', '', '', 'Krishi Gobeshona Foundation (KGF)', 1972876, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', 'a.	High Yielding shorter duration sarisha verities have been identified.\r\nb.	High yielding sesame verities have also been identified.\r\nc.	Production technologies for high yielding sarisha and sesame have been developed.\r\nd.	Improved cropping patterns with the inclusion of high yielding sarisha and sesame have been developed for Manikgnoj and Faridpur district. \r\n', '1.	Yield of rapeseed mustard and sesame can be increased with the replacement of local cultivar by modern varieties and production technology.\r\n2.	Farmers net income will be increased.\r\n3.	Oil seed production will be increased and import cost will be reduced. \r\n', ''),
(1078, 'Department of Agricultural Extension', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Development of mushroom variesties suitable for rural level in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-06-1998', '31-05-2001', '', '', 'i) Selection of suitable mushroom strains under Bangladesh condition\r\nii) Find out the suitable low cost substrate for growing different kinds of mushroom under Bangladesh climatic condition\r\niii) Find out the proper cultivation procedure for selected strain\r\niv) To improve the cultivation technologic for different mushroom', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Horticulture', 'Mushroom', '', '', ''),
(1077, 'Bangladesh Tea Research Institute', 'Forestry', 'Project', 'Updating and enrichment of tea germplasm in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '05-02-1998', '31-03-2001', '05-02-1998', '', 'i)  Collection and preservation of potentially valuable genetic materials from old sections/seed baris (orchards) due for uprooting. \r\nii)  To establish a central germplasm pool of tea at BTRI main station and BTRI sub-station at Fatikcharri, Chittagong. \r\niii)  Preliminary screening and evaluation of diverse tea germplasm in the nursery and field.\r\niv) Selection of desirable and presentable planting materials from them.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Biodiversity', 'Tea', '', '', ''),
(1076, 'Dhaka University', 'Nutrition', 'Project', 'Studies on the nutritive value of major crop cultivars developed by the NARS Institution of Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-06-1999', '31-05-2001', '', '31-03-2001', '1. To analyze the proximity composition (fat, protein, carbohydrate, energy value, ash, moisture, vitamins and minerals) of rice cultivars developed by BRRI.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n2. To analyze the proximity composition of all food crops (cereals, and others) developed by BINA.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n3. To analyze the proximity composition of all food crops (wheat, maize, millet, potato, pulses, oilseeds, fruits and vegetables, spices and condiments) developed by BARI.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n4. To anlyze the major nutrient content of newly developed sugarcane varieties developed by BSRI.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n5. To compare the nutritive value of the same crop cultivars (eg. Rice, Wheat, etc.) developed by different NARS Institutes and to recommend for those which shown higher nutrient containts (with higher yields).', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1181678, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Food Composition', '', '', '', ''),
(1075, 'Bangladesh National Nutrition Council', 'Nutrition', 'Project', 'Studies on the Effectiveness of Dietary intervention to Control Vitamin A Deficiency and Nutritional Anemia: Comparative Performance of Home Gardening Programs of Different Organization and Identification of Success Factors for Sustaibability.', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-11-1997', '30-09-2000', '01-11-1997', '30-04-2000', 'i)  To evaluate and identify success  (or failure) factors through participatory rural appraisal method.To evaluate the impact of current programs on uutritional  status especially of children and women (Anthropometry). \r\nii)  To evaluate the participation of women (and their role ) in the controlling additional resources generated from the programs.\r\niii)  To evaluate the effectiveness of home gardening programs as an IGA and also its translation into nutritional well-being by measuring the micro-nutrient like Iron, vitaminA status and anthropometry of children and women. \r\niv)  To make available of information on the effectiveness of vegetable species currently cultivated for their ability (or inability) to reduce anemia and vitamin-A deficiency.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1144410, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Dietary Intervention', '', '', '', ''),
(1074, 'Dhaka University', 'Nutrition', 'Project', 'Study on Food Intake of the Marginal Peasant Families of Bangladesh in Respect of Nutritional Adequacy and Anthropometry.', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-01-1997', '30-06-1999', '', '30-06-2000', 'i)  To study the situation of food availability of the peasant households throughout the year.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nii)  To study the per capita food and nutrient intake by different food groups and by age and sex and to find out food preferences among the family members.&lt;br /&gt;\r\niii)  To assess the health and nutritional status of the household members by undertaking anthropometric measurements such as height, weight, MUAC and nutritional deficiency symptoms including morbidity of various diseases.&lt;br /&gt;\r\niv)  To study the sex differential in food  and nutrient intake as will as in nutritional status of the peasant household members.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nv)  To study the household expenditure specially on food, expenditure on food production as well as sources of income/money for household expenditure and food production/purchase.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nvi)  To identify the determinants of food unavailability of peasant households.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nvii)  To search for the appropriate means and ways to increase household food availability and thereby food intake.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nviii)  To study the seasonal variation in food and nutrient intake as well as nutritional status.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 903560, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Nutritional Indicators', '', '', '', ''),
(1072, 'Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute', 'Soil', 'Project', 'Maximizing Production of sugarcane with package of Appropriate technologies and soil resilience pratices.', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-03-1999', '31-08-2000', '01-03-1999', '', 'i)  To introduce sugarcane production technology package at farm level to produce 100 tons cane/ha.\r\nii)  To accommodate Soil Resilience Practices in the production technology package.\r\niii)  To make use of soil test values in the calculations for the recommendation of fertilizers as given in BARC Fertilizer Guide. For achieving this objective farmers will be familiarized with soil test based fertilizer recommendations for both macro - and micro-nutrients (matching the nutrient needs for the targeted yields considering fertilizer efficiency and expected benefits of soil tests at farm level). Additional information on the need for Ca and micronutrients i.e. B, Mo, Mn, and Cu will also be monitored. \r\niv)  To familiarize farmers with the nutrient deficiency symptoms in sugarcane through seminars and visits to BSRI.\r\nv)  To make Bangladesh self sufficient in sweetening agents in 7-10 yrs time.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1800000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(1071, 'Soil Resources Development Institute', 'Soil', 'Project', 'Soil health card programme.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-07-1999', '31-12-2000', '01-08-1999', '', 'i)   To mitigate soil degradation and restoration of Soil health for sustainable yield.\r\nii)   To select sites and farmers in different thanas of Bangladesh to introduce Soil Health Card Programme.\r\niii)   To provide training to selected farmers and BS on how to collect composite soils samples for analyse.\r\niv)   To determine base line soil nutrient status and nutrient requirement of different crops.\r\nv)  To provide advisory services and to motivate farmers to use soil test based fertilizer recommendation.\r\nvi)   To collect field information on soil and crop management and crop response.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 2000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Fertility Management', 'Soils', '', '', ''),
(1070, 'Bangladesh Rice Research Institute', 'Soil', 'Project', 'Updating of soil and fertilizer management for rice based cropping pattern.', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-02-1998', '31-01-2001', '15-03-1999', '', 'a) To  develop an agronomically and economically suitable combination of chemical and organic fertilizer for sustainable high crop yield.\r\nb) To increase efficiency as well as the reduction of off-farm inputs through optimal combination of plant nutrient sources available within the farm and thereby conserve environment and decrease or eliminate pollution of soils and ground water.\r\nc) To create awareness on soil testing as an effective tools for balanced fertilization.\r\nd) To update BARC fertilizer recommendation guide.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 719000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Fertility Management', 'Soils', '', '', ''),
