(1068, 'Dhaka University', 'Soil', 'Project', 'Coordinated Project for Development of Blue Green Algae Technology as Biofertilizer for Rice Cultivation (DU Component)', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-1998', '31-12-2000', '', '', 'i)  Study of the physical, chemical and biological factors of some rice fields to identify factors that control BGA growth.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nii)  Screening of fast growing and super N2 fixing BGA from different soil types, at least ten strains from each type.&lt;br /&gt;\r\niii)  Production of soil-based or foam-based fresh inocula of selected BGA in pits. This will be done under different pest and fertilizer management practices to identify the best pesticide to control grazers and best dose of fertilizer(s) to be used in mass production.&lt;br /&gt;\r\niv)  Screening of strains which remain viable for about a years as soil-based inoculum in polythene bags; or selection of various carrier-based inocula for various agroclimatic zones of Bangladesh.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nv)  To develop technology for successful establishment of inoculated strains in rice fields (foam has been found suitable), where indigenous N2 fixing GBA population is low. In addition attempt will be teamken to enhance growth of indigenous N2 fixing BGA applying  TSP.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nvi)  To study the effect of algalization on rice yield under different fertilizer management practices and compared with yield in rice fields where recommended fertilizer doses were used.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 500000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Bio-fertilizer', 'Soils', '', '', ''),
(1067, 'Bangladesh Rice Research Institute', 'Soil', 'Project', 'Use of Azolla as Biofertilizer for Rice Production', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-07-1998', '31-12-2000', '01-11-1998', '', 'i) Selection of strains which are fast growing and super nitrogen fixing, and tolerant to heat and  salinity and  strains with a high N:P ratio, toreduce the need for P fertilization.\r\nii) To design economically  viable methods of cultivation  Azolla throughout  a year and to produce 15-20t fresh wt./ha/ cover\r\niii) To develop recommendations for the complementary use of Azolla and chemical nitrogen, to obtain maximum crop yield  and reduce dependence on urea N.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 200000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Bio-fertilizer', 'Soils', '', '', ''),
