(1056, 'Rajshahi University', 'Soil', 'Project', 'Coordinated project on vermiculture : Production of vermicompost and its use in upland and horticultural crops (RU Component).', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-08-2000', '30-04-2001', '01-08-2000', '', '1. Collection and identification of available  earthworm species prevailing in the country\r\n2. Assessment of species efficacy in vermicomposting and screening out of the most efficient species\r\n3. Development of sustainable methods for vermiculture and vermicomposting\r\n4. Evaluate the effect of vermicompost for sustainable crop production in highland and hilly areas of Bangladesh.\r\n5. Conduct Nutrient analysis of vermicasting/vermicompost.\r\n6. Organize training programme for the farmers for practicing vermiculture in their production system.\r\n7. Demonstrate the vermiculture in farmers level through NGOs.\r\n8. Mitigate soil degradation and restoration of soil health for sustainable agriculture.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 300000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Fertility Management', 'Soils', '', '', ''),
(1054, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Soil', 'Project', 'Management of coastal saline soils for crop production.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-08-1998', '31-07-2001', '01-12-1996', '30-06-2001', 'i)  To make a thorough study of physico-chemical characteristics and fertility status of the soil for identifying proper management practices for coastal saline soils. \r\nii)  To make a comprehensive study of salinity regime of soils and underground water of coastal saline area during different month of the year in order to determine the suitability of the soils for growing suitable crops and to identify the most suitable period of the year for growing the crops. \r\niii)  To develop appropriate agronomic management practices for coastal saline area.\r\niv)  To develop location specific appropriate cropping pattern for maximizing the land use in coastal saline area.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 708400, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Salinity Management', 'Soils', '', '', ''),
(1055, 'Bangladesh Institute of Nuclear Agriculture', 'Soil', 'Project', 'Integrated soil and nutrient management for sustainable crop production.', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-02-1998', '31-01-2001', '15-02-1998', '', 'a) To survey and identify the constraints related to soil and environment of the locations/AEZ under study.\r\nb) To development suitable production packages integrating inorganic and organic nutrients, and other management aspects for increasing production trend and sustaining soil productivity.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1336000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Fertility Management', 'Soils', '', '', ''),
(1053, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Soil', 'Project', 'Production and use of  bacterial fertilizers of rhizobium and mycorhiza for legume and other crops.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-03-1998', '28-02-2001', '01-03-1998', '', 'i) To survey and assess the potentiality of mycorrhiza cum Rhizobium technology in different AEZ soils of Bangladesh.\r\nii) To determine the increase in yield due to Mycorrhiza cum Rhizobium inoculation of the major leguminous pulses, oil seeds, vegetable crops and N2 fixing tree crops.\r\niii) To produce bacterial fertilizers of mycorrhiza cum Rhizoboum for use at farm levels and to make available extension service for demonstratioh.\r\niv) To ensure quality of mycorrhiza cum Rhizobium inoculants for use at farm levels.\r\nv) To organize training and workshop of research and extension agents for use of mycorrhiza cum Rhizobium technology.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1122000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Bio-fertilizer', 'Soils', '', '', ''),
(1052, 'Bangladesh Institute of Nuclear Agriculture', 'Soil', 'Project', 'Soil Health Card Services to Farmers for Sustainable Crop Production.', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-07--1998', '30-06-2000', '', '30-09-2000', 'i)  To make a detailed soil survey, mapping, collect and analyse information on existing and, soil water resources cropping pattern and pattern based fertilizer recommendataion etc.\r\nii)  To collect soil and water samples for laboratory and field analysis of soil physical, chemical and microbiological characters and prepare site specific fertilizer recommendation.\r\niii)  To  prepare soil health cards for the farmers and train the BS and the farmers on the use of soil health cards.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1943000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Fertility Management', 'Soils', '', '', ''),
(1051, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Soil', 'Project', 'Conservation of Soil and Water for Crop Production in the Hills.', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-11-1997', '31-10-2000', '01-11-1997', '', 'i)  To assess the present practices and erosion situation of the area concern.\r\nii)  To find out the production technology combined with conservation measure.\r\niii)  To identify the existing crop in a cropping pattern which is suitable to conserve soil and water.\r\niv)  To monitor soil water changes over time and storage during the cropping seasons.\r\nv)  To study the suitability and potentiality of growing permanent fruit trees and forages to minimize soil loss.\r\nvi)  To study the over all loss and to assess the parameters that affecting the declination of soil resources.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1200000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Soil Conservation', 'Soils', '', '', ''),
(1050, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Soil', 'Project', 'Nutrient Management for Maximum Yield and Sustainable Production in Specific Sites', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-12-1997', '30-11-2000', '01-12-1997', '', 'i)  To make a thorough study of physio-chemcial characteristics and fertility status of the soil for identifying proper management practices for maximum and sustainable crop production.\r\nii)  To develop location specific appropriate cropping pattern for maximizing and sustainable crop production.\r\niii)  To estimate the requirement the individual  nutrient with other inputs for maximum yield for year round production  plan.\r\niv)  To develop appropriate management practices for maximum yield and sustainable production towards 25 million ton food products by the year 2001.\r\nv)  To develop suitable technology packages for the specialized areas.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1800000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Fertility', 'Soils', '', '', ''),
(1049, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Soil', 'Project', 'Fertility Improvement and Management Practices for River Basins and Charlands.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-06-1997', '31-05-2000', '01-12-1997', '31-03-2001', 'a)	To generate appropriate technology for sustainable crop yield in charland.\r\n\r\nb)	To find appropriate means and ways to increase farmers income.\r\n\r\nc)	To improve soil fertility and stabilize soil.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1200000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Fertility Management', 'Soils', '', '', ''),
(1048, 'Department of Livestock Services', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Development of cellular biotechniques for quick genetic improvement of dairy cattle in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-01-2000', '30-06-2001', '01-01-2000', '30-06-2001', 'i) Testing the identification of best ovarian response of dairy cattle with standard super-ovulation treatments in different genotypes under the climatic condition of Bangladesh;\r\nii) Development of Cryo-biological technology with a view to make efforts of establishing a future Gene Bank to conserve valuable genetic resources for future use in the field of animal breeding in Bangladesh. Also attempts would be made to find out the possible ways and means to extend over the outcome of the research at farmers level in the way of conventional Technology Transfer process;\r\niii) Development of a foundation group of Superior Nucleus Breeding Herd of defined genetic merit in the National Dairy Farm, Savar consisting of different blood lines to minimize the Inbreeding Depression upon inter-se mating to introduce the ONBS in dairy cattle development.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 800000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Cellular Biotechnology', 'Dairy Cattle', '', '', ''),
(1047, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Control of clostradial enterotoxaemia of rumonant with experimentally prepared vaccine/toxoid .', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-06-1999', '30-11-2000', '01-09-1999', '30-06-2001', 'i) Isolation and production of toxins from Clostridium perfringens (Already completed and specimens maintained in the laboratory);\r\nii) Characterization of toxins of Clostrindinum perfringens;\r\niii) Preparation of toxoid/vaccine;\r\niv) Efficacy of toxoids/vaccines in the lab animals and ruminant hosts;\r\nv) Laboratory and field trial of toxoids/vaccines in ruminant hosts and lab. animals.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 917000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Biologies and Preventives', '', '', '', ''),
(1046, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Quantification of locally available feed Resources and feeding systems of animal in different regions of Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-1998', '31-12-1999', '02-05-1998', '30-04-2000', 'i)  To provide an updated information on the sources and availability of feed resources\r\nii)  To quantify the available feed resources in different areas in Bangladesh.\r\niii)  To study the seasonal variation on the availability of feed resources.\r\niv)  To provide an updated information on the sources on the feeding systems in different season\r\nv)  To collect a detailed information of what is available, where and when and their current prices.\r\nvi)  To collect information on the growing pattern and utilization of different types shrubs and tree fodder in the homestead.\r\nvii)  Acceptability of different feeds and fodder available in the village.\r\nviii)  To asses the quantity of res.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1450000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Animal Nutrition', 'Animal Feeds', '', '', ''),
(1044, 'Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Selection and improvement of native ducks', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-07-1998', '31-12-2000', '01-07-1998', '30-06-2001', 'i)  to compare the production performance of native ducks available in different regions of the country.\r\nii)  to select the potential native ducks in order to increase the egg production.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1800000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Genetics and Plant  Breeding', 'Ducks', '', '', ''),
(1045, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Comparative study of the performance of different commercial strains of layer and broiler under Bangladesh condition.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-1999', '30-09-2000', '30-06-1998', '30-06-2000', 'i)  To study the performance and  adaptibility of poultry parent stock during brooding, growing and laying period.\r\nii)  To investigate the hatchability traits (fertility, embryonic mortality, hatchability etc.) of poultry parent stock.\r\niii)   To study the performance and adaptability of commercial chicks ( brooding, growing and laying periods hatched out from poultry parent stock)', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 700000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Poultry Production', 'Chickens', '', '', '');
