(1043, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Effect of dwarf gene on the performance of broiler strain in hot humid tropics.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-1998', '31-12-2000', '15-02-1998', '28-02-2001', ' Suggested Information: These should be specific with respect to the problem that will be studied. It often takes several experiments or projects to solve a major agricultural problem. Therefore, the objectives should not be more ambitious than the actual capabilities or scope of work that will be done in the proposal.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1100000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Genetics and Plant  Breeding', 'Chickens', '', '', ''),
(1042, 'Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Epidemiological study of Pests Des Petits Ruminants (PPR) in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-06-1998', '31-05-2001', '11-05-1998', '30-06-2001', 'i)  Isolation identification and characterization of the actiological agent  of the disease;\r\nii)  Identification of epidemiological factors of the diseases including host, agent and environmental interaction;\r\niii)  Seromonitoring of small ruminants for PPR and RP antibodies; and\r\niv)  Formulation of long-term control programme of the disease;', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1500000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Epidemiology and Control', '', '', '', ''),
(1041, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Studies on the development of herd health management package for the organized dairy farms.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-06-1998', '31-05-2001', '01-06-1998', '30-06-2001', 'i)  To study the incidence of diseases, reproduction and production performances of dairy animals in the organized farms; \r\nii)  To study the effect of diseases on production and find out the factors and causes of disease susceptibility of cross-bred dairy cattle;\r\niii)   To innovate herd health data recording system in the organized farms; and\r\niv)  To develop herd health management package;', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1300000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Farm Management', 'Dairy Cattle', '', '', ''),
(1040, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Bioclimatographic studies of gastro-intestinal nematodes of ruminants in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-1998', '31-12-2000', '01-04-1998', '31-03-2001', 'i)  Identify the information on the Bionomics/ecology of parasities (Gastro-intestinal nematodes) which are lacking in the country.\r\nii)  Determine the influence of climatic factors on the incidence of parasitic diseases (Gastro-intestinal nematodes). \r\niii)  Correlate the influence of climatic factors and husbandry paractices/socio-economic condition on the incidence of parasitic disease (Gastro-intestinal nematodes) in different farm categories in deffernet agro-econogical zones.\r\nComponent-2\r\ni) Develop information models for useful collection of dazta on the parasitic diseases   (G.I. Nematodes) from TLDCs which further could be used for data collection on other diseases to develop Disease Reporting system (DRS).', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1344000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Epidemiology and Control', '', '', '', ''),
(1039, 'Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Production of pests des petits ruminants(PPR) vaccine and its field application.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-02-1998', '31-01-2000', '01-06-1998', '31-12-2000', 'i)  Production of vaccine virus using vero cells and determine the techniques of vaccine formulation and lyophilization\r\nii)  Evaluate the vaccine virus under laboratory and field conditions in different breeds of goat in different age group of anilmals.\r\niii)  recommendations for the mass production for wide field application as well as marketing.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1500000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Biologies and Preventives', '', '', '', ''),
(1038, 'Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Study on avian mycoplasmosis and its control in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-06-1998', '31-05-2001', '01-06-1998', '30-06-2001', 'i)  Isolation identification and characterization of the actiological agent of the disease;\r\nii)  Identification of epidemiological factors of the disease including host, agent and enviornmental interaction;\r\niii)  Seromonitoring of small ruminants for PPR and RP antibodies Formulation of long- term and short-term control programme of the diseases;', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 900000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Epidemiology and Control', '', '', '', ''),
(1037, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Field trial of an experimentally developed vaccine and comparison of its efficacy with the currently used one to control fowl pox of chicks of rural poultry.', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-01-1998', '31-12-2000', '15-02-1998', '30-06-2001', 'i)  Preparation of experimentally developed chicken egg-embryo adopted pigeon pox vaccine with the field isolate of virus previously characterised and stadardised for the purpose.\r\nii)  Field tiral of the vaccine through participatory activities (diffusion of technology)\r\n a). Conduct vaccination programme with the test and the currently used one in order to reduce incidence/epidemics of fowl pox in chicks of selected (Project) village/poultry units.\r\n b). Training of backyard/small scale poultry raisers for management and administration of the vaccine.\r\niii)  Evaluation of the efficacy of the schedule of administration as well as potency of the experimentally developed pigeon pox vaccine (test vaccine) and comparison of these parameters with the vaccine ', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1005000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Biologies and Preventives', 'Chickens', '', '', ''),
(1036, 'Department of Livestock Services', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Development of Vaccine Against Chicken Coccidiosis Using Precocious Line.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-05-1998', '30-04-2001', '', '31-05-2001', 'i) Single oocyst derived strain of E. tenella, E. acervulina, E. maxima and E. brunetti will  be isolated from naturally infected chickens;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nii) Precocious line of E. tenella will be developed by serial passages in chicks. The immunogenecity and margin of sefety will be tested by infecting chicks with nocysts of precocious line of E. tenella.&lt;br /&gt;\r\niii) Precocious lines of E necatrix E. acervulina will be developed as in above and their immunogenecity and margin of sefety will be determined.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 904000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Biologies and Preventives', 'Chickens', '', '', ''),
(1034, 'Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Development of beef cattle breed using Gayal (Bos frontalis.)', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-05-1998', '30-04-2001', '13-05-1998', '30-04-2001', 'i)  To increase the number of Gayal and their crossbred with other beef type breed;\r\nii)  To analyse the chromosomal variations in pure Gayal and their crossbred progenies;\r\niii)  To produce fodder by implementing SALT module for feeding Gayal under stall condition;\r\niv)  Expected output/benefits: A beef cattle breed will be developed; and\r\nv)  Indicators of success: Success in crossbreeding between Gayal and domestic cattle will ensure the development of beef breed;', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1495000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Genetics and Plant  Breeding', 'Cattle', '', '', ''),
(1035, 'Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Improvement of black bengal goat through selective breeding.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-02-1998', '31-01-2001', '11-05-1998', '31-05-2001', 'i)  Identification and selection of best available Black  Bengal goats.\r\nii)  Establishment of nucleus breeding herd\r\niii)  Improvement of Black Bengal goat through selective breeding.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1700000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Genetics and Plant  Breeding', 'Goats', '', '', ''),
(1033, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Identification of best genotype of Buffalo for dairy purpose in Bangladesh and to improve their productivity.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-07-1998', '31-12-2000', '01-12-1997', '31-12-2000', 'i)  Identification and characterization of buffaloes used for dairy purpose in Bangladesh.\r\nii)  Evaluation of the genetic merit of buffaloes used for dairy purpose in Bangladesh.\r\niii)  Identification of best genotypes of buffalo for dairy purpose in Bangladesh.\r\niv)  Improvement of productivity of buffaloes used for dairy purpose in Bangladesh through improvement of environment factors (Hygeine, Nutrition, reproduction and management).', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 2124000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Genetics and Plant  Breeding', 'Buffaloes', '', '', ''),
(1032, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Livestock', 'Project', 'Development of the Multiple Ovulation Embryo Transfer Techniques in the Bovine in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-09-1998', '31-08-2001', '01-01-1998', '31-03-2001', 'i)  The response of zebu cattle to standard superovulatory treatment. Selected zebu cattle in good health (both general and gynaecological) will be treated with FSH-prostaphlandin F2a zebu cows. Efforts will be made to use locally produced serum to avoid the hazard of incorporatiing exotic diseases through importation of serum.\r\nii)  The effect of different gonadotropin prreparations on the superovulatory response of zebu cors, Gonadotropins, like FSH and PMSG will be tested in different preparation at various dose levels for their efficacies in repeated superovulatory treatment of a certain number of cors. Data obtained will be evaluated with regard to the number of transferable quality embryos per unit price. The cost-effective gonadotropin preparation with easy applicability will be selected for routine MOET programmes.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1515000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Cellular Biotechnology', 'Bovines', '', '', ''),
(1029, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Fisheries', 'Project', 'Investigation on the diseases of some small indigenous freshwater fishes of Bangladesh', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-02-1998', '31-01-2001', '01-02-1999', '30-04-2001', 'a) To investigate the nature and extent of disease in clarious, puntius, nundus, anabus &amp; channa species from Mymensingh area.\r\nb) To identify the consative agent associated with disease.\r\nc) To find out relationship between histopathological changes with parasitic infection.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Fish Diseases', 'Fish Disease', '', '', ''),
(1030, 'Rajshahi University', 'Fisheries', 'Project', 'Development of hatchery and culture technique for freshwater prawn, Macrobrachium Malcolmsonii H. Mine Edwards.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-1998', '31-01-2001', '', '31-01-2001', 'a) Collection and identification of prawn seed from natural water.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nb) Brood stocking for spawning in the hatchery condition.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nc) Water qualdity analysis of the nursery and stocking ponds.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nd) Larval rearing with supplementary feeds.&lt;br /&gt;\r\ne) To develop appropriate technique to minimize the mortality rate of prawn.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 600000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Fish Breeding', 'Prawns', '', '', ''),
