(1001, 'Bangladesh Rice Research Institute', 'AgEng', 'Project', 'Development of suitable salinity management techniques and their environmental impact assessment on the coastal ecosystem of Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-02-1998', '31-01-2001', '01-03-1998', '28-02-2001', 'i) Identification of the existing farmers salinity management practices at farm level and determination of its improvement potentiality in the coastal area. \r\nii) Performance evaluation of different on-farm salinity management techniques and its suitability by using available saline surface and groundwater in the coastal area. \r\niii) Determination of both surface and groundwater salinity i variation pattern. \r\niv) Development of suitable techniques for managing shallow saline aquifers to increasing the irrigation potentiality in the coastal area.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1400000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Irrigation Engg. and Water Management', '', '', '', ''),
(1000, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'AgEng', 'Project', 'Improvement of the water resources management for a sustainable rice-wheat system in Dinajpur &amp; Jessore area.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-03-1998', '28-02-2001', '01-03-1998', '30-04-2001', 'i) To assess the present status of irrigation and water management practices for rice-wheat systems and identify the major constraints to irrigated rice and wheat cultivation in rice-wheat cropping system.\r\n\r\nii) To improve the land and water productivity for sustainable rice-wheat system and improve water use efficiency at crop, farm and system level, through the improvement of water distribution, application and irrigation scheduling.  \r\n\r\niii) To study the effect of delay drainage of floodwater, water logging and salinity on Rice-wheat system in the field. \r\n\r\niv) To study the effect of duration of water logging at different growth stages of wheat on its yield.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Irrigation Engg. and Water Management', '', '', '', ''),
