(1303, 'Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Agricultural University', 'Agricultural Economics Division', 'Project', 'Socio-Economic Assessment of Arsenic Contamination in Some Selected Areas of Bangladesh', 'Chandpur and Faridpur', 'High', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-05-2009', '30-06-2010', '01-05-2009', '30-06-2010', 'a. To assess the level of arsenic contamination in crop production and understand the magnitude of land degradation due to arsenic contamination in the sampled areas of Bangladesh.\r\nb. To understand the possible effect of arsenic contamination of crop production and estimate the productivity differences between contaminated and non-contaminated rice farms int he study areas, and\r\nc. To delineate farmers'' practices/coping mechanism in overcoming the problem of arsenic contamination in crop production.', 'Study area selection: Kachua (Chandpur), Bhanga and Faridpur Sadar (Faridpur district), Upazila were selected for carrying gout in depth socio-economics survey.\r\nSampling and data: Collected data were scrutinized, edited and compiled using appropriate software tools.\r\nAnalytical tools: Both descriptive and inferential statistics were employed in analyzing the data\r\nTest of Significance and Profitability analysis.', '', 'Socio -Economics, Arsenic, Assessment of Arsenic, Arsenic contamination', 'IRRI', 300000, 300000, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Agricultural Policy and Development', 'Rice', '', '', ''),
