(971, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'AERS', 'Project', 'NGO,s involvement in agricultural sector in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Demonstrative', 'Completed', '01-06-1999', '31-05-2000', '01-10-1999', '31-03-2001', 'a)	To prepare an inventory (profile) of various NGOs operating in Bangladesh and to categorize them according to local, regional, national and international. \r\n\r\nb)	To make a comparative analysis of the objectives and programmes particularly in agricultural sector of the NGOs working in the country.\r\n	\r\nc)	To identify the target beneficiaries (both men and women) of different NGOs and to assess how these beneficiaries are being served by the NGOs.\r\n\r\nd)	To list the major agricultural progremmes of the NOGs and to determine the extent of complementarily, competitiveness, or overlappingness of these programmes with the mainstream government programmes.\r\n\r\ne)	To determine the opinions/reactions of the target beneficiaries about their concerned NGOs.\r\n\r\nf)	To suggest some policy guidelines for the government agencies and the NGOs so as to enable the NGOs to act as collaborative development partners with the GOs.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 831000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Impact Study', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(969, 'Rajshahi University', 'AERS', 'Project', 'Socio- economic assessment of improved sugarcane production technology and identification of constaints of higher production in Bangladesh .', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-02-1999', '31-12-2001', '', '31-05-2001', 'a)	To know the ownership and utilization pattern of the available resources of sugarcane farmers.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nb)	To determine the per hectare costs and returns of sugarcane production.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nc)	To determine the yield gap and the causes of variation in costs and returns and other constraints of producing higher production among the farmers.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nd)	Resource use efficiency in sugarcane production by different farm sizes.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\ne)	To identify the constraints to adoption of sugarcane production technology.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nf)	To study the impact of modern sugarcane production technology of BSRI on income and employment of sugarcane farmers.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\ng)	To study the impact of modern sugarcane production technology of BSRI on income and employment of sugarcane farmers.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 453850, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Socio Economics', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(968, 'Bangladesh Academy for Rural Development', 'AERS', 'Project', 'Changing agrarian communities in Bangladesh : A study on farm families social values and polarization .', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-06-1999', '31-05-2001', '', '30-06-2001', 'Major Objectives\r\na)To know and focus the changes occurred in the agrarian communities.\r\nb)To know the changes in this communities due to intervention.\r\nc)To understand the changes if any without any interventions.\r\nThe specific objective of the study:\r\na)To identify the impact of internal and external factors on socio-economic life of the agrarian communities.\r\n', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1535600, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Anthropology', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(967, 'Dhaka University', 'AERS', 'Project', 'A Study on the fertilizer distribution and pricing policy in Bangladesh: current state of the art and overhaulling needed for a bright future.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-07-1999', '31-12-2000', '', '30-04-2001', 'a)	Analyse the spread between farm gate price and retailers price by investigating costs associated with different stages of fertiliser marketing.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nb)	Analyse the fertiliser crisis from perspectives of farmers and dealers.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nc)	Investigate the fertiliser procurement system and implied transaction costs associated with this procurement system.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nd)	Examine the nature, features and the extent of efficiency of the present privatised fertiliser distribution system.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\ne)	Examine the impact of use of the fertiliser and other inputs in general and timely availability of fertiliser in particular on production and income of farmers.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nf)	Present a comparative analysis of availability and prices of fertilisers in easy access areas and remotely access areas in peak and lean seasons.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\ng)	Ascertain how far the farmers had to travel during the peak season to buy fertiliser and what the implied transportation costs associated with such traveling were?&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nh)	Assess to what extant the timely availability of fertilisers in adequate quantity is linked to efficient and optimal use the of fertiliser and in that respect how the do farmers judge the present system relative to other two systems. &lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\ni)	Ascertain if the farmers think that (a)  new system of distribution is better than the previous system (quantify in terms of percentage); and (b) whether they are satisfied with the present system; and if not, recommend measurers to remove the constraints.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 727000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Pricing', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(965, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'AERS', 'Project', 'Impact of NGOs on Socio-Economic Development of Target Population in Some Selected Areas of Bangladesh', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-06-1998', '31-12-2001', '01-07-1998', '31-03-2000', 'i)  To explore the various objectives of the selected NGO,s\r\nii)  To study the income and employment  generation potentials of the NGOs.\r\niii)  To examine the success of the NGOs in overall production increases and poverty alleviaation which resulted from their programme activities.\r\niv)   To investigate the  impact of the NGO activities  on poverty allevation income  generation and up gradation of the gender status of the women of the participant households.\r\nv)  To make an over all comparative study of the performance of the selected NGOs.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 403000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Socio Economics', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(966, 'Khulna University', 'AERS', 'Project', 'Shrimp culture and changes of landuse pattern in costal belt of Bangladesh: A spatio- temporal analysis.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-03-1999', '28-02-2001', '01-04-1999', '30-09-2000', '1. To monitor the landuse changes in the study area over a period of twenty four years (retrospective landuse survey, 1975, 1985, 1995 and todate) and to find the trend of changes through time.\r\n2. To identify the factors influencing socio-economic and physical causing of landuse changes.\r\n3. To identify and assess the ecological effects on fisheries activities diversity, vegetation and animal habitat.\r\n4. To identify and assess the physico-chemical effects on situation, water logging, soil fertility and salinity.\r\n5. To identify and assess the physico-chemical effects on agricultural land, agricultural production, land ownership pattern, employment and navigation.\r\n6. To provide some policy guidelines in order to protect the natural environment and provide some suggestions for planned and controlled shrimp culture activities.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1107400, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Socio Economics', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(963, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'AERS', 'Project', 'Economics of milk production in Bangladesh', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-07-1998', '30-06-2000', '01-07-1998', '30-06-2000', '1. To examine the existing milk production system in Bangladesh.\r\n2. To determine private profitability of milk production with local and cross-breed animals.\r\n3. To determine social pprofitability of milk production with local and cross-breed animals.\r\n4. To identify potentials of and constraints to dairy development within the existing livestock development policy in Bangladesh.\r\n5. To suggest policy measures for improving dairy development consistent with the socio-economic environment prevailing in the country.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 446000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Production Economics', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(964, 'Bangladesh Rice Research Institute', 'AERS', 'Project', 'Crop cultivation practices: Input-Output Relationship of Major Crops of Bangladesh(Component-I)', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-10-1998', '31-03-2000', '01-07-1998', '30-06-2001', '(1) To estimate the productivity of paddy, wheat, jute, sugarcane, pulse and other crops.\r\n(2) To estimate the cost of production and returns to the above mentioned crop.\r\n(3) To study the inter relationship between inputs and output of crops.\r\n(4) To develop input-output matrix of different crop cultivation.\r\n(5) To examine the resource utilization patterns at the farm level. \r\n(6) To derive policy implication from the above.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 717000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Economics', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(962, 'Bangladesh Tea Research Institute', 'AERS', 'Project', 'A study to assess the socio-economic status in the context of working efficiency of tea workers in Bangladesh', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-06-1998', '31-12-1999', '01-06-1998', '30-04-2000', 'a)	To find out the living condition of the tea workers.\r\n\r\nb)	To measure the efficiency of the tea workers.\r\n\r\nc)	To find out the ways and means to increase the efficiency of the tea workers.\r\n\r\nd)	To assess the social and economic condition under which the tea workers work.\r\n\r\ne)	To identify the relationship between the workers and the management', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 671640, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Socio Economics', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(961, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'AERS', 'Project', 'Impact of field demonstrations conducted by the Department of Agricutlural Extension.', '', '', 'Demonstrative', 'Completed', '01-03-1998', '31-08-1999', '01-05-1998', '31-03-2000', 'i)  To determine the extent of success of the DAE conducted demonstrations as perceived by the farmers and Block Supervisors.\r\nii)  To determine the impact of the demonstrations in terms of the following:\r\n gain in knowledge by the farmer\r\n yield/income obtained by the farmer\r\n continuation of the use of technology demonstrated by the farmer in subsequent       \r\n seasons/years\r\n number of surrounding fellow farmers adopted the technology.\r\niii)  To determine the cost-benefit ratio of the technologies demonstrated.\r\niv)  To determine the success and failure factors of the DAE demonstrations.\r\nv)  To determine the profile characteristics of the farmers selected for conducting demonstrations.\r\nvi)  To determine the motivation of the farmers in conducting demonstrations.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 400000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agricultural Extension', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(960, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'AERS', 'Project', 'A study on the effects of price and non-price factors on the production of crops in Bangladesh: a pooled time-series and cross-section analysis.', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-03-1998', '31-10-1999', '01-04-1998', '31-03-2000', 'i)  Assessing the relative growth performance of the major and minor crops and to delineate the factors affecting individual crop growth acceleration/deceleration or stagnancy. \r\nii)  Evaluating the impact of price and non-price factors (expected yield, rainfall and risk factors), and revenue on area allocations among crops.\r\niii)  Estimating the performance of aggregate crops output supply in terms of changing agricultural terms of trade, development of markets and technological development in agriculture. \r\niv)  Estimating the area response elasticites according  to different sizes of farm Tholdings.\r\nv)  Suggest policy measures to the government aiming a breakthrough in agricultural development in terms of increased growth commensurating the supporting growth in the non-farm sector  meeting the demand for sustainable overall development during the early 21st century.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 466000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Economics', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(958, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'AERS', 'Project', 'Marketing and Economic Use of Pesticides and Their Impact on Crop Productivity.', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-04-1997', '31-03-2000', '01-12-1997', '31-03-2000', 'i)  To identify the channels of pesticides marketing.\r\nii)  To measure the efficiency of marketing.\r\niii)  To observe the type, timing, frequency of pesticides application at farm level\r\niv)  To examine the storage and safety practice of the farmers and incidence of pesticides poisoning among them.\r\nv)  To estimate the relationship between pesticides use and crop productivity.\r\nvi)  To evaluate the integrated pest management technologies in Bangladesh.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1060000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Marketing', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(959, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'AERS', 'Project', 'Identification of Appropriate Homestead Farming Technologies and the Barriers in Diffusing Those among the Rural Women.', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-01-1997', '31-12-1997', '01-05-1998', '30-04-1999', 'i)  To identify and assess the appropriate homestead technologies for horticultural production (seed preparation, seed storage, transplanting, compost utilization, plant protection and water use, etc.), poultry raising (breeds, feeding, housing, caring and managemnet, etc.) and livestock rearing (breed, feeding, caring and management, etc.), minipond fisheries being used by the rural women.\r\nii)  To findout the extent of diffusion of these production technologies.\r\niii)  To explore different personal, social, economic and technological barriers or constraints faced by the users in utilizing the technologies.\r\niv)  To suggest some way and means to solve constraints in homestead production and utilization.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 220000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agricultural Extension', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(956, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'AERS', 'Project', 'Marketing of Major Fruits in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-07-1997', '30-06-2000', '01-01-1998', '31-05-2001', 'i)  To study institutions and channels of fruits marketing;\r\nii)  To know the trend and seasonal variations of prices\r\niii)  To quantify the post-harvest losses of fruits;\r\niv)  To find out the marketing efficiency;\r\nv)  To identify the marketing problems of fruits both at farmers and traders level; and\r\nvi) To suggest implications of the findings of the study.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 728000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Marketing', 'Flood', '', '', ''),
(957, 'Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute', 'AERS', 'Project', 'Womens Participation in Raising Livestock in Some Selected Areas of Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-10-1997', '31-03-1999', '01-03-1998', '30-06-2000', '1. To determine the contribution of women in animal husbandry.\r\n2. To analyse the livestock processing activities carried out by women.\r\n3. To determine the incentive that motivate the family members to participate in livestock raising and processing activities.\r\n4. To determine the contribution of women in family income through livestock raising.\r\n5. To ascertain the magnitude of consumption of livestock products from own source.\r\n6. To suggest suitable policy measures for encouraging women''s participation in livestock rearing and processing.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 818400, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Gender', 'Socio-economics', '', '', ''),
(1296, 'Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Agricultural University', 'Agricultural Economics Division,', 'Project', 'Rice production situations in different Agricultural Regions of Bangladesh', 'Seven Production Environments', 'High', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-02-2007', '30-06-2009', '01-02-2007', '30-06-2009', 'a.	To estimate the total supply of paddy/rice and quantity consumed per capita per day at the household levels;\r\nb.	To identify rice deficit/surplus area in Bangladesh with a view to develop production and marketing strategies for the country;\r\nc.	To determine the present storage capacity and actual quantity of paddy stored at the farm levels with the benefits derived; and\r\nd.	To suggest necessary policy guidelines.\r\n', 'A nation-wide survey of different production environment s of Bangladesh (i. e.  non-flood, drought, Flood prone, drought prone, Saline Tidal-submergence, Hilly area and Flash flood) was conducted with the financial assistance from Bangladesh Agricultural Research Council (BARC). The reort presented here is based on primary level data collected from 240 sample farms of the sample villages were selected randomly on the basis of availability at home during the survey. The Selected farmers were then interviewed using a set of structural questionnaire which were prepared and pre-tested in advance. The collected data were then coded, entered into the computer using Microsoft Excel program and validated using the computer program. Finally, the data were analyzed using SPSS and presented in tabular form.', '', 'Agricultural Regions, Rice production, Environments, Agricultural Poligy, ', 'BARC', 100000, 100000, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Agricultural Policy and Development', 'Rice', '', '', ''),
(955, 'Soil Resources Development Institute', 'SOIL', 'Project', 'Study on the effect of sediments deposited during devastating flood in 1998 .', '', 'High', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-12-1998', '31-08-1999', '01-12-1998', '31-08-1999', 'The program was undertaken with a view to detrimental effect if any, of the sediments laid down during recent flood through different river system of Bangladesh in general and in particular to determine the\r\na)  Physical and chemical properties of sediments.\r\nb) Increase of soil fertility through the availability of plant nutrient elements.\r\nc) Increase of organic matter through the accumulation and decomposition of BGA/plant and animal residues.\r\nd) Detrimental effect, if any, due to coarser sedimentation.\r\ne) Management practices to the farmers.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 718000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Fertility Management', 'Flood', '', '', ''),
(953, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'AERS', 'Project', 'Crop Cultivation Practices : Input Output Relationship of Major Crops of Bangladesh (Component -2).', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-07-1998', '30-06-2000', '01-10-1998', '31-12-2000', 'a)	To estimate the productivity of potato, wheat, maize, vegetables, oilseed and pulses.\r\n\r\nb)	To estimate the cost of production and returns to the above mentioned crops.\r\n\r\nc)	To study the inter relationship between inputs and output of mentioned crops.\r\n\r\nd)	To examine the resource utilization patterns at farm level.\r\n\r\ne)	To derive policy implication from the above.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 817000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Economics', '', '', '', ''),
(952, 'Bangladesh Academy for Rural Development', 'AERS', 'Project', 'Techniques of Overcoming Rice Yield Stagnancy.', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-07-2000', '30-06-2001', '', '', 'a)	To identify the real factors (both technical and social) associated with rice yield stagnancy for some of the AEZs of Bangladesh.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nb)	To find the gap between the available and recommended technologies for rice cultivation.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nc)	To search the zone-wise appropriate technologies/strategies emphasising the use of organic fertilizers and modern irrigation technologies and to train the farmers through demonstrations and field visits.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nd)	To highlight the real zone-wise environmental consequences for imbalanced uses of modern inputs.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 600000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Economics', '', '', '', ''),
(951, 'Bangladesh Sericulture Research and Training Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Introduction of appropriate technologies to improve the productivity of silk.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-1999', '30-06-2001', '01-07-1999', '', 'a)	Improvement of mulberry plants and multiplication of bivoltine/hybrid silkworms for the target sericultureists.\r\n\r\nb)	Strategies of micro-environment management of bivoltine/hybrid by the target sericulturists.\r\n\r\nc)	Selection and multiplication of viable parent lines of bivoltine/hybrid suitable for Bangladesh condition (ie. four seasons).\r\n\r\nd)	Improvement of micro-environment in mounting room.\r\n\r\ne)	Quantitative and qualitative improvement of commercial cocoons for more economic returns to the sericulturists.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 2000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', 'Silk worm', '', '', ''),
