(934, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Germplasm evaluation, production and storage technology of jackfruit.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-1999', '31-12-2000', '01-01-1999', '', 'a)	To study on growth behaviour of trees, physio-chemical characteristics of fruits of the existing 64 clones in the BAU jackfruit orchard for final selection as varieties.\r\n\r\nb)	To study on floral biology, pollination and fruit development of the clones.\r\n\r\nc)	To develop a suitable method for storage of fruit, bulb and seed.\r\n\r\nd)	To determine an optimum irrigation schedule.\r\n\r\ne)	Transfer of production technology to farmers/interested growers.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 662000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Horticulture', 'Jackfruit; Castard apple.', '', '', ''),
(935, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Study on the post harvest fruit rot of banana and its control .', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-1999', '31-12-2000', '27-01-1999', '', 'The objective of the study is to develop an integrated approach for management of post-harvest fruit rot disease of banana. To achieve the main objective, the following specific objectives are set.\r\na)	To identify and characterize the post-harvest fruit rot diseases of 3 banana varieties (i.e. Amrita Sagar-Sabri and Chinee Champa).\r\n\r\nb)	To determine the factors that affect the post-harvest fruit rots of banana.\r\n\r\nc)	To find out the cause of tissue hardening of ripe banana fruits.\r\n\r\nd)	To formulate the most suitable/appropriate methods to minimize post-harvest rot diseases.\r\n\r\ne)	To analyze the economic and nutritional status of banana fruits affected with post harvest rot diseases.\r\n\r\nf)	To determine the cause of black-sporting of banana.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Post Harvest', 'Banana', '', '', ''),
(933, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Characterization and evaluation of jute, kenaf and mesta germplasm.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-04-1999', '31-03-2001', '01-05-1999', '', 'The aim of the project is to strengthen the genetic resources activities of jute, kenaf and mesta germplasm for the genetic improvement through identification of desired morpho-agronomic attributes, screening for diseases and pests tolerance, identification through bio-chemical analysis and quality fibre test.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 2000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Physiology and Biochemistry', 'Jute', '', '', ''),
(932, 'Bangladesh Rice Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Expanded farming system research and development programme for technology dissemination in greater extrapolation areas of FSRD site at Kapasia, Gazipur.', '', '', 'Demonstrative', 'Completed', '01-07-2000', '31-12-2001', '01-07-2000', '', '1. To disseminate technologies in extrapolation areas for increasing output and income.\r\n2. To promote integrated approach to increase farm productivity.\r\n3. To improve farm skill of the extension providers as well as farmers.\r\n4. To strengthen linkage among researchers, extension providers and farmers to expedite technology transfer process.\r\n5. To develop agri-business and enterprenuership in farming.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 2345140, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'FSRD', '', '', '', ''),
(931, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Antiserum production of potato viruses S, X, Y and PLRV and establishment of detection methods of viruses.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-03-1999', '28-02-2001', '01-04-1999', '', 'i)	To find out the occurrence of different potato viruses with their strains in different locations of Bangladesh and to produce antiserum against the major potato viruses.\r\n\r\nii)	To establish serological detection methods for potato viruses and to develop ELISA kit for PSV, PXV, PYV and PLRV for rapid diagnosis of these viruses.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 2000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Vorology', 'Potatoes', '', '', ''),
(930, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'An integrated approach for the management of Anthracnose and wilt disease of guava.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-04-1999', '31-03-2001', '01-04-1999', '', 'a)	Survey on the incidence of anthracnose and wilt disease in different varieties of guava grown in different regions in order to find out varietal and regional variation in occurrence of the diseases and to collect the disease specimen and seedlings of different guava varieties.\r\n\r\nb)	Management of anthracnose and wilt disease of guava through varietal resistance, organic and inorganic soil amendments and soil and plant treatments.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Technology', 'Guava', '', '', ''),
(929, 'Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Controlling mosaic disease of sugarcane germplam.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-02-1998', '31-01-2000', '01-02-1999', '', 'a)	To find out appropriate control measures of mosaic disease of sugarcane.\r\n\r\nb)	To find out the effective time temperature  combination of serial hot water treatment in controlling the SCMV.\r\n\r\nc)	To assess the efficacy of serial hot water treatment in controlling mosaic in plant cane and subsequent generation.\r\n\r\nd)	To build up and maintain a mosaic free germplasm bank to broaden the scope of hybridization to develop mosaic free clones and subsequent release as variety. The ensured mosaic free clones can be mutually exchanged among the SAARC countries.\r\n\r\ne)	To control mosaic disease of sugarcane in Breeder Seed for subsequent supply to the mill and non mill zones. \r\n\r\nf)	To recommend the cane growers to use the disease free seed for controlling of mosaic disease.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 600000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Technology', 'Sugarcane', '', '', ''),
(928, 'Bangladesh Rice Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Research and development of rice varieties for coastal salinity.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-01-1999', '31-12-2000', '01-01-1999', '', 'a)	Determine the maximum level of salinity tolerance of the coastal popular rice varieties for using them in diallel crossing design to produce saline tolerant progenies.\r\n\r\nb)	Isolate improved progenies from F2 and onward segregating populations at a salinity level of 8-10 dS/m.\r\n\r\nc)	Identify general and specific combiners for yield and its component characters among the highest salinity tolerant local rice varieties.\r\n\r\nd)	Develop salinity tolerant improved genotypes and conduct farmers participatory research to evaluate the existing advance breeding lines at coastal districts.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 845300, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Breeding', 'Rice', '', '', ''),
(927, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Collection and improvement of variety and production package of Grape', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-1999', '30-06-2001', '01-07-1999', '', 'a)	Collection of grape varieties.\r\n\r\nb)	Selection of superior lines suitable for cultivation in Bangladesh ecological condition.\r\n\r\nc)	Preparation of grape cultivation procedure.\r\n\r\nd)	Make available the seedlings/saplings for the farmers.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1992000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Breeding', 'Fruits', '', '', '');
