(926, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Development of export oriented production technology and packing methodology of pineapple.', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-02-1999', '31-01-2001', '01-02-1999', '', 'a)	To standardise the exportable size and quality of pineapple.\r\n\r\nb)	To ensure year round supply of pineapple.\r\n\r\nc)	To develop short term storing method.\r\n\r\nd)	To develop exportable packing device and packing method.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1051000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', 'Pineapples', '', '', ''),
(925, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Coordinated Research on Insecticide Residue and Resistance in Major Vegetable Grown in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-1997', '30-06-2000', '01-01-1998', '', 'A. Field Survey:\r\ni) Documentation of the existing pattern (kind, dose, frequency etc.) of insecticide      usage on vegetables;\r\nii) Identification of problem areas (hot spots) and causes of overusing insecticides.\r\n\r\nB. Residue Analysis:\r\ni)    Providing a holistic insecticide residue situation on soil, ground water,harvested vegetables and consumers blood;\r\nii) generation of residue data and comparison with MRL set by FAO/WHO. Dissemination of such data to end users to make awareness among growers and consumers concerning insecticide residue levels in consumable vegetables.\r\n\r\nC.  Detection and Monitoring of resistance:\r\ni) Collection and rearing of target insect pests (BSFB, and DBM) of problem   areas;\r\nii) Establishment of base-line toxicity;\r\niii) Development of appropriate method for the detection of resistance;\r\niv) Monitoring of resistance/cross resistance over time and space to understand the distribution and changes in the frequency of resistance;\r\nv) Identification of hot spots of resistant bio-types.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 2100000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Effect of Insecticides', 'Vegetable', '', '', ''),
(924, 'Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Studies on the Date Palm and Palmyra Palm Trees in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-10-1997', '30-09-2000', '01-11-1997', '', '1. To find out appropriate management practices of date palm and palmyra palm trees to enhance juice secretion and gur recovery without lossing the quality.\r\n2. To find out effective &quot;type of cut&quot; to enhance juice secretion and to get higher quantity of gur.\r\n3. To find out low cost appropriate preservation technique of date palm and palmyra palm.\r\n4. Plantation of noble date palm (Phoenix dectylifera) along with wild date palm (Phoenix sylvestris).', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1490400, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Horticulture', '', '', '', ''),
(923, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Screening of Brassica germplasm for saline tolerance and their possible use as or in commercial varieties.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-1997', '30-06-2000', '24-01-1998', '', 'i)  To test a good number good number of B. capestris, B. Juncea and B napus  varieties/ germplasms against  different levels of salinity at the seedling stage. This is to identify the resistant or moderately resistant ones at the initial stage of plant growth .\r\nii)  To test a number of varieties/germplasms (already identified as resistant or moderately resistant in the seedling stage) against different levels of salinity at the vegetative, fruiting and ripening stage. This is to identify the resistant or moderately resistant varieties/ germplasms up to maturity stage.\r\niii)  To identify the major morphological characters which influence in salt tolerance This to transfer the character(s) to a commercial variety.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 250000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Genetics and Plant  Breeding', 'Oil Seed', '', '', ''),
(921, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Collection, evaluation, conservation and improvement of gladiolus flower', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-07-1997', '31-12-1999', '16-06-1998', '', '(1) To optimize spacing, planting time, nutritional management as well as irrigation scheduling for higher productivity of the crop.\r\n(2) To develop all cultural management suitable for higher production of corn and cormels.\r\n(3) Development of protocol regarding post-harvest technology like cauliflower, corm etc.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 500000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Floriculture', '', '', '', ''),
(920, 'Bangladesh Rice Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Upland aus rice culture in the coastal saline area in Bangladesh', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '20-05-1998', '19-11-2000', '20-05-1998', '', 'a)	Study the adaptability of some BRRI and BINA varieties of rice under different saline conditions of some coastal districts (Noakhali, Feni) during the Kharif-I (Aus) seasons.\r\n\r\nb)	Develop some cultural practices which will admit the HYV rice to be grown under the adverse edaphic condition of salinity and drought.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 500000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', 'Rice', '', '', ''),
(919, 'Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Biological Nitrogen Fixation (BNF) Studies in Sugarcane', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-1998', '31-12-2000', '01-07-1998', '', 'a)	to develop suitable methodologies for screening out sugarcane clones with proven-capability of Biological Nitrogen Fixation (BNF).\r\n\r\nb)	To find out the inherent BNF-potential, if any, of the existing germplasm, commercial hybrids and promising clones through lab and field testing..\r\n\r\nc)	Isolation and characterization of N-fixing bacteria in sugarcane.\r\n\r\nd)	Multiplication of BNF-endowed cane varieties through tissue culture and other rapid multiplication procedures.\r\n\r\ne)	To identify potential parents (with BNF-capability) which could be used as sources of BNF-endowment for future breeding programme.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1200000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Physiology and Biochemistry', 'Sugarcane', '', '', ''),
(918, 'Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Effectiveness of selected technology transfer approaches for the diffusion of modern sugarcane cultivation practices', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-04-1998', '31-03-1998', '01-04-1998', '', '(1) To measure the effectiveness of selected technology transfer approaches affecting the diffusion of modern sugarcane cultivation practices.\r\n(2) To identify appropriate technology transfer approaches for the small, medium and large farmers.\r\n(3) To generate baseline information on knowledge, attitude and practices (adoption) of both modern and indigenous sugarcane production technologies in the study locations.\r\n(4) To generate baseline information on farmers socio-economic profiles e.g. farm size, income, extension contact, social participation, production and marketing of sugarcane and other related information.\r\n(5) To determine the influence and contribution of selected socio-economic, personal, organizational and other factors affecting knowledge, attitude and adoption behavior of small, medium and large farmers.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 500000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Education, Extension and Advisory Work', 'Sugarcane', '', '', ''),
(917, 'Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Sugarcane Response to Salinity', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-05-1998', '30-04-2001', '01-05-1998', '', 'a)	To study the effects of NaCl concentrations on sugarcane growth and to establish critical concentration of NaCl for sugarcane. \r\n\r\n	b)	To identify the basic morphological and physiological characteristics of sugarcane plant that controls salinity tolerance.\r\n\r\n	c)	To assess the effects of rising salinity to tissue mineral composition.\r\n\r\nd)	To determine a suitable rapid and defendable methods of screening of sugarcane crop against salinity tolerance.\r\n\r\ne)	To quantitatively partition the significance of change in net assimilation a assimilatory area to growth changes resulting from rooting medium salinity.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1200000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', 'Sugarcane', '', '', ''),
(916, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Microclimatic manipulation and adaptation of quality protein maize (QPM) under dry-land conditions', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-01-1998', '31-12-2000', '01-01-1998', '', 'i)  under  rice straw  rice husk, ash and water hyacinth mulches.\r\nii)  Monitoring of soil temperature and soil moisture contents with and without mulching materials.\r\niii)  Estimation of chlorophyll contents and their stability index under different conditions.\r\niv)  After mulch analysis of soil organic matter &amp; nutrient contents.\r\n\r\nGrowing of QPM  and a local cultivars under  dry-land conditions to assess their     relative performances', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', 'Maize', '', '', ''),
(915, 'Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Agricultural University', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Collection, characterization, conservation, and yield and nutritive value evaluation of under-exploited fruits in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-02-1998', '31-01-2001', '15-02-1998', '', 'a)	To survey and collect the germplasms of the under exploited fruits species.\r\n\r\nb)	To characterize the available indigenous fruit species in Bangladesh.\r\n\r\nc)	To find out the yield potential of the under exploited fruits.\r\n\r\nd)	To determine the nutritive value of the under exploited fruits. \r\n\r\ne)	To take integrated approach for increasing plantation and production of off session indigenous fruits like anona, hogplum and olive.\r\n\r\nf)	To emphasis for planting more under exploited fruits for preserving environment, improving nutrition and generating farmers income.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 600000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Horticulture', 'Fruits', '', '', ''),
(913, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Development of off-season mango variety.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-03-1998', '28-02-2001', '01-06-1998', '', 'i) To develop off-season variety (ies)\r\nii)  To get the fresh fruits in lean period and also to lengthen the period of availability of fresh fruits.\r\niii)  For year round production', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 600000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Horticulture', 'Mangoes', '', '', ''),
(914, 'University of Chittagong', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Exploration of biodiversity in aroids, yams, ipomoeas and zingibers from Bangladesh for their conservation and domestication towards sustainable development.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-02-1998', '31-01-2000', '09-02-1998', '', 'i)  Exploration, identification, and documentation of distribution of lesser used, underutilized and under exploited wild crop resources in aroids. yams ipomoeas and zingibers from Bangladesh.\r\nii)  Documentation of indigenous knowledge of user, cultivation management and conservation \r\niii)  Centralization of germplasm as ex- situ conservation and genetic resources for future crop development research programme.\r\niv)  Cytological investigation\r\nv)  Biochemical investigation\r\nvi) Recommendation for domestication.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 300000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Horticulture', '', '', '', ''),
(912, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Mango research and development', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-01-1998', '31-12-2000', '25-01-1998', '', 'a)	To control alternate bearing in mango.\r\nb)	To increase fruit set and reduce fruit drop in mango.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 400000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Horticulture', 'Mangoes', '', '', ''),
(910, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Adaptive Research for year round fruits and vegetables production in hilly region', '', '', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-07-1998', '31-12-2000', '01-07-1998', '', 'i)  Study adaptability of selected fruits and vegetables varieties in hill region.\r\nii)   Study the sustainability of these technologies in hill sloes\r\niii)  Collect fruits and vegetables germplasms from hill region as well as other parts of the country and evaluate the same at hill Agricultural Research Station Khagrachari.\r\niv)  Impart training on adoption of developed technologies  to the farmers of hill region.\r\nv)  Propagate the existing suitable varieties of fruits and vegetables and distribute those among the hill farmers', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 2000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Horticulture', 'Fruits', '', '', ''),
