(459, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'EVALUATION OF ADVANCED STRAINS/VARIETIES IN DIFFERENT AEZ IN DIFFERENT SEASONS.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Evaluation on the performance of advanced strains of Kenaf and mesta in respect of yield and adaptability in farmers fields.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(460, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'BREEDING FOR HIGH BIOMASS PRODUCING STRAINS OF KENAF AND MESTA.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'a) Selection or screen the available genetic resources of kenaf and mesta in respect of high biomass production\r\nb) Evaluation of advanced strains at zonal and advanced yield trial level.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(461, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'BREEDING FOR STRESS TOLERANT KENAF AND MESTA LINES.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'a) Development of less thermo and photosensitive kenaf and Mesta strains.\r\nb) Development of breeding materials resistant to leaf mosaic disease, root-knot  nematode, spiral borer, stem-rot diseases.\r\nc) Development of breeding materials suitable for growing in saline soils.\r\nd) Development of breeding materials of Mesta tolerant to wet foot condition and waterlogging.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(462, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'PARENTAL MATERIALS DEVELOPMENT WITH WIDER GENETIC BACKGROUND.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Searching for, and subsequently incorporating the genetic resources providing (a) photo and thermo insensitivity, especially allowing more flexibility of sowing and harvesting time with optimum biomass formation, \r\n(b) tolerance to problem soils (eg. salinity, root-knot nematode, soil toxicity, wet foot condition, etc.), \r\n(c) small seed size with long duration of seed viability, (d) indehiscence of fruits (mesta), (e) smoothness of plant, fruits.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(463, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'FIELD EVALUATION OF ADVANCED BREEDING LINES FOR YIELD   AND ADAPTABILITY.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To evaluate fibre and seed yield, quality, adaptability and above all  suitability of newly developed advanced breeding line(s) by the members of Field Evaluation Team of NSB through field trials at both farmers'' plots and at regional stations for recognition as superior variety to the existing cultivar(s) in the prevailing 3-cropping pattern for enhanced income generation of the small jute farmers.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(464, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'BREEDING FOR BIOTIC AND ABIOTIC STRESS   TOLERANT TOSSA  JUTE.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Jute crop specially tossa often face different biotic and abiotic stresses. Of which short day &amp; low temperature, waterlogging and drought, mite and diseases are the main ones. These stresses have an adverse effect on the area and production. In order to breed varieties resistant to those stresses this project has been undertaken.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(465, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'BREEDING FOR LATE SEEDING GENOTYPES   OF TOSSA JUTE FOR   MEDIUM-HIGH AND HIGH LAND.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(466, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'DEVELOPMENT OF PARENTAL/BREEDING MATERIALS WITH WIDER  GENETIC BACKGROUND.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'DEVELOPMENT OF PARENTAL/BREEDING MATERIALS WITH WIDER  GENETIC BACKGROUND.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(467, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'VARIETAL  IMPROVEMENT  OF  JUTE,  KENAF AND MESTA THROUGH BIOTECHNOLOGICAL APPROACHES', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1) Production of genetic variants of C. capsularis and C. olitorius, kenaf and mesta through in vitro culture of explants and their utilization in breeding programme for varietal improvement.\r\n2) Production of haploid plants through anther culture\r\n3) Introduction of foreign genes in jute, kenaf and mesta through genetic transformation for crop improvement.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(468, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'ANATOMICAL STUDIES IN RELATION TO FIBRE CONTENT AND QUALITY OF JUTE', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Yield of fibre is dependent on the internal structures of plant i.e. bark thickness, number and area of phloem wedges in the stem. Previous studies indicated that bark thickness and area of phloem wedges are significantly correlated with fibre yield and are proved to be an important criteria for selection of genotypes for higher fibre contents. Study of these anatomical characters have been undertaken for selection of genotypes with higher fibre contents.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(469, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'BREEDER FOR DERIVING GENETIC VARIABILITY IN WHITE JUTE', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To create new genetic materials for utilization  in long term breeding program.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(470, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'BREEDING FOR IMPROVEMENT OF FIBRE QUALITY OF JUTE.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To develop better quality of fibre varieties.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(471, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'PHYSIOLOGICAL SCREENING OF GERMPLASM FOR ENVIRONMENTAL STRESS TOLERANCE.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To fit jutein three crop pattern, it has become essential to shift jute cultivation to late February or early March.To achieve that we require environmental stress tolerant varieties to drought, short days and low temperature. Therefore, the initial task isto screen germplasm materials with tolerance to those conditions. These short listed materials, in future, may be used as parent materials in the breeding programme.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(472, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'STUDIES ON ADAPTABILITY AND SUITABILITY OF 	      GERMPLASM FOR CULTIVATION OF JUTE, KENAF AND MESTA ON MARGINAL LAND.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To study the adaptibility and suitability of germplasm for marginal land cultivation of jute. A marginal land may be saline area or area under waterlogged condition.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(473, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'FLOWERING IN JUTE.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To identify the governing factor of flowering in jute.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(474, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'STUDIES ON JUTE SEED PHYSIOLOGY (PRODUCTION  AND STORAGE).', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ' For jute fibre production, the target is higher vegetative growth and the thumb rule is, higher the vegetative growth, lower the  seed production. Therefore, the newly breed varieties due to their higher vegetative growth for higher fibre production are lower seed producer. Moreover, their response to storage conditions could be different and needs investigation. So, the newly developed varieties needs to be investigated for their seed production response to different climatic condition and storability response to different storage condition.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(475, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'BIOCHEMICAL STUDIES ON THE MOLECULAR BASIS OF  		STRESS TOLERANCE.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To study and isolate the chemical that is resposible for stress tolerance.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(476, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'EVALUATION  OF  PROMISING  STRAINS  OR  VARIETIES  AGAINST SEEDING AND HARVESTING TIME,POPULATION,  DENSITY, ETC.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To evaluate the performance of different advanced strains of jute, kenaf and mesta due to different agronomic manipulations, viz. population density, spacing, time of sowing, time of harvest etc. on yield and quality of fibre in  different agro-ecological zones.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(477, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'CROPPING PATTERN STUDIES WITH DIFFERENT VARIETIES OF JUTE', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Fitting jute varieties as a component crop in the existing cropping patterns to optimize yield', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(478, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'COST  REDUCTION  THROUGH ANIPULATION  OF CULTURAL PRACTICES', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To minimize cost of production through manipulation of agronomic  practices viz. crop combination, land preparation, weeding, thinning, stage of harvest, fertilizer application etc. Reduction of cost of production of fibre is very important to make jute more competi', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(479, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'IMPROVEMENT OF SEED PRODUCTION  TECHNOLOGIES', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Improvement of jute seed production technologies.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(480, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'UPDATING OF FERTILIZER RECOMMENDATION FOR TOSSA AND WHITE JUTE UNDER MAJOR AEZ.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'The fertilizer recommendation is generally made for sustaining higher yield of crops. But the fertility status of the soil may changed in different AEZ under different agricultural practices. Again the nutritional requirement of newly improved varieties may also be different in different situations. Therefore, this project has been undertaken to find out the nutritional requirement of newly developed varieties of jute.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(481, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'UP-DATING OF FERTILIZER RCOMMENDATION  OF SEED PRODUCTION OF JUTE, KENAF AND MESTA FOR DIFFERENT AEZ.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Frequently Bangladesh is facing jute seed scarcity. For large scale production of seed, modern technology is needed. Bangladesh Jute Research Institute has developed late jute seed production technology. A balanced fertilizer is needed for maximum seed yield per unit plot. So this project has been under taken for recommendation  of fertilizer for seed production.of jute, kenaf and mesta .', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(482, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'MANAGEMENT OF ORGANIC MATTER FOR JUTE CULTIVATION.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'For productivity of crops organic matter in soil is essentially needed which is chiefly derived from decaying of plant materials. Even the most productive land may gradually became less productive due to intensive cropping, inadequate supply of moisture, excess acidity, salinity and improper management practices. Organic matter improves the physical properties of soil. Therefore, constant efforts should be needed in supplementary the degraded soil with proper application of agricultural wastes for increasing food and fibre production. This projects has been initiated (i) to enrich organic matter content of soil \r\n(ii) to substitute chemical fertilizers for organic matter (iii) to enrich physical, chemical and biological condition of soil.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(483, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'MANAGEMENT OF PROBLEM SOIL FOR JUTE KENAF /MESTA CULTIVATION', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'The problem soils of Bangladesh consists of acid sulphate saline and peat soil. About 6.7 and 2.8 millions hectares of land consists of acid sulphate and saline soil. Beak et al.1980, Karim et.al 1982). There is virtually only one rice crops is grown. Because of lack of any tested technology suited to local condition, these lands remain fallow. Monitoring of soil water and salinity is basic pre-requisite for making any production plan for coastal saline and  acid sulphate soils. A great deal of information regarding the coastal saline and acid sulphate soils are now lacking. If  proper studies on the utilization of these lands are done according to appropriate technologies suited to local conditions are made available to farmers it is possible to increase the productions for food and fibre crops in Bangladesh.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(484, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'EFFICIENT WASTE MANAGEMENT A CHECKING DISEASES AND POLLUTION.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'There have been a great awareness among the people about soil and environmental pollution. Wastes are valuable resources and contain various essential plant nutrients. Management of wastes are essential. Chemical fertilizer and organic resources ( crop residues) will be applied in the soil to ascertain its potentialities for soil borne disease of jute plant.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(485, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'NEW FERTILIZER FOR JUTE CULTIVATION.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'With advent of W.T.O. in action in our country. Various types of fertilizers would try to enter the country for the beneficial of soil productivity and increasing the food production. The national Technical Committee has approved after proper evaluating the ingradients presents in the fertilizers &amp; forwarded to us to conduct experiments to ascertain the effectiveness of the fertilizers in the production of jute.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(486, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'NUTRIENT SURVEY OF JUTE GROWING AREAS UNDER DIFFERENT AEZ.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Jute, still occupies a major cropping areas of Bangladesh. Moreover, it is one of the component of dominent cropping pattern. Jute produces large quantity of leaves throughout the growing period and 70% of which is being defoliated into soil. It also leaves a large quantity of roots in the soil system. These defoliated leaves &amp; roots add nutrients into the soil through decomposition. Therefore this project has been undertaken to ascertain the nutrient status of jute growing soil.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(487, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'POPULATION DYNAMICS OF JUTE RHIZOSPHERE, ITS IMPACT ON JUTE NUTRITION AND SOIL ENVIRONMENT (Ph.D. PROGRAMME).', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'i. Isolation and identification of microbes associated with N, P and S transformation in jute rhizosphere and non rhizosphere soil.\r\nii. Effect of jute cultivation on the activities of major groups of soil micro flora.\r\niii. Influences of microbial activities on the nutrition of jute.\r\niv. Effect of jute cultivation on soil environment.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(488, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'INTEGRATED SOIL FERETILITY &amp; FERTILIZER MANAGEMENT PROJECT PHASE-II', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(489, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'ENVIRONMENTAL ASSESSMENT OF JUTE AGRICULTURE', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'The project has been conducted in BJRI (Agri) sponsored &amp; financed by IJO since January1998 involving 4 areas of research activities viz. Fertilizers management, Retting &amp; post harvest management, Insect management and Disease management related to environmental studies.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(490, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'SURVEY OF DISEASE', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(491, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'STUDY  ON  THE  SOURCES  OF  ORGANISMS PATHOGENIC TO BAST FIBRE CROPS.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ' Most of the pathogens and a good number of saprophytes of bast fibre crops are seed borne. Under improper storage they cause damping off and affect on viability of seed. In soil the pathogens become active and cause seedling To avoid incidence of disease, examination of seeds as well as soil prior to sowing is necessary for proper recommendation, adoption of effective measure and study of organisms involved.blight. Further, they can over winter through alternate host. As a result, gradual increase of inoculum potential occurs and the soil becomes unsuitable for growing fibre crops. It is also a menace to standing crops. Infected seeds and contaminated soils are, therefore, considered as primary and secondary sources of pathogens.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(492, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'SCREENING FOR RESISTANCE OF JUTE, KENAF AND MESTA GERMPLASM AGAINST FUNGAL AND LEAF MOSAIC DISEASES.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To select germplasm tolerant/resistant to diseases from various exotic and indigenous accessions of Gene Bank and advanced lines for improvement of jute crop.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(493, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'CONTROL OF DISEASE.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Diseases are caused under the influence of various soil, natural agents and other environmental factors yet to be established. Though diseases are not totally curable may be checked below economic injury level. So attempts for their control through application of chemicals, cultural practices, integrated pest management etc. need to be taken for saving the standing crops.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(494, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'EVALUATION OF BOTANICALS FOR JUTE PEST CONTROL.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Jute the main fibre crop of Bangladesh is attacked by about 48 species of insects and mites. Generally chemical insecticides are used to control these pests. But insecticides create several problems in agro-ecosystem such as direct toxicity to beneficial insects, fishes and men, increased environmental and social costs. To minimize the use of insecticides in pest control program, botanicals may be used as an alternative or biodegradable substances. Indigenous botanical agents are broad-spectrum in pest control, easily be used and hazard free in comparison to chemical insecticides. Therefore it  has become necessary to investigate the indigenous plant materials which are more effective for the control of jute pests.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(495, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'HOST RESISTANT/TOLERENT AGAINST JUTE AND ALLIED FIBRE PESTS', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Chemical control of insect pests in general is very hazardous and costly which the farmers can not afford. Moreover pesticides kill not only the pests but also their parasites and predators and create imbalance in nature. Development of resistant variety will help in reducing the cost of production since it does not involve any extra cost for pest control.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(496, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'INSECT ECOLOGY', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Insect ecology means the interaction between the insects and its habitat which includes the study  of   life history, behavior fecundity, alternate host and nature of damage caused by the pests to the crops.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(497, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'BIOLOGICAL CONTROL OF JUTE PESTS.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'The objective of this project is to detect and identify the parasites, predators and pathogen associated with jute insect pests. Detail studies in respect of efficiency, synchronization  of the life history of major endemic parasites, predators of jute weevil (Apion corchori) and yellow mite (Polyphagotersonemus latus) that of the hosts species and the influence of environmental factors on the life stages and longevity of parasites and predators are aimed at.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(498, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'MONITORING OF THE PEST STATUS IN PROMISING VARIETIES OF JUTE ALLIED FIBRE.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Pest infestation varies from variety to  variety and region to region. Pest susceptibility of newly developed varieties needs to be studied for comparison with that of the standard varieties in different regions.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(499, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'PESTICIDE EVALUATION.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'In pest management  programme, the use of pesticide is widely recommended, specially in emergency action when pest populations approach or exceeds the economic threshold level. So, new chemicals need to be evaluated as routine work for recommendation.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(500, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'Development of improved practices for retting jute and allied fibre plants for the acceleration  of  retting speed and  ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To search for newer scientific informations/retting microbes for the development of  methodologies/technologies for the acceleration of retting speed and production of good quality Jute and Allied fibres.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(501, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'UPGRADATION OF LOW QUALITY JUTE AND ALLIED FIBRES.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To up-grade the low quality jute and allied fibres and to improve the fibre quality.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(502, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'DISSEMINATION  OF  MATURE  JUTE  RETTING TECHNOLOGIES  AND  FIBRE  GRADING  SYSTEM.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To disseminate the mature location specific jute retting technologies and fibre grading system to the jute growers and Agri. Extension personnel through training    Programmes/Workshops/Field days/Demonstrations.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(503, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'REGION  SPECIFIC RESEARCH', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(504, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'ON-FARM SOCIO ECONOMIC STUDIES', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'To conduct studies relating to socio-economic and production aspects of jute and jute-based farming systems.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(505, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'CROPPING PATTERN STUDIES IN DIFFERENT AGRO-ECOLOGICAL REGIONS', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'i) to identify and evaluate traditional cropping systems\r\nii)  to develop suitable cropping systems for different land types and socio-economic group  of  farmers.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(506, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'ON- FARM JUTE SEED PRODUCTION', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ' i)   to know the status, problems and prospects of jute seed production at farm level\r\nii) to develop appropriate cropping systems involving jute seed crop for different AEZ of Bangladesh.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(507, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'COLLABORATIVE RESEARCH-EXTENSION PROGRAMME', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'i)To study the adoption performance of improved production technologies at farm level\r\nii) To identify the limiting factors in spread/dissemination of improved technologies at farm level.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(508, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'ARB', 'Project', 'WOMEN''S PARTICIPATION IN JUTE  AND  UTILIZATION.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'i)   To identify and document role of women in jute production\r\nii)  To document gender specific tusks in jute production for different agro- ecological and socio-economic setting.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(509, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'TRB', 'Project', 'Determination of the cause of obnoxious odour produced in wet jute products and its preventive measure', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Jute and particularly jute bag and carpet Produce serious bad smell on wetting. The smell is more obnoxious in case of old and long used. Jute products as compared with fresh jute and jute products it is assumed that some intermolecular change may occur in the core of the fibre due to ageeing coupled with microbial action. If by due experimentation the reason of the bad smell so produced is known appropriate measure can be devised for protection thereof.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(510, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'TRB', 'Project', 'To make fine yarns and fabrics of modified jute.', '', '', '', '', '01-01-2000', '', '', '', 'Jute is a lignocellulosic fibre. It has some inherent defects for using as a textile fibre. Jute is physically coarse, meshy and irregular in length and diameter. Consequently jute fibre is not spinnable for finer textile products because of high content (40%) lignin and other non fibrous materials present along with cellulose (60%). It is known that the properties of jute fibre could be improved through chemical; modification by partial; removal; of lignin and other non-fibrous materials. After chemical; modification the fibres need to be processed like cotton staples in the textile machinery in order to produce yarns of finer count. This processing is to be performed with the modified jute fibres alone or through blending with natural fibres like cotton and synthetic fibres like nylon,polypropylene, polynitriles etc.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', ''),
(511, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'TRB', 'Project', 'Analytical studies of jute and allied vegetable fibres..', '', '', '', '', '01-01-2000', '', '', '', 'Analysis of jute and other lignocellulosic fibres is very much essential for any development research work for their diversified textile uses. BJRI conducts research on different varieties of jute including kenaf, mesta etc. The fibres produced therefore need to be evaluated. In terms of their physical and chemical composition and properties. Scientists working in this domain of research are to depend on some conventional analytical procedures/techniques which are needed to be reviewed and evaluated for advancement of knowledge on fibre analysis. In view of this the present programme has been undertaken.', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', '', '', '', '');
