(878, 'Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Control of white leaf disease of sugarcane', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '15-02-1998', '14-02-2001', '', '', 'a) To find out appropriate control measures of white leaf disease of sugarcane.\r\nb) To find out the effective time temperature combination of moist hot air therapy for controlling white disease.\r\nc) To find out the efficacy of heat therapy in controlling white leaf disease in plant cane and its subsequent generations.\r\nd) To find out the effect of heat therapy on cane yield and sugar/gur recovery.\r\ne) To suggest the cane growers to adopt specific technologies for controlling white leaf disease. \r\niii) To study the associated biotic and abiotic factors\r\niv) To explore the methods (physical, cultural, chemical and botanical) to  minimize of losses  due to diseases .', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 600000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Pathology', 'Sugarcane', '', '', ''),
(879, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Management of post-harvest loss of potato due to diseases and disorders', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-02-1998', '31-01-2001', '', '', 'i) Survey on pre and post storage diseases of potato under ambient and refrigerated  condition including market diseases,\r\nii) to estimate the post-harvest loss of potato due to diseases\r\niii) To study the associated biotic and abiotic factors\r\niv) To explore the methods (physical, cultural, chemical and botanical) to  minimize of losses  due to diseases .', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Pathology', 'Potatoes', '', '', ''),
(874, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', '', 'Disease management and production technology of Banana.', '', '', '', '', '01-03-1998', '29-02-2000', '', '', 'i)  To investigate the distribution and prevalence of sigatoka, panama and bunchy top  diseases of banana along with their reaction on local existing cultivars at different  agro-ecological zones (AEZ) of Bangladesh\r\nii)   To detect virus free mother plant through ELISA for subsequent in-vitro multiplication.\r\niii)   To study the post harvest diseases of banana: i) prevalence and ii) control measure\r\niv)   To evaluate the var./cultivars of banana against panama and bunchy top and diseases under inoculated and natural field conditons.\r\nv)   To find out effective control measures against major diseases of banana.\r\nvi)   To publish a booklet with colour photograph on banana diseases and their control.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 2000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agronomy', 'Bananas', '', '', ''),
(883, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Biological control of soil borne diseases of vegetable crops', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-06-1998', '31-12-2000', '01-06-1998', '', 'a)	To evaluate the ability of rhizosphere and rhizoplane fungal and bacterial isolates in suppressing soil borne diseases of vegetable.\r\n\r\nb)	To investigate the growth promoting ability of vegetable plants by biocontrol agents.\r\n\r\nc)	To analyze the performance of selected nonpathogenic fungal and bacterial isolates in suppressing the disease incidence of vegetables caused by soil borne plant pathogenic fungi under commercial conditions.\r\n\r\nd)	To investigate the enhanced proliferation of the biocontrol agents in the presence of the pathogens by the quantitative relationship between the host plant, the pathogen and the biological control agent.\r\n\r\ne)	To find the environmental conditions for expression of the biological control activity and to reduce the infection caused by soil borne plant pathogenic fungi.\r\n\r\nf)	To advice and disseminate the knowledge to the vegetable growers about soil borne disease of vegetables and their control using biocontrol agents.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 600000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Technology', 'Vegetable', '', '', ''),
(880, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Study on bacterial wilt of solanaceous crops in Bangladesh', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-03-1998', '28-02-2001', '01-06-1998', '', 'i)  To observe the status of bacterial wilt incidence  on different solanaceous vegetable grown in Bangladesh\r\nii)  To find out the predisposing factors for diseases development. \r\niii)  To characterize and classify the isolates of the pathogen.\r\niv)  To formulate the strategy to manage the disease.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Technology', '', '', '', ''),
(881, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Development of papaya varieties resistant to papaya mosaic virus through plant biotechnology', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '15-03-1998', '14-03-2001', '15-03-1998', '', 'i)  To develop PMV resistant papaya varieties through interspecific hybridisation between papaya and C. canflora and F1 doubled haplid system of breeding using biotechnological approach,.\r\nii)  To develop an efficient high frequency and rapid haploid plant regeneration system of papaya through anther culture for production of homozygous diploid lines to study the genetics of recessive traits such as flesh colour, dwarfism etc.\r\niii)  To develop the PMV resistant papaya varieties through A. tumefaciens mediated genetic transformation approach.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Technology', 'Papayas', '', '', ''),
(882, 'Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Integrated Pest Management in Sugarcane', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-1998', '31-12-2000', '', '', '(1) On farm trial of recommended technologies for the control of major sugarcane pests through IPM.\r\n(2) Training/Demonstration/Adoption of IPM for sugarcane extension personnel/farmers.\r\n(3) To study the economics of IPM in sugarcane.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 2000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Integrated Pest Management', 'Sugarcane', '', '', ''),
(886, 'Bangladesh Institute of Nuclear Agriculture', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Varietal Improvement of Groundnut under Existing Cropping Pattern and Environmental Conditions of Bangladesh through Mutation Breeding Technique.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-01-1997', '31-12-1999', '15-11-1997', '', 'a)	Early maturity (100-120 days), as a measure of drought and high temperature tolerance.\r\n\r\nb)	Leaf resistance, root/shoot exploitation, stem reserve, chlorophyll stability and grain growth exploitation as a measure of drought tolerance.\r\n\r\nc)	Stability in yield under normal and moisture deficit environments.\r\n\r\nd)	Higher biological nitrogen fixing efficiency for limited use of synthetic fertilizers.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 725000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Breeding', 'Groundnut', '', '', ''),
(884, 'Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Screening sugarcane germplasm for resistance to red rot wilt and red rot wilt complex.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-07-1998', '31-12-2000', '01-07-1998', '', 'a)	To identify and select sugarcane germplasms having superior resistance against red rot to use as parent materials for hybridization purposes in breeding programme.\r\n\r\nb)	To identify and select sugarcane germplasms having resistance against, wilt disease to use as parent for hybridization purpose in breeding programme.\r\n\r\nc)	To identify and select sugarcane germplasm having combined resistance against red rot and wilt complex.\r\n\r\nd)	To collect, maintain and to evaluate the resistance of exotic and indigenous sugarcane germplasm against red rot, wilt and their combined complex to broaden the scope of hybridization for developing future hereditary resistant varieties to the aforesaid diseases. The sorted out resistant clones can be mutually exchanged among the SAARC countries.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Pathology', 'Sugarcane', '', '', ''),
(885, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Varietal Improvement, Manipulation of Growth Cycle and Development of Production Technology for Better Yield and Higher Allicin Content of Garlic.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-10-1997', '30-09-2000', '', '', 'i)  To develop high yielding short- day cultivars of garlic with higher allicin content &amp; long shelf life.\r\nii)  To develop variability  among the existing cultivars through mutagens.\r\niii)   To improve existing yellow mosaic virus affected  varieties through positive selection .\r\niv)  To develop suitable production systems for bulbing with emphasis to late season planting and higher allicin content\r\nv)  To adjust planting time and to examine the benefit of exposing seed cloves to low temperature for higher yield .', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 420000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Horticulture', 'Garlic', '', '', ''),
(887, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Varietal improvement of barley', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-04-1998', '31-03-2001', '01-04-1998', '', '(1) Collection, evaluation and characterization of barley genotypes specially for early hull-less and salt-tolerance.\r\n(2) Selection of barley germplasm to develop early and hull-less varieties.\r\n(3) Screening of barley germplasms against salinity to develop salt-tolerant varieties.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 700000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Breeding', 'Barely', '', '', ''),
(888, 'Bangladesh Institute of Nuclear Agriculture', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Development of saline resistant mutant varieties of mustard/rapeseed through induced mutation techniques.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-01-1998', '30-09-2001', '01-10-1998', '', '', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 500000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Breeding', ' Mustard', '', '', ''),
(889, 'Bangladesh Institute of Nuclear Agriculture', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Development of high yielding dwarf  sunflower varieties with drooping heads through induced mutation techniques.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '15-02-1998', '14-02-2001', '15-02-1998', '', 'Development of high yielding dwarf varieties with drooping heads. Short (dwarf) stem prevents lodging and directs more assimilates to the head and also permits greater plant population per unit area.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 400000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Mutation Breeding', 'Sunflower', '', '', ''),
(890, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Maintenance breeding and development of suitable castor variety', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-03-1998', '28-02-2001', '01-03-1998', '', 'i)  Collection of local and exotic germplasm for using in the variety development programme.\r\nii)  Selection of varietgh best suitable for summer season as well as for winter season.\r\niii)  Identification and selection of suitable varieties having higher oil content, higher seed yield and disease insect pests tolerant.\r\niv)  Development of appropriate crop management practices.\r\nv)  Promotion of castor production in the probable areas by motivation farmers', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 500000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Breeding', 'Castor', '', '', ''),
(891, 'Bangladesh Institute of Nuclear Agriculture', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Assessment of the advanced mutant lines/varieties of BINA with emphasis on physiological criteria', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-07-1998', '30-06-2001', '01-07-1998', '', 'a)	To evaluate existing advanced mutants of lentil on the basis of physiological parameters such as growth characters (crop growth rate, net assimilation rate, relative growth rate, leaf area index, leaf area ratio etc.) dry matter partitioning and yield.\r\n\r\nb)	To select such mutants of crops to be suitable for adoption by farmers of different agro-ecological zones of Bangladesh.\r\n\r\nc)	To prescribe selection criteria for lentil with respect to be above mentioned objectives.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1200000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Physiology and Biochemistry', '', '', '', ''),
(892, 'Bangladesh Jute Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Varietal improvement of jute through Agrobacterium-mediated transformation', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-04-1997', '31-03-2001', '01-04-1998', '', 'a)	To develop an efficient and repeatable plant regeneration system from the explants of C. olitorius to be used for the introduction of Foreign genes through Agrobacterium vectors.\r\n\r\nb)	To establish a protocol for the introduction of foreign genes with agronomic traits in jute cultivars through Agrobacterium vectors for crop improvement.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1976000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Breeding', 'Jute', '', '', ''),
(893, 'Bangladesh Institute of Nuclear Agriculture', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Varietal improvement of cotton through mutation breeding and advanced breeding techniques.', '', '', 'Basic', 'Completed', '01-06-1998', '31-05-2001', '01-06-1998', '', 'a)	To develop high fibre yielding and early maturing cotton variety (s) with improve fibre quality.\r\n\r\nb)	To develop varieties with resistant/tolerant to jassid and boll worm.\r\n	\r\nc)	To develop varieties with synchronous boll maturity.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 700000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Mutation Breeding', 'Cotton', '', '', ''),
(894, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Breeding Rice for Aroma and Quality .', '', '', 'Applied', '', '01-07-1998', '31-12-2000', '01-07-1998', '', 'i)  To conduct farmers field trial with the fine promising aromatic advanced generation line; BAR 125\r\nii)  To grow segregation generation (F2-F2) to select desirable plants with yield, aroma and quality.\r\niii)  To evaluate germplasm ( collected earlier) for their yield, aroma and quality.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 700000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Plant Breeding', 'Rice', '', '', ''),
(895, 'Bangladesh Rice Research Institute', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Research and development of hybrid rice in Bangladesh.', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-1998', '31-12-2000', '01-01-1998', '', 'a)	Development and Identification of promising parental lines (A, B and R lines) from local and exotic sources (IRRI, China, India) suitable for agro-climatic condition of Bangladesh.\r\n\r\nb)	Evaluation of A and B lines general combining ability and heterotic rice hybrid for specific combining ability and production of experimental hybrids. \r\n\r\nc)	Breeders and Nucleus seed production of promising rice hybrids.\r\n\r\nd)	Optimization of seed production package suited to local condition.\r\n\r\ne)	Standardization of agronomic guidelines of production package of hybrid rice.\r\n\r\nf)	To develop human resources in hybrid rice technology.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 2000000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Breeding', 'Rice', '', '', ''),
(896, 'Bangladesh Institute of Nuclear Agriculture', 'Crops', 'Project', 'Varietal improvement of mungbean [vigna radiata (L.) Wilezek] through mutation breeding and other advanced techniques', '', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-1998', '31-12-2000', '01-01-1998', '', '(1) Developing varieties with resistance/tolerance to MYMV CLS and PM diseases and pod borer pest.\r\n(2) Selecting genotypes with synchrony in pod maturity and determinate type of plant growth with non-branching habit.\r\n(3) Developing short duration (65-75 days) and photo-insensitive varieties for cultivation throughout the year and to avoid weather damage in summer cultivation.\r\n(4) Breeding improved varieties with large seed size.\r\n(5) Breeding summer mungbean varieties with dormancy and resistance to weather damage.', '', '', '', 'ARMP', 1091000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Mutation Breeding', 'Mung Beans', '', '', ''),
(1166, 'Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute', 'Training and Technology Transfer Division', 'Project', 'Create Employment apportunities of char dwellers in Greater Rangpur districts through sugarcane cultivation.', 'Rangpur Sadar, Gaibandha, Kurigram, Nilphamari, Lalmonirhat', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2015', '', '30-06-2015', 'To reduce poverty by increasing famers income in Monga affected areas of Bangladesh which enhances the quality of  life and livelihood of the underprivileged people lining in the riverine char areas. ', 'Technology transfer through training demonstration and other ways.', 'The ultimate target of this project for increasing income of Monga affected char dwellers, particularly the low-income farmers and labour households. Poverty reduction is, thus the target for which necessary additional employment and high value crops will be produced so that landless labour households con earn better ways and small farmers can more cash income through producing and selling high value crops at high price.', 'Rangpur, Monga, Sugarcane, Char-Land, Char Dwellers, Employment opportunity.', '', 821000, 249000, 0, 'Report', 'Training', 0, 'Employment opportunities of Char Dwellers', 'Sugarcane', '', '', ''),
(1173, 'Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute', 'Agricultural Engineering Division', 'Project', 'Popularization of (a) Bud chip cutting machine (b) power tiller mounted trencher in sugar mill zone and non mill zone', 'Pabna sugar mills ltd, Rajshahi Sugar Mills Limited, Thakurgaon Sugar Mills, Sirajgonj , Chapai Nawabgong, Hill tracts districts', 'High', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-*06-2008', '01-06-2010', '', '01-06-2010', 'To create interest among the farmers on the use of these machines.\r\nTo stimulate local manufactures for the manufacture of the machine\r\n', 'One unit of Bud chip cutting machine, power tiller mounted trencher will be supplied in selected sugar mill zone and non mill zones.  These machines will be demonstrated to popularise among the farmers to create demands of the machines.  On the other hand local enterpreuners/ workshop can manufacture the machines and sell among the farmers in less cost involvement.', 'Agricultural Engineering Division of Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute designed and developed many Agricultural Machinery and tools for use in sugarcane field. In order to popularize a) Bud chip cutting machine and b) Power tiller mounted trencher training, demonstration and distribution of machines were executed to increase interest among the sugarcane farmers. Training of 50 farmers in Pabna Sugar Mills Ltd. and 27 Farmers in North Bengal Sugar mills Ltd. on bud chip cutting machine and power tiller mounted trencher has been completed. Two nos. Bud chip cutting machine and two nos power tiller mounted trencher were purchased and one no. of Bud chip cutting machine was distributed to Pabna Sugar Mills Ltd., Pabna for the sugarcane growers of that mill area. One bud chip cutting machine will be supplied to Joypurhat Sugar Mills Ltd for their Sugarcane farmers. Sirajgong Sador upazilla, Tala and Kaligong upazilla of Satkhira district, Sadar and Fulbaria upazilla of Mymensingh District, Agriculture offices were communicated to popularize the Budchip cutting machine and power tiller mounted trencher among the adjoining sugarcane farmers. We have visited Sugar cane farmers field in North Bengal Sugar Mill zone where budchip were used as planting materials. A progressive sugarcane farmer and an owner of a workshop, Mr.Mohammad Ali fabricated BSRI bud chip cutting machine and BSRI power tiller mounted trencher. He will multiply those machines and sell the machine in near future. He is very much convinced about the use and workmanship of the machines.  The farmers who attended the training classes appreciated the technology. They minutely listen and observe the demonstration of the machines.  The Bud chip cutting machine and power tiller mounted trencher required to be demonstrated in different location of Bangladesh. This will help to disseminate the technology among the farmers and create awareness among the farmers to use these machines. It will also help to stimulate local manufactures for the manufacturing these kinds of machines. Further study/work should be continued to popularize these two machines.', 'Sugarcane, Bud chip cutting machine, power tiller mounted trencher, Popularization.', 'BARC', 300000, 300000, 0, 'Report', 'Training', 0, 'Mechanization', 'Sugarcane', '', '', ''),
(1140, 'Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute', 'RARS, Rahmatpur, Barisal', 'Project', 'Development of rapid screening technique and control of Botrytis Gray Mold and Pod Borer of Chickpea.', 'PRC, Ishurdi, Pabna', 'High', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-072008', '30-06-2009', '', '30-06-2009', 'Development high yielding variety and suitable management practices of Chickpea against BGM and pod borer of Chickpea.', 'A total of five (5) experiments under the project &quot;Development of rapid screening technique and control of Botrytis Gray Mold (BGM) and Pod Borer of Chickpea&quot;were conducted at Pulses research sub-station (PRSS), Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute (BARI), Madaripur. The project aims was to develop high yielding Chickpea variety and management practices against BGM and pod borer. Fourteen fungicides were used in the experiment to find out the effective fungicides for BGM. Six different insecticides were used in the experiment to identify effective for pod borer and Chickpea lines were under trial for screening Chickpea genotype resistant to BGM and pod borer. Five experiments were entitled:\r\nExperiment 1. Efficacy of fungicides in controlling Botrytis Gray Mold of Chickpea (In-vitro).\r\nExperiment 2. Screening of chickpea lines against BGM through cut twig method (in-vitro).\r\nExperiment 3. Efficacy of fungicides in controlling BGM of Chickpea (in-vivo).\r\nExperiment 4. Screening of Chickpea genotypes for resistance to BGM.\r\nExperiment 5. Screening of insecticides in controlling pod borer of chickpea.\r\n', 'Chickpea is an important source of protein for human diet in Bangladesh. The crop faced a lot of production constraints regularly in the country. At least seventeen diseases were found to attack the crop, of which Botrytis Gray Mold (BGM), caused by Botrytis cinerea Pers. ex. Fr., the fungus was most important. To combat the disease by using fungicide the present investigation was under taken. From the results of bio-assay of the fungicides Companion 63 WP, Protaf, Secure 600 were selected for screening. A total of 26 desi and 34 kabuli lines were evaluated under this trial. The four entries showed the highly resistant reaction and two entries showed resistant reaction. By screening with cut twig method, 4 entries, had a score of &quot;4&quot;and eight entries had &quot;5&quot;score and were graded as resistant. Five lines showed &quot;6&quot;scoring and seven lines were graded as &quot;7&quot;while 1 entry scored &quot;8&quot;and were graded as highly susceptible. Results revealed that among the six fungicides Companion treated plot showed lowest diseases score and produced highest yield (1604 kg/ha). The highest score of BGM was observed in protaf treated plot (934 kg/ha). Six insecticides were evaluated. Among the treatments Karata (2ml/l) effectively control Chickpea pod borer and produced highest yield (1535 kg/ha).\r\n\r\n', 'Cinerea, Chickpea pod borer', '', 500000, 500000, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Pulse Crop', 'Pod borer of Chickpea', '', '', ''),
(1280, 'Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Agricultural University', 'Agricultural Economics Division', 'Project', 'Up-Scalling/Up-Dating the Adoption of Modern Rice Technologies at the Farm Level.', 'Sunamganj, Chandpur, Sirajganj, Rajshahi, Chapai, Barishal, Jhalokathi, Bogra, Satkhira  and Khulna', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2007', '30-06-2008', '01-01-2007', '30-06-2008', 'a. To estimate the region/environment-wise adoption rate of different rices in Boro and T. Aman seasons;\r\nb. To estimate productivity and profitability of different rice in T. Aman and Boro season\r\nc. To assess the level of varietal drop out and understand the reasons of dropping out the varieties under different production environments; and\r\nd. To feedback the information to the main stream of technology transfer processes for accelerating adoption at the farm level.', '', '', 'Up-scalling/Up-dating the adoption of modern rice, Modern Rice Technologies, Rice', 'BARC', 150000, 150000, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'More Production Technology', 'Rice', '', '', ''),
