om jute seed as a sole crop 543 kg/ha and 532 kg/ha in Kalapara and Amtoli respectively. The benefit cost ration (BCR) on full cost basis ranges from 1.06 to 1.65. Other experiments are in the field. As a result, the data collection of the experiments not yet has been completed. There were four farmers training programme conducted at Kalapara, Amtoli and Dumki with participation of 200 farmers and three field days were conducted at Kalapara and Dumki with participation of 133 farmers and SAAO at jute fibre maturity stage in the year 2011-12.', 'Cropping Patterns, Maximum yield of Jute seed, Bench mark survey, Jute fibre maturity stage.', 'BARC', 1000000, 650000, 0, 'Report', 'Training', 200, 'Seed Production', 'Jute', '', '', ''),
(1236, 'Bangladesh Rice Research Institute', 'Agronomy Division, Gazipur', 'Project', 'Crop productivity enhancement under climate change sitution in the char land Eco-system', 'Kustia char land and Ishurdi char land', 'High', 'Adaptive', 'On-going', '23-05-2012', '30-06-2013', '', '30-06-2013', '1. To introduce adaptable new crops in the project areas for exploiting the potentiality of the productive char lands under climate change situation.\r\n2. To replace local crop varieties by modern varieties to increase crop productivity ensure food security, social protection and reduce malnutrition of poor and vulnerable farmers of char lands under climate change situation.\r\n3. To maintain soil health through environmental friendly crop production practices.\r\n', '1. Baseline survey through random sampling in the project area.\r\n2. Selection of Farmers for experimentation.\r\n3. Purchase of seeds of modern crop varieties from REsearch Institute and BADC\r\n4. Training on dodern cultivation techniques and inputs supply to the farmers\r\n5. Experimentation / demonstration and data collection\r\n6. Data analysis, Reporting and Publication\r\n', 'On-farm trails will be conducted for validation and adoption of improved crop varieties and production practices by the farmers of char areas at Daulatpur and Bheramara upazila in Kushtia districts. The project activities will be carried out in the co-operator farmers'' fields with farmers'' participatory approach. The performance of different technologies will be monitored regularly and necessary dat awill be collected properly using standard methods.', 'Climate Change, Environmental Science', 'BARC', 300000, 50000, 0, '', '', 0, 'Environmental Science', 'Climate Change', '', '', ''),
(1237, 'Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Agricultural University', 'Pest Management Division', 'Project', 'Development of Threshold level (Seed Health Standard) of Colletotrichum corchori in jute seed.', 'Manikganj, Rangpur, Faridpur and Comilla', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '28-06-2010', '27-06-2013', '27-06-2013', '27-06-2013', '1) To recommend procedure for routine seed health test for detection of Colletotrichum corchri in jute seeds.\r\n2) To determine the level of fungal infestation in capsularis jute seeds in Bangladesh.\r\n3) To determine the level of transmission of C. corchori from seed to plant to seed in jute.\r\n4) To develop the threshold level (Seed health standard) of the seed borne fungal pathogen C. corchori in jute.\r\n5) To increase the quality and yield of fibre and seed through reducing fungal (C. corchori) infestation in jute (Corchorus capsularis).', '', '', 'Seed Health Standard, Fungal Pathogen, Seed-borne association', '', 6015240, 2900000, 0, 'Report', 'Training', 200, 'Seed Health Management', 'Jute', '', '', ''),
(1278, 'Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Agricultural University', 'Horticulture Research Centre, Gazipur', 'Project', 'Integrated crop management for the improvement of Jackfruit.', 'Ramgarh, Bijoynagar, Shibpur, Modhupur and Sripur and Kapasia. ', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '24-02-2010', '23-02-2013', '', '23-02-2013', '1. Identification and documentation of major insect pests and disease, nutritional and water deficiencies causing severe damage of jack fruit trees.\r\n2. Document the extent of damage severity in several jackfruit growing areas of Bangladesh.\r\n3. Development of integrated management packages for jackfruit production.\r\n4. Growing awareness among the farmers about the benefit of ICM technologies in producing jackfruit.\r\n5. Training of farmers, extension peoples, NGO personnel&amp;rsquo;s for successful production of jackfruit and improving socio-economic condition.\r\n', '', '', 'Jackfruit, Gummosis, Management', 'World Bank', 4217650, 3900000, 0, '', '', 450, 'Disease and pest management', 'Jackfruit', '', '', ''),
