(1391, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Dept. farm power &amp; Machinery', 'Project', 'Development of small scale electric powered oil expellers suitable for adaptation among the rural farmers in Bangladesh.', 'BAU (Mymensingh) &amp; BCSKS (Bittohin Chasi Samaj Kallyan Sangstha, Ishurdi, Pabna), Modhupur, Muktagacha.', 'High', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-05-2009', '30-05-2010', '01-05-2009', '30-05-2010', 'a.Design and development of electric powered oil seed crusher and its performance studies.\r\nb.Development of heat treatment system for the rotating parts.\r\nc.Study the factors affecting oil yield and oil extracting pattern.\r\nd.Determination of different physical parameters of seeds containing soil.\r\ne. Adaptation of expellers to the end users through survey, discussion, presentation of posters and leaflets.\r\nf. Development of training manual and field level workshop.\r\ng. An NGO will be involved for field level dissemination of the expeller.', 'A. Design: A mechanical drawing will be prepared under trail and error method and a best drawing will be selected for fabrication. An assembly drawing will be prepared for helping the manufacturing of the electric powered expeller.\r\nB. Materiel Used: Materials required for the construction of the electric powered expellers will be estimated and will be purchased from the local market such as screw press, angel bar, M/S rod, hopper, nut and bolt, balance, flat-belt, wheel, spur gear, container, electric motor,diesel engine, etc.\r\nC. Oil seeds will be collected from the farmers and the performance study will be carried out and the yield will be recorded for different parameters.\r\nd. Field survey will be conducted at farmers field level at char areas where oil seeds are grown and available.\r\nE. The different designs and drawing of the oil expellers will be explained to the farmers about their functions and benefit to the end users.\r\nF. A five day t raining program will be arranged to train five manufactures and 50 farmers. A training manual, leaflet, poster will be prepared to used in the workshop during training period.', '', 'Small scale electric power, Oil seed, oil seed crusher', 'Krishi Gobeshona Foundation (KGF)', 1976000, 0, 0, 'Report', 'Training, Workshop', 50, 'Electric Power for Rural Farmers', 'Oil seeds', 'More efficient 9less extraction time, less extraction cost and more oil recovery) oil expeller has been developed for rural areas.', '1.	Local entrepreneurs will be encouraged to provide oil extraction services with less cost.\r\n2.	More oil will be extracted from same of amount of oil seed. \r\n', ''),
