(1430, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Animal Breeding and Genetics', 'Project', 'Conservation of Black Bengal Goat as the potential genetic resource in Bangladesh.', 'Department of Animal Breeding and Genetics, BAU, Mymensingh-2202', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '2006', '', '2006', '', '1) Production and use of goat frozen semen and evaluate its proposed prospect in Bangladesh.\r\n2) Popularize artificial insemination (AI) activity using selected bucks to rural community in Bangladesh.\r\n3) Syncronization of estrus for maximizing the fertility.\r\n4) Sustainable genetic improvements of Black Bengal Goats for appropriate conservation of this genetic resource and estimation of genetic parameters for its appropriate documentation.\r\n5) Strengthen the income generation activities of the rural people.', '', 'A project was initiated in 2006 in the department of Animal Breeding and Genetics, Bangladesh Agricultural University, Mymensingh entitled Conservation of Black Bengal Goat as the potential genetic resource in Bangladesh with the aim of appropriate conservation and genetic improvement of the Black Bengal goats as well as improvement of socio-economic condition of the rural goateries of Bangladesh. The project activities were performed in four sub-headings: i) establishment of the selected nucleus breeding flocks, ii) collection and production of frozen semen and adaptation of artificial insemination (Al) for goat in Bangladesh condition, iii) synchronization of estrus, and iv) sustainable genetic improvements of Black Bengal goats for appropriate conservation of this genetic resource and estimation of genetic parameters for its appropriate documentation. Under this project one pH D and 21 MS students have already obtained their degree and at present 3 Ph D and 7 MS students is doing research.\r\n\r\nWith the subsequent advancement of our project activities we obtained basic morphometric and performance information about Black Bengal Buck and doe for appropriate documentation, relationship of body weight with heart girth, body length and height at wither as well as relationship among age, body weight, scrotal circumference and semen volume in buck. Heritability estimates for growth traits, reproductive traits, milk yield, and semen production were found high, low, low and moderate respectively. On estrus behavior and synchronization, physiological peculiarities effect of seasons and effect of prostaglandin and progesterone were observed. We had established standard collection method of cumulous oocyte-complexes (COCs) form slaughterhouse ovaries and also observed that there had relationship between ovarian condition and the quality of collected COCs. We obtained the effect of supplemented Bovine serum albumin (BSA and goat follicular fluid (gFF) on in vitro maturation (IVM) and in vitro fertilization (IVF) of goat oocytes. Ti was possible to establish the suitable culture condition for in vitro production (IVP) of goat embryos. We evaluated Black Bengal buck semen, established a suitable protocol for the production of frozen semen as well as measured the fertility level of bucks in terms of semen quality and conception rate in does and also compared the conception rate following AI with fresh-diluted and frozen thawed semen. Already compound pellet feed for goat has developed for the first time in Bangladesh. Compound pellet feeding found superior and this information might be the milestone for practical goat farming. We observed different types of disease were   provoked but incidence of diseases was reduced gradually by advancement of the year in improved flock. On the other hand, production and reproduction performances of the flock were improved on successive years.\r\n\r\nFinally it may suggest that, there exists sizable variation among the potentiality of breeding bucks. Besides the scarcity of breeding bucks may be minimized by population of AI using frozen semen of good quality selected bucks and increased the total production profile of Black Bengal goat.\r\n', 'Goat, Balck Bengal, ', 'USDA', 0, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Goats production', 'Animal', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, Volume-22, 2011.  Proceedings of the workshop of BAU Research Progress, 02-03 April 2012.'),
(1431, 'Sylhet Agricultural University', 'Department of Agribusiness and Marketing', 'Project', 'Feasibility study on agribusiness development through contract farming in Bangladesh', '', 'High', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'Completed', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2012', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2012', '1.To study the performance of dairy and crop contract farming practices in providing opportunities to the farmers of technology transfer, increasing in incomes and improved marketing facility in Bangladesh.\r\n2.To examine the distribution mechanisms of increased income generated through value adding activities.\r\n3.To study the accessibility of contract farming arrangement by the different sections of the farming community, irrespective of size of land holding. \r\n4.To make recommendation for leveraging contract farming for improving supply chain efficiency. ', '', '', 'Dairy farm, Crop, Agricibusiness', 'BAU-UGC', 120000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Dairy Farming and Crop', 'Agriculture', '', '', ''),
(1432, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Crop Botany', 'Project', 'Genetic Improvement of Teasle Gourd through Biotechnological Approaches.', 'Department of Crop Botany, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2012', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2012', '', '', '     Teasle gourd (Momordica dioeca Roxb.) is dioecious in nature and belongs to the family cucurbitaceae. Among the summer vegetables, it is rich in protein, carotene, carbohydrate, vitamins (Vit. C) and minerals. Its propagation entirely depends on underground tuberous roots. Maintenance of quality of tuberous roots in the field as well as storage condition is troublesome.  Fruit quality of teasle gourd deteriorates due to the presence of large number of hard seeds. Micro-propagation and use of mutagenes may help to overcome these problems to a great extent by producing new variants. To establish and develop a complete protocol for regeneration and rapid multiplication of plants from different explant (shoot tip, leaf segment, nodal segment and internode) have been cultured on MS medium supplemented with NAA (0.0, 0.1 &amp; 0.2 mgL-1) and BAP (0.0, 0.5, 1.0, 1.5 and 2.0 mgL-1) for callus initiation. The culture medium supplemented with 0.5 mgL-1 NAA and 1.0 mgL-1 BAP resulted best callus induction from internode explant. Use of physical mutagene (i.e. Gamma radiation) in different doses on different explants was attempted which might create heterogeneity. We are expecting seedless or reduced seeded teasle gourd from this attempt. Treatments of gamma rays on callus at 0, 20, 40, 60 &amp; 80 gay were applied. The calli responded differently with the different treatments of gamma radiation. Result revealed that gamma radiation at 60 gay has been influencing in gaining the size of calli slowly. This research work has been under study and continuing. ', 'Genetic improvement, Teasle gourd, Biotechnological approaches', 'BAURES', 0, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Genetic improvement of vegetable crop', 'Teasle gourd', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, 07-08 March, 2010. Bangladesh Agricultural Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress. Volume 20. Proceedings of the Workshop of University Research System (BAURES), BAU, Mymensingh.'),
