(1487, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agricultural Extension Education', 'Project', 'Need Assessment of Women for capacity building in post harvest facilities of vegetables towards poverty alleviation.', 'Savar Upazila of Dhaka District', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-11-2009', '31-12-2009', '01-11-2009', '31-12-2009', 'to assess the extent rural womens need for capacity building in conducting post harvest activities of vegetables towards poverty alleviation', '', 'The major objective of the study is to assess the extent rural womens need for capacity building in conducting post harvest activities of vegetables towards poverty alleviation. Data were collected from 100 women who were engaged in vegetable production of a village of Savar Upazila during November to December 2009. For collecting data from the women, interview method was followed using a pre-tested interview schedule. Other than interview, some group approaches of data collection methods were applied. Correlation coefficient (r) values were calculated to explore relationships among dependent variable and independent variables. More than two thirds (68%) of the respondents felt high need and the rest (32%) felt medium need for capacity building in utilizing post harvest facilities of vegetables. Regarding the areas of need for capacity building, most of the women felt high need for physical facilities and the next felt area was the management skill. Their farm size, annual income and training exposure showed significant negative correlation with their need for capacity building. On the other hand, rest of the characteristics did not show any significant relationship. The main problems confronted by the women in utilizing the post harvest facilities of vegetables were insufficient knowledge and skill on post harvest activities, lack of physical facilities, absence of community sales center, lack of capital to buy the instruments/equipments and lack of marketing facilities for value added products. It is recommended that farm women engaged in vegetable production need to be trained on multifarious issues of post harvest activities of vegetables and should get credit facilities to establish community centers for production and sale of processed products of vegetables which may support in alleviating their poverty to a greater extent.   ', 'Need assessment, Capacity building, poverty alleviation', 'BAURES', 73450, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Women capacity building', 'Post harvest handling of vegetables', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, 07-08 March, 2010. Bangladesh Agricultural Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress. Volume 20. Proceedings of the Workshop of University Research System (BAURES), BAU, Mymensingh.'),
