(1494, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Plant Pathology', 'Project', 'Environmental friendly control of Foot and Root rot of lentil and chieckpea in the field', 'Field Laboratory, Department of Plant Pathology, Bangladesh Agricultural University (BAU), Mymensingh', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2009', '', '', 'to determine the effect of BAU-Biofungicide for controlling foot and root rot disease of lentil (Lens culinaris) and chickpea (Cicer arietinum)', '', 'The experiment was carried out in the Field Laboratory, Department of Plant Pathology, Bangladesh Agricultural University (BAU), Mymensingh, Bangladesh to determine the effect of BAU-Biofungicide for controlling foot and root rot disease of lentil (Lens culinaris) and chickpea (Cicer arietinum). BAU-biofungicide significantly reduced the foot and root rot disease incidence of seedlings of the test pulses by upto 68% over the control. Seed treatment with BAU-biofungicide was found best for controlling seedling diseases of lentil and chickpea. Moreover, it increased significantly fresh weight of plant, number of nodules/plant  as well as weight of nodules/plant of lentil. BAU-biofungicide significantly increased ', 'Pulses, Chickpea, Lentil, BAU-Biofungicide', 'UGC-BAU', 78000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Disease control of pulse crop', 'Lentil and Chickpea', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, 07-08 March, 2010. Bangladesh Agricultural Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress. Volume 20. Proceedings of the Workshop of University Research System (BAURES), BAU, Mymensingh.'),
