(1532, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department. of Agronomy', 'Project', 'Development of dry bed direct seeded Boro rice production system towards saving irrigation system water and attaining food security. ', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-10-2010', '30-09-2011', '01-10-2010', '30-09-2011', '', '', 'Boro rice cultivation by puddled transplanting with conventional or alternate wetting and drying (AWD) irrigation system requires huge irrigation water while dry bed direct seeding (DBDS) following AWD irrigation could save 60% irrigation water. The present study was initiated with the aim of developing technologies for DBDS boro rice production system. Three experiments were conducted during October 2010 to September 2011 such as (1). Effect of  hydro priming duration on seedling emergence performance of boro rice cv. BRRIdhan29, (2) Effect of osmo priming on the seedling emergence performance of boro rice cv. BRRI dhan29, and (3) Effect of integrated weed management on the performance of boro rice under dry bed direct seeded system. In experiment 1, seed was soaked in water for 0, 6, 12, 18, 24, 30, 36, 42, 48, 54, 60 and 66 hours while in experiment 2, seed was soaked in 1%, 3% And 5% solution of CaCI2, ZnSO4 and KCI and also in distilled water for 24, 30, 2642 and 48 h respectively. Following soaking each seed lot was incubated for 30 h under room temperature both for hydro and osmo priming. Among the hydro priming treatments seed soaking in water for 30-60 hours gave best seed emergence performance in term of percentage germination, vigour index, mean germination time and seedling growth attributes. Osmo priming performed better than hydro-priming and the soaking of seeds in 3% ZnSO4 for 30 h showed the best performance. Experiment 3 included three sowing depth viz. 2, 5 and 8 cm and 7 weed management treatments such as (I) No weeding, (II) hand weeding, (III) Blade + hand weeding, (IV) Blade + rake + hand weeding, (V) Serius (Pyrazosulfuron-ethyle) + hand weeding, (VI) Top (pretilachlor) + hand weeding, and (VII) Panida (pendimethalin) + hand weeding in a field trial using RCBD with three replications. The result showed that application of Panida ata2 and 22 days after sowing (DAS) followed by one hand weeding at 35 DAS gave the best weed control and highest yield performance. The present study indicates that priming of seed with 3% ZnSO4 and weed management using herbicide (e.g. Panida) could help improving seedling establishment and attain high yield of boro rice cv. BRRI dhan29 under dry bed direct seeded system. ', 'Rice, Seed bed, ', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Seed Production', 'Rice', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, Volume-22, 2011.  Proceedings of the workshop of BAU Research Progress, 02-03 April 2012.'),
