(1581, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Soil Science', 'Project', 'Organic amendments for mitigating soil salinigy in rice-maize cropping system', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2014', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2014', '1.	To investigate the protective effect of maize against salt stress.\r\n2.	To exam the effect of proline on K/Na ratio, cholera Phil content and proline accumulation by rice and maize under slat stress.\r\n3.	To examine the effect of proline on ascorbate and glutathione contents and the activity of ROS scavenging antioxidant enzymes under salt stress. \r\n4.	To investigate the effect of organic manures on the growth and yield of rice and maize under salt-stress.\r\n5.	To suggest on approach for the improvement of crop production under salinity.\r\n', '', '', 'Soil, Salinity, Rice-maize', 'BARC', 1200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Salinity', 'Soils', '', '', ''),
