(1583, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Biotechnology', 'Project', 'Selection for Anthracnose Resistance in chilli Germplasm and development of Resistant lines ', 'Plant Genetic Resource Centre (RGRC), BAU and different area of Bangladesh. ', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-01-2012', '31-12-2014', '01-01-2012', '31-12-2014', '1.	To develop efficient molecular diagnostics and screening methodologies for  pathogens \r\n2.	To screen chili germplasm for anthracnose resistance markers. \r\n3.	To develop disease resistant varieties of chili.\r\n', '', 'Thirty germplasms have been collected from different area of Bangladesh and Plant Genetic Resource Centre (RGRC). Several diseased samples have been identified and studied for isolation of the pathogen. It was found that the disease was caused by Collectotrichum capsici. Pure culture of isolated pathogen was done. Among the 25 primers initially tested, six primers (S1184, OPAB10, S1320, OPA02 and OPB02) Yielded comparatively higher number of amplification product with high intensity and minimal smearing, good resolution and also clear bands. Selected six primers generated 51 bands. Out of 51 bands, 44 bands were polymorphic (86.27%) and 15 bands were monomorphic (13.73%). The six selected primers generated various banding patterns, ranging from 6 (S1320) to 10) OPAB20 &amp; OPAB02). Primer S1184, OPA02 &amp; OPB02 produced highest percentage of polymorphic loci (100%). Thus it showed higher level of polymorphism. On the other hand S1320 primer produced lowest number of polymorphic band non-symmetrical to others resulting in lower polymorphism. Mean diversity across all population for all the loci studied was 0.2639. High level of gene diversity was found for primer S1184-8 (0.6931) whereas the gene diversity values for primer OPAB10-3, OPaB10-4, S1320-5 &amp; S1320-6 were zero. Dendrogram based no Neis (1972) genetic distance using Unweighted Pair Group Method of Arithmetic Means (UPGMA) indicated segregation of the 30 chilli germplasms into 2 main clusters, ombai morich grouped solitary into Cluster I and other 29 germplasms are grouped into Cluster II. Further study is underway to select anthracnose resistant chilli germplasm.  ', 'Chilli, Spices, ', 'BAS-USDA', 5336754, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Chilli germplasms &amp; resistant lines', 'Spices', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, Volume-22, 2011.  Proceedings of the workshop of BAU Research Progress, 02-03 April 2012.'),
