(1663, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Pharmacology', 'Project', 'Determination of environmental contamination of lead &amp; its toxic effects on poultry production &amp; health.', 'Department of Pharmacology, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2008', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2008', '1) Detection of lead level in environment and commercial poultry in certain selected areas of Bangladesh.\r\n2) Study the effects of garlic in minimizing the lead levels in different organs, muscles, blood, bone and eggs in lead induced poultry.\r\n3) Study the hematological, biochemical and immunologic effects of garlic in lead induced poultry.\r\n4) Determination of magnitude of lead toxicity on biosynthesis of DNA in poultry.   ', '', 'In Bangladesh, the toxic signs have been recognized to arsenic only, but there are wide ranges of other chemicals that are even more potent for producing toxic signs. Among the toxic heavy metals, mercury, lead and cadmium called big three toxic metals due to their major impact on the environment (Volesky, 1994). Lead compounds play no known beneficial role in biological processes affecting the ecosystem productivity and nutrient cycling (Gulson, 1996). The aim of this project was determination of the therapeutic effects of garlic (allium sativum) to minimize or to reduce the accumulation of lead (Pb) in different organs in lead (Pb) toxicity induced broiler chickens, investigation of hemato-biochemical effects following the therapeutic application of garlic (allium sativum) in lead (Pb) toxicity induced broiler chickens. Estimation of carcass yield, body weight, body weight gain, feed consumption and feed conversion ratio in lead (Pb) toxicity induced broiler chickens following (allium sativum) therapeutic application of garlic. The hemoglobin concentration was measured by cyanmethemoglobin method. The result was expressed in g%. Packed cell volume (PCV) was determined by the micro hematocrit method using capillary tubes and the percentage of packed erythrocytes was determined. After thawing of the serum samples, the biochemical parameters was determined by Reflotron &reg; Plus biochemical Auto-analyzer using the previously collected serum samples. Garlic effects on body condition. The statistical analysis of variance will be analyzed by Duncans Multiple Range Test (DMRT) using the General Linear Models (GLM) procedure of SAS (SAS Institute, 1985). Results will be displayed as means standard error. All statements of significance will be based on the 0.05 level of probability.  ', 'Environmental Contamination, lead, Toxic effects, poultry production', 'BARC', 250000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Environmental contamination of lead', 'Poultry', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, 07-08 March, 2010. Bangladesh Agricultural Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress. Volume 20. Proceedings of the Workshop of University Research System (BAURES), BAU, Mymensingh.'),
