(1668, 'Bangladesh Sericulture Research and Training Institute', '', '', 'On station Trial of Mulberry, their propagation, Conservation &amp; Improvement through Biotechnology.', 'Rajshahi', '', '', '', '', '', '01-10-1998', '30-09-2000', 'A. Identification of few (5-7) elite mulberry genotypes from the heterogeneous population in Bangladesh;\r\nB. Identified and selected mulberry genotypes must have the intrinsic qualities like, quicker and robust growth habitat, high nutritional quality of leaves for healthy silk warm rearing, disease resistance as well as drought resistance that can survive in prolonged summer;\r\nC. Cloning of these elite genotypes to develop clone garden for breeding and large scale propagation program;\r\nD. Large scale propagation of clones through vitro techniques will be considered;         \r\nE. Collection of germplasm from neighbouring countries, their maintenance and conservation through in vitro techniques;   \r\nF. Micro-propagation and clonal multiplication of difficult to root elite genotypes.', '', '', '', 'USAID', 750000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Crops', 'Mulberry propagation.', '', '', '');
