(1737, 'Proshika Manobik Unnayan Kendra', '', '', 'Extension of Beef Cattle Fattening Project.', 'Singair, Manikganj', '', '', '', '', '', '01-07-1999', '30-06-2001', 'A. Capacity building of the rural farmers for adoption & execute improved technology of livestock;        B. To find out age group of cattle, season of the year in which highest daily average body weights gain under improved management & greater market value & demand;                   C. To find out the impact & low cost improved feed supplement after deworming whether it could enhance substantial body growth of the animal & increase income manifold compared to the traditional system of rearing;    D. Increase the use of organic manure for soil fertility & enhance  the ecological agricultural system;', '', '', '', 'USAID', 500000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Livestock', 'Beef fattening.', '', '', ''),
(1738, 'Proshika Manobik Unnayan Kendra', '', '', 'Production of green grass and its preservation technique for future use.', 'Mirzapur, Tangail', '', '', '', '', '', '01-08-1999', '30-06-2001', 'A. The farmer will be able to know the production technique of high yielding variety of  green grasses and its preservation processes;                    B. The shortage of green grasses during dry season would be mitigated through the excessive production in the rainy season;                                   C. Green grass provides adequate amount of microbial protein in the rumen and increases microbial function, which prevents the loss of body weight in cattle;                       D. The cattle will be prevented from various deficiency diseases like blindness, night blindness, and in fertility;', '', '', '', 'USAID', 200000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Livestock', 'Grass preservation.', '', '', ''),
(1739, 'Proshika Manobik Unnayan Kendra', '', '', 'Use of algae in cattle feed: an alternative feed supplement instead of green grass.', 'Saturia, Manikganj', '', '', '', '', '', '01-07-1999', '30-06-2001', 'A. Straw is abundantly used in rural level. So cattle can?t gain metabolizable energy and protein according to their need. Algal water helps to increase that metabolizable energy and protein in the cattle;         B. Algal water provides adequate amount of microbial protein in the rumen and increases microbial functions, which prevents the body weight loss of cattle;                        C. The cattle suffer in various deficiency diseases like blindness, night blindness, and infertility due to scarcity of green grasses. Algae contain much vitamin and minerals, which prevents those diseases;         D. Algae absorbs carbon-di-oxide from the air and exhaust oxygen, 1 gm algae can produce approximately 1.6 gm oxygen. It serves as a supplement to keeping environment ecological balance;                                          E. Algae, as a feed has no side effect;', '', '', '', 'USAID', 250000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Livestock', 'Algae production.', '', '', ''),
