(1831, 'Winrock International', '', '', 'Rearing of crossbreed Hens in Rural Bangladesh.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '01-07-2000', '30-06-2001', 'In the economy of rural poultry plays a very important role. Poultry keeping is one of the most appropriate income generating activities for the rural women, youth, landless and marginal farmers. It provides cash income, generate employment opportunities and at the same time increase production of very valuable protein food-meat and eggs. Out of total animal protein food consumed in the country 28% comes from the poultry meat and eggs alone; The village women with short-term poultry training under this project on modern management including the prevention of diseases by learning vaccination techniques against prevalent rural poultry diseases can earn a respectable income to improve their living by raising poultry by scavenging, semi-scavenging or expended poultry operation with larger number of broiler and layers. These trained women will act as local trainers to other village women poultry raises in their and act as model poultry growers for others in the neighbourhood; In keeping livestock including poultry in the rural farming household, the role played by women, from the initial investment to the consumption and marketing of livestock is an essential part of the family involvement in agricultural production process and in the earning of family livelihood; For women who stay home livestock raring is often their only way of earning some income. Women irrespective of class differences feel the need of having a separate income of their own and livestock including poultry is one of the major sources of some income; a)To help the family in time of need;b)To save money for future investments in land etc.c)To buy things for herself and her children like daily necessities, good food and books etc. d)To eat more eggs and meat to supplement protein intake for the family to avoid malnutrition of women folks and children particularly, the most vulnerable groups.e)To enhance their status in the family.f)To empower them in the decision making process. Commercial private poultry farmers have already initiated a program called Contract Growing System. Under this contract system, the entrepreneurs supply high producing quality baby chicks, feed, vaccines, medicines and supervision to the flocks the village growers provide housing and labor only. At appropriate age, the contracting farms buy back the grown-up broilers/pullets from the growers at market rate. This program gives a handsome income for the growers. Trained women under this project can very well take part in the contract growing system to increase their income and thereby better livelihood;', '', '', '', 'USAID', 300000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Livestock', 'Hen rearing.', '', '', ''),
