(1833, 'Winrock International', '', '', 'Integrated Fish-chicken farming.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '01-07-2000', '30-06-2001', 'To select and lease 4 ponds having total 280 decimals in size from the project area of Bangappara under Austagram Thana of Kishoreganj district;To selected 80 organized disadvantaged women interested in fish-chicken farming unitedly under technology transfer project;To impart 5 days training to  organize women under the technology transfer program on fish-chicken farming for improving their knowledge and skills in the allied field and changes of attitude, beliefs and perception; To impart 5 days orientation training to 3 technology transfer program staff for efficient program implementation by enhancing their knowledge and skills in the light of technology transfer and enable to generate social mobilisation in favour of integrated fish-chicken farming in the area;To conduct baseline survey of 80 beneficiaries to identify their problems and needs on technology transfer of integrated fish-chicken farming; To use phostoxin tables in technology transfer ponds 4 tables per decimal for destroying Rakhush fish; To provide 6101 fingerlings of 8-10 cm size/ha Ruhi 25%, Siver carp - 30%, Catla 10%, Mrigal 20%, Common carp 5%. In addition Rajpunthi 2000 per hectare for fish rearing in accordance with the technology transfer of Bangladesh Fisheries Research Institute;To rear total 565 layer chicken (500 chicken per hectare) in 4 technology transfer ponds through 16 chicken sheds (4 sheds in each pond) as per procedure of technology transfer project; To provide prepared chicken feed as per technology transfer to 565 chickens for 36 weeks during project period as per recommendation of technology transfer project; To impart intensive motivation to fish-chicken farming organized women to ensure their participation in technology transfer for getting higher animal protein for family consumption as well as supplementary income out of sale of suplus production in the form of fish, meat,  egg and others;To take appropriate care about health and hygiene of chicken for prevention and curative measures of diseases;To rear fish without fish feed by adopting other modern technology as proposed by Bangladesh Fisheries Research Institute for bumper fish production;To ensure regular supervision, follow-up monitoring and reporting for popularising the programme socially accepted and significant achievement; To ensure audit and evaluation of program for significant achievement;', '', '', '', 'USAID', 300000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Fisheries', 'Integrated farming.', '', '', ''),
