(1888, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agricultural Engineering Division', 'Project', 'Utilization and management of sugar mails effluent water  for irrigation purpose to increase crop', 'North Bengal Sugar mill-Notore, Pabna Sugar mill-Pabna, Rajshahi sugar mill-Rajshahi.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2010', '30-06-2012', '01-01-2010', '30-06-2012', '1.	To study the physico chemical properties of effluent on soil physicochemical properties.\r\n2.	To determine the transport properties of pollutants in effluent water through soils.\r\n3.	To study the effects of treated effluent water on growth and yield of sugarcane and other crops.\r\n4.	To evaluate the effect of effluent water on soil physiochemical properties. \r\n5.	To investigate possibility of treating the effluent by low-cost simple technique and \r\n6.	To design and develop a low-cost effluent treatment plant. \r\n', '', '', 'Sugarcanek, Irrigation, Water Management. ', 'NATP-SPGR', 9259840, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Agricultural Mechanization and water management', 'Irrigation and Water Management', '', '', ''),
(1889, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Technology', 'Project', 'Assessment of the post harvest loss of Ilish, Tenualosa ilisha in Bangladesh', 'Cox''s Bazar, Chittagong, Khulna, Barishal, Chandpur and Dhaka', '', 'Applied', '', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2013', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2013', '1) Examining existing ilish handling and processing practices with constraints.\r\n2) Assessing component wise post harvest loss of ilisha at each step of harvest, handling, packaging, transportation, marketing and processing.\r\n3) Recommending draft polices based on research results, in order to develop a sustainable ilish handling and processing system for Bangladesh.', '', '', '', 'BAURES', 240000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(1890, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agronomy', 'Project', 'Integrated Nutrient Management for maximizing growth, yield and quality of rice', 'Agronomy Field Laboratory, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', '', '01-07-2008', '30-06-2009', '01-07-2008', '30-06-2009', '1) To find out the performance of transplant aman and boro rice varieties.\r\n2) To find out the effect of urea supergranules (USG) on the yield and yield attributes of transplant aman and boro rice varieties.\r\n3) To find out the effect of poultry manure (PM) on the performance of transplant aman and boro rice varieties.\r\n4) To evaluate the combined effect of USG and PM; and Prilled urea and PM on the yield and yield attributing characters of transplant aman and boro rice varieties.', '', 'Two experiments were carried out at the Agronomy Field Laboratory, Bangladesh Agricultural University, Mymensingh in transplant aman and boro seasons 2008-2009 with objectives 1) To find out the performance of transplant aman and boro rice varieties 2) To find out the effect of urea supergranules (USG) on the yield and yield attributes of transplant aman and boro rice varieties 3) To find out the effect of poultry manure (PM) on the performance of transplant aman and boro rice varieties 4) To evaluate the combined effect of USG and PM; and Prilled urea and PM on the yield and yield attributing characters of transplant aman and boro rice varieties. The experiments were 1) Effect of variety, poultry manure and urea supergranules on the growth, yield and quality of transplant aman rice and 2) Effect of variety, poultry manure and urea super granules on the growth, yield and quality of boro rice. Two rice varieties viz. BRRI dhan41 and BRRI dhan46 for transplant aman and BRRI dhan28 and BRRI dhan29 for boro season, were included in the study. Data were recorded on same parameters in both experiments. In experiment-1, variety BRRI dhan41 gave higher yield than BRRI dhan46. For fertilizer effect, the highest grain yield (5.17 t ha-1) was obtained from full dose of USG and other inorganic fertilizers, which was similar to full dose of USG (1.8g) + PM at 2.5 t ha-1 followed by full dose of PU + PM at 2.5 t ha-1. The lowest yield was obtained in the control treatment. For treatment combinations the highest grain yield was obtained in BRRI dhan41 &times; 1.8g USG and other inorganic fertilizers and the lowest one was the control treatment. In experiment-2, variety BRRI dhan29 gave higher grain yield than BRRI dhan28. For fertilizer effect, the highest grain yield (6.16 t ha-1) was found from 2.7g USG and other inorganic fertilizers which was similar to 2.7g USG + PM at 5 t ha-1. The lowest grain yield (3.89 t ha-1) was obtained from control treatment. For interaction, the highest grain yield (6.28 t ha-1) was found in BRRI dhan29&times; 2.7g USG and other inorganic fertilizers. The lowest grain yield (3.59 t ha-1) was found in control treatment.', 'Integrated nutrient management, Quality of Rice, BRRI dhan41, BRRI dhan28, BRRI dhan29', 'BARC', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Crop nutrient management', 'Rice', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, 07-08 March, 2010. Bangladesh Agricultural Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress. Volume 20. Proceedings of the Workshop of University Research System (BAURES), BAU, Mymensingh.'),
