(1959, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Pathology', 'Project', 'Infectious coryza in poultry: characterization of Avibacterium paragallinarum by conventional and molecular methods along with experimental pathogenesis study by local isolate', 'Department of Pathology, BAU', 'High', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2012', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2012', '1.	To isolate and indentify avibacterium paragallinarum from dead and alive birds through conventional and molecular methods\r\n2.	To determine the prevalence of diseases \r\n3.	To study the pathological lesions of upper respiratory tract op poultry in natural cases.\r\n4.	To study the pathogenesis of the disease in experimental birds with local isolate of A paragallinarum. \r\n', '', '', 'Poultry, Pathology, Birds diseases', 'AU-UGC', 120000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Diseases', 'Poultry', '', '', ''),
(1960, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Farm Power and Machinery', 'Project', 'Experimental Investigation of the performance of the solar Tunnel Drier for drying Banana, Jack fruit and Spices.', '', 'High', 'Applied', '', '01-04-1998', '31-03-1999', '01-04-1998', '31-03-1999', '1) To determine the performance of the solar module and the fan operated by the solar module.\r\n2) To assess the performance of the solar tunnel drier in terms of drying time and product quality.\r\n3) To identify the most appropriate and economic design best suited to the needs of the users in Bangladesh.', 'The existing design of the solar tunnel drier in the Department of Farm power and Machinery will be further redesigned and modified. Drying tests will be conducted with banana, jack fruit and spice. During the drying tests solar radiation, ambient temparature and relative humidity, air flow rate inside the drier, temparature along the drier and weight change of the fish will be recorded at regular intervals. After production of dried products, the next step is to assess the quality of the dried products during storage. In general, the shelf life of the dried products is affected by the storage conditions in terms of temparature, relative humidity, the initial condition of the product as affected by pretreatments and drying strategyies and type of packaging materials used. In this study the influence of these parameters will be investigated in the ambient conditions using different packaging materials. Finally an economic analysis will be conducted to evaluate the viability of the system and an appropriate and economic design best suited to the needs of the users will be identified.  ', '', 'Drier, Banana, Jack fruit', 'BAURES', 145227, 0, 0, 'Report', 'Workshops', 0, '', '', '', '', '');
