(2360, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agricultural Extension and Education', 'Project', 'Identification and characterization of Technologies for households food security towards sustainable livelihood improvement in Haor area of Netrokona District. ', 'Department of agricultural extension and education, BAU, Mymensingh-2202', 'High', 'Applied', '', '', '', '', '', '1) To identify the flood tolerant crop technologies.\r\n2) To identify the short duration rice varieties in boro season.\r\n3) To ascertain the constrainsts faced by the rural poor households in food security during floods in haor area.', '', 'Haor area is a specialized area of Bangladesh becuase of its geographical settings and climatic characteristics . It is estimated that about 50 percent or more of the land surface of Bangladesh is wetland, consisting of about 700 rivers, creeks, streams and other water bodies known locally as haor, beel and khal. Food security of this area often affected seriously by flash flood, flood, droughts etc. Khaliajuri area is one of the potential haor areas. For ensuring food security of haor area, it is very needed to identify different technologies for food production. ', '', 'MOSICT', 925000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Agriculture', 'Food Security', '', '', ''),
(2361, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agricultural Chemistry', 'Project', 'Pollution assessment of industrially contaminated river water and soil surrounding Dhaka city and their impact on agricultural crops.', 'BAU, Mymensingh-2202', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '', '', '', '', '1) To assess the extent of pollution and toxicity of industrially contaminated river water and soil surrounding Dhaka city.\r\n2) To know the suitability of those contaminated water and soil for agricultural crop production.\r\n3) To examine the extent of toxicity in agricultural crops and fish population obtained from those contaminated soil and water.\r\n4) To aware the government about the acute problems of industrially contaminated river water and soil surrounding Dhaka city.', '1) Sampling Site selection: Four sampling site will be chosen from Dhaka division depending on the degree of most harmful industrial pollution.\r\n2) The pH of the soil and water sample will be analysed by immersing the electrode of pH meter.\r\n3) The electrical conductivity of soil and water samples will be measured with the help of EC meter.\r\n4) The different toxic and heavy metal content of waste water, soil and different plant samples will be determined by atomic absorption spectrophotometer following the procedure as described by APHA.\r\n5) The suitability parameters of different water samples and different water samples and different nutrient analysis of soil, water and plant samples will be done. ', 'An experiment was conducted to assess the extent of pollution of four river waters viz. Buriganga, Shitalakshya, Turag and Bangshi surrounding Dhaka city and to evaluate the comparative effect of polluted and fresh water on the yield of rice cv. BRRI dhan-29 and cabbage cv. Atlas 70. Ten water samples of each river were collected and analysed. The chemical  analyses included pH, EC, TDS, DO, Zn, Pb, Cr and Cd),. Water samples were slightly acidic to slightly neutral (5.45 to 7.60). The EC, TDS and DO ranged from 170 to 1374 (&micro;S  cm-1), 451 to 1827 (mg L-1) and 1.7 to 6.5 (mg L-1), respectively. The highest Pb (72.5 mg L-1), Zn (675.8 mg L-1), and Cd (1.08 mg L-1) concentrations were found in Buriganga water and the lowest in Shitalakshya except Cd which was lowest in Bangshi. In contrast, the highest Cr concentration (95.2           mg L-1) was found in the water of Turag river and the lowest from Shitalakshya river water. Irrigation with polluted water caused drastically low yield up to 27% for rice and 38% for cabbage compared to fresh water. The results suggest that the water of those four rivers should not be used directly for crop production particularly rice and cabbage without removing the heavy metals. Otherwise irrigated soil with polluted water may also bear its toxic consequences for a long time. ', 'Pollution, river water, soil, crops, soil pollution, water pollution, Dhaka city', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Environmental pollution of soil and water', 'Agricultural crops', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, Volume-22, 2011.  Proceedings of the workshop of BAU Research Progress, 02-03 April 2012.');
