(2398, 'Sher-e-Bangla Agricultural University', 'Department of Agronomy', 'Project', 'Evaluation of all elopathic potential of mikania micrantha) on weed growth', 'Department of Agronomy, SAU, Sher-e-Bangla Nagar, Dhaka', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-04-2013', '30-06-2014', '01-04-2013', '30-06-2014', 'i) to study the effect of mikania allelopathty to different rabi weeds.\r\nii) to evaluate the effect of mikania allelopathty to different rabi and kharif weeds.\r\n', '(a) Material: Mikania fresh plants, earthen pots, soils of preceeding aman rice field (to examine the effect soil borne weed propagules on proceeding rabi crops) and soils of preceeding wheat field(to examine the effect soil borne weed prpagules on proceeding kharif 1 crops).\r\n\r\n(b) Design of experiments: Randomized complete block design (RCBD).\r\n\r\n(c) Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives:\r\nThe study will be conducted in the weed museum of the Department of Agronomy, SAU, Dhaka. Soil from field will be collected two times: after the harvest of wheat and T. aman rice to conduct the first and second experiment respectively. The collected soil will be sun dried so that fresh mikania plant can be added in right proportion by weight. Fresh mikania plants will be collected, chopped into pieces (1-2 cm.)[(as per  Ismail and Mah, 1993)]. The pots will be filled with soil. The chopped material then will be mixed with top soil (5 cm from the upper surface as the weed seeds reside at this depth in the field) at the rate as per treatments. Experiments will be set in pots to isolate the effect on field soil weed propagules from those of the experimental site. The whole pot will be burried into the soil to simulate the field condition.  A field capacity situation will be maintained by periodical (morning and evening) application of water through watering can. The experiment will be terminated after three months.\r\nAfter germination no weeding, mulching, ferlilizing will be done. \r\nData on number of individual weed species and weight of both the shoot and root will be taken at 30 days interval by sampling three pots at each sampling time from each treatment. \r\nThe data will be analyzed and the means will be compared by LSD at 5% level of significance.\r\n\r\nTreatments: \r\nExpt 1: Evaluation of mikania allelopathty on the growth of different kharif 1 weeds after the harvest of wheat.\r\nTreatments: \r\nFresh Mikania plant rates: 6 (0, 2, 4, 6, 8, 10% of 5 cm top soil of the pot by weight). [(as per  Ismail and Mah, 1993)].\r\nReplication: 9 (3 destructive samples from each treatment at each of three sampling times).  \r\nTotal pots : 6 X 9=54.\r\nDate of initiation: April-May or later, 2013 (depending upon the allocation of fund).\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nExpt 2: Evaluation of mikania allelopathty on the growth of different Rabi weeds after the harvest of T.aman.\r\nTreatments: \r\nFresh Mikania plant rates: 6 (0, 2, 4, 6, 8, 10% of 5 cm top soil of the pot by weight). \r\nReplication: 9 (3 destructive samples from each treatment at each of three sampling times).  \r\n', 'A number of natural source of herbicides has been discovered for the control of weeds. Out of them  leachates from mikania also have been found to have allelopathic properties (Saha,1985).   \r\nAny plant material when well decomposed and added to soil act as an organic fertilizer to supply essential elements to crop plants or improve soil physical properties after its proper decomposition. But when added before decomposition, they release some organic acids which are harmful to both crop and weed plants. It is normally desirable that these allelochemicals are not or limitedly harmful to crop plants. but is quite harmful to weed plants. If such happens, these allelochemicals can be used as selective organic herbicides.  So, it is essential i) to find out which weeds are sensitive to the application of the fresh plant (eg. mikania) released allelochemcals; and next step will be ii) which crop(s) are resistant to them. After acieving this knowledge the third step will be iii) to evaluate crop-weed interaction due to application of the testing material to that crop field. This proposal includes activities to execute the first step i.e. to find out which weeds are sensitive to the application of the fresh plant (eg. mikania) released allelochemcals.  \r\nMikania has allelopathic effects on weeds (Saha,1985) and is easily available in our country round the year (Anon. 2013). Fresh plant materials like mikania release leachates when applied to soil that act directly to the surrounding plant root or react with soil components and some new formed components which either kill weeds or reduce weed growth. \r\nSo, it is necessary at the first step to isolate the effect of fresh mikania on weeds only and then to verify which crop(s) are also sensitive to these mikania application and finally to examine the interaction of crop and weeds towards the mikania in the field of the crop resistant to the mikania. Such type of research would be helpful to pave the way to innovate selective organic herbicide (s) to control weeds without creating any environmental pollutions. application of the testing material to that crop field. This proposal includes activities to execute the first step i.e. to find out which weeds are sensitive to the application of the fresh plant (eg. mikania) released allelochemcals.  \r\nMikania has allelopathic effects on weeds (Saha,1985) and is easily available in our country round the year (Anon. 2013). Fresh plant materials like mikania release leachates when applied to soil that act directly to the surrounding plant root or react with soil components and some new formed components which either kill weeds or reduce weed growth. \r\nSo, it is necessary at the first step to isolate the effect of fresh mikania on weeds only and then to verify which crop(s) are also sensitive to these mikania application and finally to examine the interaction of crop and weeds towards the mikania in the field of the crop resistant to the mikania. Such type of research would be helpful to pave the way to innovate selective organic herbicide (s) to control weeds without creating any environmental pollutions. \r\n\r\n\r\n', 'mikania allelopathty, organic herbicide, Department of Agronomy, SAU, Dhaka', 'SAURES-UGC', 60000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Weed Control', 'Mikania micrantha', '', '', ''),
