(2394, 'Sher-e-Bangla Agricultural University', 'Department of Horticulture', 'Project', 'Conservation of fruit germplasms (High valued and exotic) and characterization of two new fruits (melons) ', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '', '', '', '', 'a. Collection and incorporation of rare, high valued and exotic fruit plants/planting materials in the existing germplasm centre of SAU.\r\nb.	Creation of research environments on fruits at SAU.\r\nc.	Assist to enhance fruit diversity in Bangladesh.\r\nd.	Improvement efforts directed to the development of new superior fruit plants.\r\ne.	Introduction and performance trial of two new fruit varieties (exotic melon) inside the\r\nexisting germplasm centre of SAU.\r\nInitiatives to conduct research and to release new fruit varieties of Bangladesh under the coverage of SAU.\r\ng. Transfer of technology and associated information regarding established germplasm centre to the researchers, breeders and producers of Bangladesh.\r\n', '', 'National demand for high value fruits is increasing day b) day. Fruit production is a\r\nprofitable business in Bangladesh. Our climate and soil is favourable for tropical and subtropical fruits cultivation. We can bring more land under fruit cultivation, including the utilization of fallow land, homestead, premises of school and universities, road sides\r\nand so on. We have lot of fruits under cultivation but we are in need of high value fruit germplasms and its conservation. Access to diverse germplasm pool is crucial for successful incorporation of novel, high valued exotic fruits in commercial fruit\r\nproduction in Bangladesh. Collection and performance study of new germplasm benefits fruit industries and consumers by supplementing new fruit varieties. It NNW strengthen crop diversification of Bangladesh. In addition, our activities will create research environments on fruits at SAU. Therefore, we have taken initiatives to collect rare and\r\nhigh valued crops from country as well as to introduce new fruit crops to Bangladesh from abroad. We have taken initiatives to conduct research and to release new fruit\r\nvarieties of Bangladesh under the coverage of SAU. We are confident that our project will contribute to the social and economical development of the country. Hope, this project will be a pioneer project as to introduce new fruits to the fruit market of\r\nBangladesh.\r\n', 'Fruit, germplasm, exotic fruit, fruit plants. ', 'SAURES-UGC', 50000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
