(2545, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Parasitology', 'Project', 'Studies on the role of echinostome cercariae (Trematoda: Echinostomatidae) in the possible control of fascioliosis in Bangladesh. ', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2001', '30-06-2004', '01-07-2001', '30-06-2004', '1.	To determine the frequency of Fasciola and echinostome infections in the vector snails and their seasonal dynamics.\r\n2.	To evaluated the refractory/suppressive effect of echinostome infected snails to Gymnocephalous cercariae under  laboratory and field conditions.\r\n3.	To transfer above experimental knowledge for biocontrol of fascioliosis at farmers level, if encouraging enough. \r\n', 'a. Materials: Research materials will include culture tanks and aquarium for snails, ducks, liver, gall bladder form slaughtered ruminants, chemicals appliances, etc.\r\nb. Design of experiments.\r\nc. Procedure to be followed in achieving staged objectives. \r\n', '', '', 'BAU', 225000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2546, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agro-Forestry', 'Project', 'Fallow aldn and waste land development through sustainable agroforest production technologies.', 'BAU, Mymensingh', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2008', '31-12-2009', '01-01-2008', '31-12-2009', '1.	Examine sustainability of agroforestry systems with understory crops, vegetables spices, oils, and biodiesel yielding and medicinal plants in roadside agroforestry. \r\n2.	To develop multistoried production systems in fallow lands leading to a permanent multistoried gardens with high value trees (HVT) along  with biodiesel yielding small trees/shrubs\\, beautifying and medicinal plants crops etc. and \r\n3.	To develop agroforestry programmes/methods for constant and year round output from homestead gardens using diversified plants necessary for the house owners. \r\n', 'a.	Promising species such as Neem, Goraneem, Mehogini, Jhau, Shegun, Jatropha yielding pkant gliricidia, ipil ipil, Jambura, lemon shade loving and shade tolerant spices, green chillies, aroids, other possible crops alon g with medicinal plants will be combined in this study.\r\nb.	Plantation models of RAMPT-1 to 3 (Hossain, 2006) will be followed and modified, wherever necessary, for this study.\r\nc.	The tree management technologies and integrated three and crop management technologies proposed by Hossain (1994, 96) as shown in adjusted for this study.\r\n', '', '', 'BAU', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2547, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Pathology', 'Project', 'Viral infections of poultry: Pathological investigation, virus isolation and their molecular characterization.', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '', '', '', '', '1.Studying the pathological features of virus infections ion poultry.\r\n2.Isolation of viruses using embryo inoculation and cell culture technique.\r\n3.Molecular characterization of virus isolates using PCR, RT-PCT and gene sequencing.\r\n', '', '', 'poultry, Viral Infections of  Poultry, Diseases', 'MOSICT', 1400000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Riral Infection of Poultry', 'Poultry', '', '', ''),
(2548, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Technology', 'Project', 'Development of Value Added Fish Products form Thai Pangas (Pangasius hypophthalmus) for Export Market. ', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '', '', '', '', '1.Survey on the production and marketing chain of pangas in the domestic and export market\r\n2.To prepare quality fillets from pangas fish under different packaging conditions.\r\n3.Assessment of gel-forming ability of leached meat of pangas at different biological and storage conditions.\r\n4.Development of various value added products  such as fish ball, fish sticks, fish cutlet, fish fillets, laminated blocks, and Japanese style fish cake form surimi\r\n5.Improvement of quality of the products by binding with other food ingredients. \r\n', '', '', '', 'MOSICT', 1500000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Biological Science', 'Fishes', '', '', ''),
(2907, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Parasitology', 'Project', 'Epidemiology of Visceral Schistosomiasis in ruminants in Mymensingh, Bangladesh: I Ecology of the vector snail. ', 'Department of Veterinary Science, BAU, Mymensingh', 'High', 'Applied', '', '', '', '', '', 'Since, visceral schistosomes act as a major constraint towards profitable production of sheep, goat and cattle in the country, and precise knowledge about the epidemiology and schistosomiasis ins prerequisite for planning effective control measures, the main objective of the study is to understand the ecology of the snails which act as intermediate host of visceral schistosomes. ', '1.	The study will be conducted for one full year e.g. 12 months from the data of approval. Snails find different water reservoirs e.g. cannals, bills, ponds, rivers, etc. from proposed areas will be collected fitted ids and carried to the laboratory.\r\n2.	During snail collection all hydrographic details pertaining to the area will be recorded.\r\n3.	Records of the air  temperature and the water temperature in the immediate vicinity of the snails, exposure of the habitual to the sun, the colour and pH of the water an abundance of aquatic vegetations will be recorded periodically.  \r\n', 'a.	Identify the factors leading to snail infection. Miracidium which hatches immediately after coming in contact with water needs to find the specific intermediate snail host for continuation of the life cycle. \r\nb.	Development within the snails and its effect on epidemiology: The next stage to consider the chronological sequence is that  of development within the snail and time and season of emergence of cercariae from the snail. \r\nc.	Ecology of the specific snails.\r\nd. Yearwise distribution of the work if the project needs more then one year, give yearwise programme of the works.\r\n', '', 'BAU-UGC', 81000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
