(2550, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Biochemistry', 'Project', 'Study on the yield and quality of oyster mushroom [pleurotus ostreatus] groun in different environment and location on  different substrates using water of different sources', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '', '', '', '', 'a.	To improve mushroom cultivation through identification of suitable sustainable substrate, water and environment of different part of Bangladesh.\r\nb.	To disseminate the improved and profitable mushroom cultivation technologies to obtain higher productivity, greater benefit-cost ratio and higher income of the mushroom growers through participatory research. \r\nc.	To improved rural economic level and to reduce poverty level of men, women, and other less or no privileged groups of people through mushroom cultivation.\r\nd.	To determine the amount of heavy metals in mushroom grown in different parts of Bangladesh.\r\ne.	To determine the amount of heavy metals in mushroom grown in different substrates available in Bangladesh.\r\nf.	To determine the amount of heavy metals in mushroom grown using water of different sources. \r\n', 'Improvement of substrates for better growth and high yield of mushroom:\r\n2. Participatory research to be conducted:\r\n3. Human resource development to improve research capability on mushroom:\r\n4. Holding seminar on problems in mushroom cultivation and utilization:\r\n5. Holding workshop on finding of the project to evaluation and utilization:\r\n6. Data analysis and report writing:\r\n', '', 'Mushroom, Agriculture, Environment, Biochemistry', 'MOSICT', 300000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Biological Science', 'Agriculture', '', '', ''),
(2551, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Biology and Genetics', 'Project', 'Comparative studies on development instability , growth and genetic variability of selected hatchery populations and one natural population of rohu (Labeo rohita).', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-04-2001', '31-03-2004', '01-04-2001', '31-03-2004', '1.	To present morphological evidence that the loss of genetic variation in the hatchery stocks has adversely affected the embryological development of the Indian major carp species.\r\n2.	To quantify the loss in fish production incurring due stockings of poor quality fish seed produced in the hatcheries under the current management practices.\r\n3.	To quantify the loss of genetic variability in the hatchery stocks with respect to a wild population.\r\n4.	To find any correlation between the level of heterozygosity and growth performance. \r\n5.	To aware the farmers/hatchery operators about the importance of good broodstock management.\r\n', 'a. Material, b. Study of developmental instability, c. Growth comparison- i. Design of Experiments ii. Collection and analysis of growth data, d. Study of genetic variation by randomly amplified polymorphic DNA (RAPD) technique- Screening primers and testing reproducibility. ', '', '', 'BAU', 225000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
