(2558, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Animal Nutrition', 'Project', 'Medicinal properties of diffeent traditional herbs and their effect on plasma parameters and methane production in ruminants. ', 'Mymensingh and Tangail district and BAU Laboratory. ', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2013', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2013', '1.	Determination of nutritional status in terms of proximate components of the identified herbs.\r\n2.	Determination of Bioactive components using HPLC method.\r\n3.	Feasibility study of the herbs as animal feed through feeding trail.\r\n4.	Determination of herbal effect on plasma glucose, plasma NEFA, Blood urea and NH3, NB, Dourine derivatives and methane production.\r\n', '', '', '', 'BAU', 240000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2559, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Cooperation and Marketing', 'Project', 'Sustainable participatory Social forestry for Poverty Reduction in greater Mymensingh District.\r\n', 'Sustainable  Participatory social forestry areas under Mymensingh, Tangail and Notrokona districts', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '1.	To measure the volume of wood and crop produced by the participants.\r\n2.	To investigate economic and social benefits accrued through the process.\r\n3.	To investigate the achievement in good forest management proctors.\r\n4.	To identify problems in implementing program activities.\r\n5.	To suggest replicating precedence in other areas.\r\n', 'The project would based on data to be collected from primary and secondary sources primary sources would be the program participants from Mymensnigh sadar upazila, Bhaluka, Modhupur, Haluaghat, Nakla and Nalitabari upazilas under Mymensingh, Tangail and Netrokona district. Data would be collected from 200 samples participants by administering a pre-tested questionnaire. Secondary data would be collected from offices of the forest Department located at the study areas. The data will be tabulated and analyzed by appropriate statistical techniques like Logistic Regression Model, Head count Ratio and Income Inequality Model. ', '', 'Rorestry, Development, Economica and Social benefits, Poverty reduce', 'BAU', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Development', 'Forestry', '', '', ''),
(2560, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Food Technology and Rural Industries', 'Project', 'Processing and utilization of legume LUSKS for high-fibre food formulations', 'Department of Food Technology and Rural Industries, BAU.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '15-05-2007', '14-05-2009', '15-05-2007', '14-05-2009', '1.	Technology for dietary fibre-enriched legume husks developed.\r\n2.	Nutritional quality and functional properties of modified legume husks determined\r\n3.	Formulations of dietary fibre-enriched bakery products incorporating processed/modified legume husks developed.\r\n4.	Composition nutritional constituents and shelf-life of dietary fibre-enriched bakery products determined.\r\n5.	Food industries specially baking industries and new entrepreneurs adopted the technology for production dietary fibre-enriched bakery, products.\r\n', 'a.	Materials: Commercially available legume husks of chickpea, lentil, peas, soybeans, black gram, green gram, red gram, lathyrus, cowpea and other minor legumes will be collected from local markets. \r\nb.	Analysis for chemical composition, microbiological status and nutritional constituents of modified legume husks by standard methods. \r\nc.	Sensory evaluation of products developed containing extracted and un-extracted legume husks.\r\nd.	Evaluation of the effects of extracted and unrestricted legume husk on the quality of bread, biscuits, cakes, crackers, rolls, toasts and other baked products.\r\n', '', '', 'BAU', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2561, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Food Technology and Rural Industries', 'Project', 'Use of starch as an ingredient for production of tomato based products.', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2005', '30-06-2006', '01-07-2005', '30-06-2006', '1.	To design formulations for tomato based products incorporated with starch.\r\n2.	To analyze the tomato based products for its proximate composition and functional properties.\r\n3.	To develop various tomato products such as ketchup, puree, chutney, leather and juice, etc.\r\n4.	To evaluate the effects of starch on the organoleptic quality and functional properties of the tomato based products.\r\n5.	To study the shelf life of the prepared tomato products incorporating starch.\r\n', 'a.	The fresh tomato was collected from the local market, washed, garded according to the colour, maturity and softness. It was then cut into small pieces and blended. The blended pulp was then screened with mosquito net cloths, packed in polyethelene bag and stored in deep freeze for production of tomato products.\r\nb.	The fresh tomato pulp/juice was analyzed for its proximate composition and its functional properties, such as texture, colour, flavor, viscosity and consistency were determined qualitatively through organoleptic taste testing panel.\r\nc.	The tomato ketchup was formulated and prepared with the incorporation of starch. Different proportion of starch was used in the formulation. The nutrient and the shelf life of the ketchup were examined.\r\nd.	Sensory and organoleptic quality fo the product was evaluated through a taste-testing panel.\r\n', '', 'Tomato, Vegetables, tomato juice, ', 'University Grants Commission of Bangladesh', 56000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Production', 'Tomatoes', '', '', ''),
