(2566, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Farm Structure', 'Project', 'An Investigation on strength and Economy of Cement plastered Bamboo-mat as Fence of Rural Houses.', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-09-2004', '31-08-05', '01-09-2004', '31-08-05', '1.	To determine the mechanical properties like tensile and compressive strength, torsional strength, elastic modulus and deformation characteristic of local bamboo of varieties Borak, Mahal and Muli etc.\r\n2.	To fabricate prototype fences with bamboo-splits and cement mortar of varying ratio.\r\n3.	To ascertain the rigidity of the prototype fences against impact flood and wind speed and;\r\n4.	To analyze the economic feasibility of bamboo-made fences.\r\n', 'a.	Locally available three varieties of bamboos like Borak, Mahal and Muli, about three years of maturation will be bought from the local market and will be cut into small pieces. Because of the variation in properties along the length of bamboo may occur, therefore, three sections, Bottom, Middle and Upper will be selected for the tests.  i. Tension and compression test, ii. Torsion test, iii. Fabrication of prototype fence, iv. Testing of fence strength, and v. cost analysis.', '', 'Bamboo, Bamboo-made-fences, Cement-plastered', 'BAU', 75000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Bamboo-made-fences', 'Safty Houses', '', '', ''),
(2567, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Pharmacology', 'Project', 'Comparison of efficacy of indigenous hebal drygs with that of invented mordent frugs int he treatment of diabetes mellitus.', 'Department of Pharmacology, BAU, Mymensingh-2202', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2006', '30-06-2008', '01-07-2006', '30-06-2008', '1.	To study the effects of plants extract on Hemoglobin, GlycosylateHb and Serum cholesterol in Streptozotocin induced diabetic rats.\r\n2.	To evaluate the comparative anti diabetic effects of aqueous extractors of Neem leaves, Nayantara leaves and Garlic on the blood glucose and body weight in diabetic rats with modern drug Diamicrom MR and Amayl and to establish alternative herbal therapy for diabetic patients. \r\n', 'The present study will be undertaken to demonstrate the anti diabetic effects of Neem leaves, Garlic and Nayantara leaves. The hypoglycemic effects of these herbal preparations will be compared with patent drugs Dimicron Mr and Amayl in rat. \r\nStreptozotocin (STZ) induced Hyperglycemia: In this study, diabetes will be induced by Streptozotocin (STZ) intraperitoneal administration of single dose at the dose rate of 50 mg/kg body weight in rats increased blood glucose level significantly. \r\n', '', '', 'BAU', 150000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
