(2574, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Crop Botany', 'Project', 'Micro-propagation of Bamboo through somatic Embryogenesis', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-10-2004', '30-09-2006', '01-10-2004', '30-09-2006', '1.	To establish a complete protocol for large scale propagation of bamboo through somatic embryogenesis.\r\n2.	To induce somaclonal variation for the improvement of bamboo. And \r\n3.	To indentify salt tolerant clones. (This test could be run only in 3rd year, if the project is extended up to 3 years).\r\n', 'a.	Material: Melocana baccifera, locally known as muli bans is the predominant species of bamboo of Bangladesh which constitutes more that 70-90% of the total bamboo resource of the country. Different explants like apical bud, lateral bud, intermodal tissue, nodal segment, rhizome segment and root tip will be used as explants in this project. \r\nb.	Design of experiments: Completely randomized design will be followed.  ANOVA will be used for the analysis of data and the means will be compared by DMRT.\r\nc.	Procedure to be flowed in achieving stated objectives.\r\n', '', 'Salt tolerant clones, Bamboo, ', 'BAU', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Salt tolerant clones', 'Bamboos', '', '', ''),
(2575, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Environmental Science', 'Project', 'Effect of Stand Geometry of Plants on the Evaluation of Suitable Micro-Environments for Better yield of crops.', 'Department of Environmental Science, BAU.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-10-2004', '30-09-2006', '01-10-2004', '30-09-2006', '1.	To evaluate solar radiation interception at canopy and its transmission below the canopy,net radiation and albedo.\r\n2.	To assess the radiation use efficiency.\r\n3.	To identify suitable row orientation/stand geometry and other crop micro-environments suitable for plant productivity in this latitude.\r\n4.	To determine energy balance (Rn = IE + G).\r\n5.	To assess growth and yield. \r\n', 'The research work will be carried out at the field of the Department of Environmental Science. Single soybean and single maize will be grown in first year and in the second year maize and soybean will be intercropped flowing standard cultural practices. i. Solar radiation, ii. Net radiation, iii. Soil heat fluxes, iv. Energy balance. ', '', 'Crops, Plants', 'BAU', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Production', 'Crops', '', '', ''),
(2576, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Dairy Science', 'Project', 'Improvement of Traditional Fermented Milk ''Dahi'' by using pure lactic acid bacteria stater culture. ', 'Dairy Microbiology and Technology Laboratory, BAU.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '1.	To determine the proper ratio of lactobacilli and lactococci in starter culture, amount of sugar to be added and reduction of the volume of raw materials for the preparation of standard quality dahi.\r\n2.	To evaluate physio-chemical and microbial qualities of manufactured Dahi.\r\n3.	To disseminate the technology to the producers levels at Mymensingh.\r\n', 'a.	Selection of lactic acid bacteria strains: At least 10 strains of lactic acid bacteria will be selected as starter culture for the manufacture of quality dahi.\r\nb.	Selection of containers: Two types of container will be compared for their suitability in dahi making.\r\nc.	Preparation of dahi and its quality study: Dahi will be prepared by reducing different level of volumes of milk and bny adding starter culture as various ration of Lactobacilli and Lactococci and different levels of sugar to each. \r\nd.	Statistical analysis: Data will be analyzed according to split plot design by using Randomized Completely Block Design (RCD).\r\n', '', 'Milk, Starter culture, ', 'BAU', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Starter culture', 'Milk', '', '', ''),
