(2578, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agronomy', 'Project', 'Improvement of aerobic rice cultivation for saving irrigation water and protecting soil and environmental pollution', 'Agronomy field laboratory, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2006', '30-06-2007', '01-07-2006', '30-06-2007', '(i) to identify and select/develop rice varieties with high yield potential for aerobic system of cultivation, (ii) to evaluate the performance of boro rice under aerobic and conventional systems of cultivation, (iii) to study the effect of systems of cultivation and time of planting on yield performance of boro rice, (iv) to examine the effect of seed priming on seedlingemergence of rice under different soil moisture regimes and (v) to see the effect of fertilizer management on yield performance of rice under aerobic system of cultivation.', '', 'The study was conducted at the Agronomy Field Laboratory as well as at the Seed Laboratory of Department of Agronomy, Bangladesh Agricultural University, Mymensingh during three boro seasons (2006-07, 2007-08 and 2008-09) with the objectives to (i) to identify and select/develop rice varieties with high yield potential for aerobic system of cultivation, (ii) to evaluate the performance of boro rice under aerobic and conventional systems of cultivation, (iii) to study the effect of systems of cultivation and time of planting on yield performance of boro rice, (iv) to examine the effect of seed priming on seedlingemergence of rice under different soil moisture regimes and (v) to see the effect of fertilizer management on yield performance of rice under aerobic system of cultivation. The study comprised eight experiments (two in 2006-07, three in 2007-08 and three in 2008-09). In the genotype selection trials, 72 and 115 genotypes were included in 2006-07 and 2007-08 seasons, respectively. The two years results showed that BRRI dhan29, IR74371-3-1-1, BINA6, BRRI dhan47, BR203-70-B-2, BR802-118-3-1 and BRRI dhan45 could be considered for aerobic system of cultivation in boro season. BRRI dhan29 gives higher or comparative yield in aerobic system than conventional system of cultivation. The most optimum time for planting of BRRI dhan29 is between 5 and 20 December under aerobic system of cultivation. Priming improves germination and vigour of seed and reduces field germination time. Soil test based application of either 5 to 10 tons of cowdung plus inorganic fertilizers or only inorganic fertilizer can give high yield or rice cv. BRRI dhan29 under aerobic system of cultivation.  The result showed that conventional transplanting gave higher yield in 2007-08 but aerobic rice gave higher yield in 2008-09. The study concludes that cultivation of boro rice in aerobic system could be considered as a potential water saving technology that would save 50-60% irrigation water and give high yield compared with the conventional transplanting system.', 'Aerobic rice cultivation, Irrigation water, Protecting soil, environmental pollution', 'BAURES', 75000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Saving soil, water and Environment', 'Rice', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, 07-08 March, 2010. Bangladesh Agricultural Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress. Volume 20. Proceedings of the Workshop of University Research System (BAURES), BAU, Mymensingh.'),
