(2637, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Anatomy and  Histology', 'Project', 'Comparative Studies of the Effectiveness of Commercially Used Vaccines Against Gumboro Disease on the Cell-Mediated Mucosal Immunity of the Broilers. ', 'Department of Anatomy and Histology', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2008', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2008', '', '', 'The present research was designed to study the histological and immunohistochemical changes of lymphoid organs (bursa of Fabricius and cecal tonsil) and in the iteum (representative mucosal organ) of broiler chickens after immunization with Gumboro vaccine. Two groups (n = 24) of Cobb-500 broiler chickens were reared in a same environment. A mild vaccine (BUR 706) followed by an intermediate (Nobilis Gumboro 228 E) type vaccine was administered for immunization of chickens and samples were collected at 7 days interval for up to 32 days of age. The conventional histological structure of all three organs of the present study was similar to the earlier reports. In addition, in the bursa of Fabricius, the population of lymphocytes and the size of the follicies were found to increase in vaccinated chickens than the control chickens. The lgs positive cells (lgA, lgG and lgM) were distributed principally beneath the capsule, around the follicles and in the cortex and medulla. The frequencies of lgG and lgM- positive cells were more than the lgA-positive cells in the bursa of vaccinated group. lgM-positive cells became peak at day 25 and started to decline at day 32 in the bursa of Fabricius of vaccinated groups of chickens. In the cecal tonsils and ileum, the lgs positive cells (lgA, lgG and lgM) distributed around the intestinal gland and within the lympatic nodules of the lamina propria, in the core of the villi, and within the epithelium in both the control and vaccinated chickens. Their frequency per 0.1 mm2 area of the lamina propria and in the epithelium was increased abruptly in the vaccinated group than the control broiler chickens. Like bursa, in the cecal tonsil and ileum of vaccinated chickens, the frequencies of lgG and lgM-positive cells were also more than lgA-positive cells. The present study suggested that, the lgs positive cells were greatly accelerated in the vaccinated chickens than the control chickens and it may be due to immunomodulatory effect of vaccine.', 'Poultry, Diseases, Gumboro, bursa, mucosal', 'University Grants Commission of Bangladesh', 65800, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Livestocl iseases management', 'Broiler', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress. Volume 20. Proceedings of the Workshop of Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, 07-08 March, 2010. Bangladesh Agricultural University Research System (BAURES), BAU, Mymensingh.'),
