(2657, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agronomy', 'Project', 'Development of production package of stevia as a field crop in the agro-climatic condition of Bangladesh', 'Agronomy Field Laboratory, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2009', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2009', '', '', 'A field experiment was carried out at the Agronomy Field Laboratory of Bangladesh Agricultural University, Mymensingh during the period from March to July 2008 to study the effect of fertilizer and spacing on the performance of Stevia. Factor a): fertilizer viz. no fertilizer (F1), cowdung 10 t ha-1 (F2), urea 200 kg ha-1 (F3), urea 230 kg ha-1 (F4), urea 260 kg ha-1 (F5) and factor b): Spacing viz. 50 cm &times; 40 cm (S1), 40 cm &times; 40 cm (S2) were used as treatments. The experiment was laid out in a split plot design with three replications. The plot size was 4m2 (2m &times;2m) and total number of plots 30. The result showed that fertilizer significantly influence on different yield components except plant height. In most cases cowdung 10 t ha-1 (F2) gave highest primary branches plant-1 (3.77), secondary branches plant-1 (30.23), leaf number plant-1 (191.8), total fresh weight plant-1 (34.25), leaf fresh weight plant-1 (26.87) at 80 DAT, which was statistically identical with urea 200 kg ha-1 (F3). The worst performance showed urea 260 kg ha-1 (F5) due to toxicity of fertilizer. Out of two spacing wider spacing 50cm &times; 40cm performed better than closer spacing 40cm &times; 40 cm but when leaf yield plot-1 was calculated than closer spacing produced higher yield contributing characters and yield. Combined effect of fertilizer and spacing was significantly influenced by secondary branches plant-1 and leaf fresh weight plant-1. The highest secondary branches plant-1 (30.80) and leaf fresh weight plant-1 (27.47) was found in F2S2 (cowdung 10 ton ha-1 &times; 40 cm &times; 40 cm) which was statistically similar with F2S1 and F3S1. ', 'Stevia, Production Package, Agro-climatic condition, Bangladesh', 'MOSICT', 500000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Field crop production in the present agro-climatic condition', 'Stevia', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, 07-08 March, 2010. Bangladesh Agricultural Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress. Volume 20. Proceedings of the Workshop of University Research System (BAURES), BAU, Mymensingh.'),
