(2908, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Surgery and Obstetrics', 'Project', 'Evaluation of Multiple Ovulation and Embryo transfer technique in the improved production system in Black Bengal Goat in Bangladesh.', 'Department of Surgery and Obstetrics, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2000', '30-06-2003', '01-07-2000', '30-06-2003', '1) To evaluate the MOET technique in Black Bengal Goat in Bangladesh\r\n2) If the technique prove feasible in this breed future research will be conducted to speed up the process of genetic improvement of carcass quality including other economic traits for increasing the production system and economic development of the country.\r\n3) This will also helps the students to understand the MOET technique practically.\r\n', 'Procedures was followed:\r\n1) Synchronization of donors and recipients with prostaglandins\r\n2) Superovulation of donors with superovulatory hormone\r\n3) Natural service and /or AI of donors\r\n4) Controlling of ovulation rate in donors through surgical procedure.\r\n5) Flushing of the donors by surgical procedures to collect the embryos\r\n6) Transfer of embryos to recipients by surgical procedure.', 'Identification of the problem and its significance and review about MOET clearly shows the important of MOET technique in improving the livestock production and hence the economy of any country like Bangladesh. Bangladesh is a livestock based country, whose whole economy mainly depend increased number of livestock species, for cultivation, milk, meat and lather production. Therefore there is an urgent', 'Black Bengal Goat, Embryo, MOET', 'BAURES', 225810, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Livestock production and improvement', 'Black Bengal Goat', '', '', ''),
