(2540, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Biology and Genetics', 'Project', 'Study of Inbreeding problems of thai pangas (Pangasius sutchi) in Bangladesh using Allozymen Electrophoresis.', 'Mymensingh district', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2002', '31-12-2002', '01-01-2002', '31-12-2002', '1.	To assess the genetic quality of P. sutchi allozymen electrophoresis will be conducted for the genetic variation among hatchery populations. \r\n2.	To assess the genetic variability of each population of P. Sutchi brood and their fry will be conducted for allozymen study and genotypic data will compared for the inbreeding depression rate of each generation.\r\n3.	To establish the original sources of P. sutchi brood for hatchery/farm owner to large scale genetic quality fry production using this research information.\r\n', 'a.	The stocking pond and the fingerlings (1+) rearing pond will be prepared and pond management will be done by using proper inputs.\r\nb.	The genetic distance D = 1.0 for species, 0.1 for subspecies and from 0 to 0.1 for racial level will be considered.\r\nc.	The same activities will be repeated with samples of Bogra regional in the 2nd year and with samples of jessore regional in the 3rd year.\r\nd.	At least twenty individual from each population will be considered for allozyme electrophoretic analysis. In this case both muscle and liver samples will be used for tissue specific variation.\r\n', '', '', 'ICLARM (world fish center)', 250000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2538, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Animal Science', 'Project', 'Tannin from Syzygium cumini may protect protein from ruminal degradation and may boost-up bypass protein available for the ruminants. ', 'Goat, sheep and horse farm, animal Science and Animal Nutrition Laboratory and Field Laboratory, BAU.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '1.	Characterization of Syzygium cumini leaves, seeds and bark in terms of chemical composition and anti-nutritional contents.\r\n2.	In vitro ruminal incubation to investigate the nutritional quality of leaves, seeds and bark.\r\n3.	Use of polyethylene glycol (PEG) to assess the improvement of nutritional values of leaves, seeds and bark and to assess the tannin activity.\r\n4.	In vitro incubation to study protein protection in the rumen and other fermentation parameters from a concentrate diet with the addition of tannin containing leaves, seeds and bark meals. \r\n', 'a.	Sampling of leaves and seeds\r\nb.	Chemical characterization: i. Determination of nutritional properties. ii. Determination of tannins.\r\nc.	In vitro incubations: i. Assessing fermentation pattern and the effect of polyethylene glycol- Incubation and measurement of gas, Measurement of short chain fatty acid and ammonia, Organic matter digestibility and metabolizable energy. \r\nAssessing protein precipitation capacity- Incubation and sampling, analysis of soluble and pellet protein, Evaluation of protein pattern with electrophoresis. \r\n', '', '', 'BAU', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2537, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Farm Power and Machinery', 'Project', 'Feasibility study on the production of Bio-diesel form Jatropha Carcus in Bangladesh. ', 'BAU farm, Modhupur forest area, and Brahmaputra riversides (char area)', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '1.	To verify the present state of the art on the use of jatropha carcus in Bangladesh and suitable cultivation technique. \r\n2.	To develop suitable oil expellers for Jatropha seed crushing.\r\n3.	To develop methods to verify the physic-mechanical, electrical and thermal properties of jatropha oil suitable for diesel engine operation and rural energy supply for the poor people. \r\n4.	Performance studies of small diesel engines with Jatropha oil and economics of Jatropha oil use in Bangladesh. \r\n', '', '', '', 'BAU', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
