(2535, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agricultural Finance', 'Project', 'An Economic evaluation of the leasing System of Jalmahal Management of Bangladesh', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-1996', '30-06-1997', '01-07-1996', '30-06-1997', '1.	To examine the leasing arrangements of inland open water bodies and its terms and conditions with the government.\r\n2.	To identify beneficiaries of leased out water bodies and determine their socio-economic characteristics.\r\n3.	To determine the extent of under valuation of the leased out water bodies over time.\r\n4.	To analyze the profitability of open water fishing taken place in leased-out water bodies.\r\n5.	To identify problems associated with the leasing system of management of jalmahals from the view point of fisherman. \r\n', '', 'a.	Name of districts and water bodies.\r\nb.	Identification of successful bidders.\r\nc.	Identification of sub-leases.\r\nd.	First bid values of the successful bidders/\r\ne.	Sub lease values of the water bodies.\r\nf.	Names of fisherman operating in the water bodies.\r\ng.	Socioeconomic characteristic of the first leassess.\r\nh.	Comments of different parties regarding Jalmahal administration and management.\r\ni.	Repayment schedule of the bid values.\r\n', '', 'University Grants Commission of Bangladesh', 100000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2536, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Farm Structure', 'Project', 'Low-cost evaporative cooling system for tunnel ventilation of poultry farms', 'Meterial &amp; conccrete testing laboratory, BAu, Poultry farm, BAU, Aftab Bahumukhi Farm ltd. Bajitpur, Kishoregonj.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', 'The purpose of the study is to develop low cost, durable and effective evaporative cooling system for the tunnel ventilation system, which will certainly improve the cooling performance of the poultry, sheds in summer and the production rate till increase significantly. The performance of the proposed system will be studied and compared with the existing ones. The total is of two folds \r\na. to develop an low cost evaporative cooling pad, \r\nb. to develop[ a cold water circulation system that will be used to drip on the pad.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2531, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Irrigation and Water Management', 'Project', 'Evaluation and development of Low-head Drip Irrigation Systems for Small Scale Farmers', 'Hydraulic Laboratory, Dept. of IWM and Bangladesh Agricultural University Farm, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2010', '30-06-2012', '01-07-2010', '30-06-2012', '1.	Construction of a experiment framework in the laboratory for evaluating the performance of the existing drip irrigation system. The effect of water supply head, land slop and lateral length on emitter discharge along with the drip line will be evaluated.\r\n2.	The Design parameters for an appropriate low-head drip irrigation system will be identified in order to design and develop a low-cost drip system using indigenous resource and skill.\r\n', '', 'This experiment was conducted to evaluate the suitability of a drip irrigation system which has been introduced recently in some places of Bangladesh by ARPA Engineering, Dhaka without any technical and economic evaluation to evaluate the performances of this system, a timber framework was conducted in the laboratory to support the drip lines at various land slopes (0-1.5%). A mini water tank having the capacity of about 100 liter water was placed on a wooden stand the height of which could be changed to achieve varying supply heads. The combined effects of water supply head, slope and lateral length on water distribution along the drip line were evaluated. Coefficient of variation (CV), emission uniformity (EU) flow variation (FV) and emitter discharge (Q) were computer. The computer values showed that for different heads and slopes Eu values are &lt;70% and Fv values &gt;20% which indicate that the performances of this drip system are very poor and would emit water non-uniformly along a drip line. This drip system will lead to either over irrigation or under irrigation along different section of a drip line and result in very low irrigation efficiency. As such a mini plastic discharging tube (2-5 mm dia) passing through the metallic nut engrave wooden ring with facility of screwing was developed to work as emitter (wooden tap). The tap was found very effective and suitable as emitter. ', 'Irrigation, Water Managemet', 'University Grants Commission of Bangladesh', 240000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Irrigation and Water Management', 'Agriculture', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, Volume-22, 2011.  Proceedings of the workshop of BAU Research Progress, 02-03 April 2012.'),
(2532, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agricultural Economics', 'Project', 'An Investigation of Integrated Rice processing Technology for Improving Livelihood in an Agriculture Community.', '', 'High', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2006', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2006', '1.	To familiarize the devices for harvesting, threshing and drying in rice processing to the farmers.\r\n2.	To estimate the economic return through reducing harvest labor and post harvest losses of rice processing, and increased return for quality improvement.\r\n3.	To examine the profitability of investment on mechanical reaper, power thresher and dryer in rice processing system.\r\n4.	To investment the problems and constraints faced by the farmers for adopting the devices of rice processing system.\r\n5.	To suggest for polity implication.\r\n', 'The collected data will be compiled, tabulated and analyzed in accordance with the objectives of the study. in some cases, some sophisticated statistical tools such as student t-test, analysis of variance (ANOVA), Dun-can''s multiple range test (DMRT) will be used to test the significance of the different variables. ', '', '', 'BAU', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2533, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agricultural Economics', 'Project', 'Community based integrated technology investigation for post harvest rice processing for improving livelihood of resource poor farmers.', 'Takurgaon district', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-11-2002', '31-10-2003', '01-11-2002', '31-10-2003', '1.	To familiarize the devices for harvesting, threshing and drying in rice processing to the farmers.\r\n2.	To estimate the economic return through reducing harvest labor and post harvest losses of rice processing, and increased return for quality improvement.\r\n3.	To examine the profitability of investment on mechanical reaper, power thresher and dryer in rice processing system.\r\n4.	To investment the problems and constraints faced by the farmers for adopting the devices of rice processing system.\r\n5.	To suggest for polity implication.\r\n', 'To achieve the objectives, it has been planned to implement the project with joint collaboration of ASA and its informal group at village level and with technical assistance from the BAU, Mymensingh,  post harvest operation of BRRI and RDRS workshop at Takurgaon. this project is mainly for paddy that difficult to dry especially in the rainy season due to cloudy weather. So , Boro season is the best time to conduct this research. At least one boro season need to be considered for better and conclusive findings/outputs.', '', '', 'BAU', 75000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Harvesting', 'Rice', '', '', ''),
(2529, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Irrigation and Water Management', 'Project', 'Deficit irrigation for maize production.', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Farm, Mymensingh.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2008', '30-06-2010', '01-07-2008', '30-06-2010', '1.	To evaluate the effects of different deficit irrigation levels on growth and development of maize at different growth stages. \r\n2.	To study the effects of irrigation on yield and yield components of maize.\r\n3.	To find out the water productivity of maize, and\r\n4.	To identify the moisture sensitive growth stages of maize.\r\n', '', '', 'Irrigation, Maize, Water management.', 'BAU', 240000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Irrigation and Water Management', 'Crops', '', '', ''),
(2530, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agricultural Economics', 'Project', 'Poverty reduction through women employment in farms and rice mills in some areas of Dinajpur district.', 'Rice-parboiling mills and farms in Dinajpur district ', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2009', '30-06-2010', '01-07-2009', '30-06-2010', 'The specific objectives of the study are: \r\ni. to examine the socio-economic profiles of women participated in farms and rice parboiling mills activities;\r\nii. to examine contribution of women to household income which reducing their poverty;\r\niii. to identify the factors influencing the level of family income in farms and rice parboiling mills workers; and iv. to identify the problems and constraints of farms and rice parboiling mills. ', 'According to Yang (1995)&quot;The area in which a farm business survey is to be carried out depends on the particular purpose of the survey and the possible co-operation form the farmers. to achieve the objectives of the present study a preliminary survey will be conducted in Sadar Upazila of Dinajpur district to understand the broad socioeconomic characteristics of the area. It is always convenient to choose the sampling technique the planning stage of the farm household survey. Considering the objectives, time availability of fund, manpower and availability of mill proprietors, mill women labourer and farm women labourer mentioned above will be selected randomly. Sixty mill women labourer, 60 farm women labourer will be selected randomly from a list of total number.', '', 'Employment, Manpower, Women, Rice mills', 'BAU', 120000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Employment', 'Manpower', '', '', ''),
(2526, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Food Technology and Rural Industries', 'Project', 'Studies on design, fabrication and parameters optimization of a low cost laboratory scale bioreactor/fermenter', 'Department of food technology and rural industries.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-7-2009', '30-06-2011', '01-7-2009', '30-06-2011', 'Efficient design, fabrication with locally available materials and application in some biotechnological processes of a laboratory scale bioreactor. ', 'a. Materials/equipments: Microbial strains, enzymes, motor, thermocouple, pH probe, stainless steel/Pyrex glass jar, PVA filter, aeration arrangement and holding arrangement.\r\nb. Methods: Design of fermenter- H/T ratio, D/T ratio, Baffle ratio.', 'Biotechnology is an important tool in manufacture of foods with better digestibility, improved taste, nutritional value and functional properties. In Bangladesh, biotechnological application in food processing is limited only in manufacture of some traditional products like pickles, vinegar, bread, black tea, yogurt, dahi, butter etc. the latest concern in the field of food biotechnology like production of high yielding microbes, isolation and cultivation of pure culture, enzyme production and bioconversion are in quite development stage. Lack of suitable infrastructure and modern facilities are thought to be the major constrains in this regards. The foremost equipment necessary for food biotechnological process ins fermenter/reactor, which provides controlled environmental condition for the growth of microbes preventing the entry and growth of undesirable microbes preventing the entry and growth of undesirable microbes from other side. However, the equipment is not available in any laboratory in Bangladesh Agricultural University (BAU). In this connection the completed project was undertaken to design, fabricate and parameters optimization of a low cost laboratory scale fermenter, which was carried out in the department of Food Technology and Rural Industries, BAU, Mymensingh and Bismillah Engineering, Saidabad, Dhaka and it is available in the Development laboratory. Design of different parts like vessel, impeller, shaft, motor capacity etc. of the fermenter was carried out using standard dquations, charts and graphs and layout of each part was carried out according to the calculated dimensions. According to the design and layout, the fermenter was fabricated with the heop of Bismillah Engineering, Saidhabad, Dhaka. The fabricated fermenter consists of stainless steel vessel o  capacity 25 L having the total high-diameter ratio of 2:1 and a stirrer shaft connected with an impeller of dia 7.9 inch at the lower part and a 1Hp three phase variable speed (0-1320) motor at the upper part. A control panel, thermometer, safety valve and pressure gauge were also facilitated for safe operation of the fermenter. Parameters optimization of the fabricated fermenter is yet to be completed due to unwanted early closing of the project', 'Food, Vinegar, bread, black tea, yogurt, dahi, butter', 'BAU', 239520, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, Volume-22, 2011.  Proceedings of the workshop of BAU Research Progress, 02-03 April 2012.'),
(2527, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Food Technology and Rural Industries', 'Project', 'Development of Jujuble (Ziziphus jujubal) preservation, processing, packaging and products diversification technologies.', 'Department of Food Technology and Rural Industries, BAY, Mymensingh-2202', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2010', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2010', 'Adequate packaging, processing and storage methods developed for fresh jujube and jujube products of commercial importance', 'a. Materials: Three varieties of Jujube, food-grade chemicals and preservatives, sugar, spices, packaging materials etc.\r\nb. Methods: i. Proximate analysis of the different varieties of jujube will be completed following standard methods of analysis. ii. List of products that will be developed. iii. Proximate analysis of the products developed. iv. Shelf-life studies of the products developed. v. Taste panel evaluation and scoring of the products. \r\nc. Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives. ', '', '', 'University Grants Commission of Bangladesh', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2528, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Irrigation and Water Management', 'Project', 'Improvement of Irrigation system performance and assessment of irrigation water quality of BAU farm. ', 'BAU Farm, Mymensingh', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2010', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2010', '1.	Quantification of irrigation water used for rice and wheat\r\n2.	Determination of ET for rice and wheat.\r\n3.	Judicious irrigation scheduling.\r\n4.	Determination of crop water productivity for rice and wheat.\r\n5.	Reduction of conveyance loss and field loss.\r\n6.	Study the recharge and depletion characteristics of ground water, and \r\n7.	Determination of irrigation water quality parameters including arsenic. \r\n', 'Series of field experiments will be carried out at BAU farm with various rice and wheat varieties combining with different water management practices in order to find out the best irrigation scheduling strategies for optimum yield of crop using minimum water.\r\nInflow-outflow method will be used for measuring conveyance loss and various combination of low-cost lining materials will be used to reduce conveyance loss in earthen channel\r\n', 'A field experiment was carried out at the Bangladesh Agricultural University (BAU) farm during Aman Season to find out the effect of alternate wetting and drying (AWD) irrigation method on water productivity and production of rice. The experimental layout was made using split-plot design (SPD) with two high yielding varieties of rice V1 (BRRI) dhan-49) and V2 BINA-7) and four irrigation treatments viz. rainfed (T1), water applied to make 5 cm submergence when the water level within the observation pipe fell 15, 20 and 25 cm below ground level and were denoted as T2, T3 and T4, respectively. Perforated pipes were installed in the plots according to IRRI guideline to measure depletion of water level by suing Graduated scale. During crop establishment stage, 5 cm standing water was maintained. Irrigation treatments showed significant effect on yield and other contributing characters of rice. The highest grain yield (7.75 t/ha) was found in treatment T3, its water use efficiency was also the highest which is 57.83 kg/ha/cm (0.58 kg/m3). The lowest grain yield (6.01t/ha and found in treatment T1 and the yields for treatments T2 and T4 were found as 6.65 t/ha and 7.48 t/ha, respectively. The highest water requirement (110 cm) was found in treatment T1 and the lowest (80 cm) in treatment T4. The highest grain yield of 7.26 t/ha was obtained with V1 (BRRI dhan-49) and 6.67 t/ha in V2 (BINA-7_. Considering the interaction effects, the highest grain yield of 8.46 t/ha was obtained in V1T4, second highest as 7.81 t/ha, was obtained in V2Y3. The various irrigation water quality indicators such as, total dissolved solids (TDS), sodium adsorption ration (SAR), soluble sodium percentage (SSP) and residual sodium bi-carbonate (RSBC) were calculated. All these values were found within the safe limit indicating that the water can safely be used for irrigation purpose. ', 'Irrigation, Aman, Rice, Water productivity', 'BAU', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Rice and Wheat production', 'Irrigation and Water Management', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, Volume-22, 2011.  Proceedings of the workshop of BAU Research Progress, 02-03 April 2012.'),
