(2440, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Soil Science', 'Project', 'Yield maximization of pulse crops in Bangladesh', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2005', '30-06-2006', '01-07-2005', '30-06-2006', '1.	Maximization of yield of pulses such as, a. Mungbean b. Blackgram.\r\n2.	Seed production and preservation through promising farmers, and\r\n3.	Training of new batches of farmers on improved production and preservation package of pulses.\r\n', '1.	Fertilizer Treatment:\r\na.	Contro (without fertilizer)\r\nb.	Farmers Practice\r\nc.	Complete inorganic fertilizer\r\nd.	Bio+Inorganic fertilizer\r\n2.	Number of Replications: 4 (four)\r\n3.	Experimental design: Randomized block design\r\n4.	Characteristic of the plots/units;\r\na.	Number 16 plots for each experiment\r\nb.	Plot size 4m x 5m (20m2)\r\nc.	Planting distance: standard practice will be followed\r\nd.	Crop variety: modern HYV mungbean\r\ne.	Border area description: 1 m on all sides; same crop to be fertilizer lightly \r\n5.	Factors in study:\r\na.	Initial analysis of soil samples\r\nb.	Dry matter yield at different stages of growth\r\nc.	Yield contributing characteristic and yield of crops\r\nd.	Protein content of the grain\r\ne.	Statistical interpretation and socio-economic analysis\r\nf.	Post-harvest analysis of soil \r\ng.	Development of scientific ways of pulse preservation by farmers\r\nh.	Development of awareness for increased requirement of pulse gains by common people in dietary food habit. \r\n', '', '', 'BARC', 120000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Production', 'Pulse', '', '', ''),
