(2434, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agricultural Extensiion Education', 'Project', 'Livelihood improvement of landless Rural women through technological interventions of GO-NGO collaboration', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '', '', '', '', 'To make aware and develop skill of landless rural women, field level development workers in utilizing income generating technologies (IGTs) towards livelihood improvement. This can be achieved through.\r\na.	Demonstrations of selected income generating technologies and meeting at demonstrations, and\r\nb.	Publishing and distributing leaflets/folders on selected IGTs to rural women and concerned development workers. \r\n', 'The study locale would be one village each of Muktagacha and Fulbaria upazila of Mymensingh district were DAE has been implementing its collaborative efforts with GGOs to include landless women in IGTs towards sustainable agricultural and rural development. Because, the study will utilize the landless women groups already exist in the locality.\r\nSAAO and related NGO workers would be selected from those who already received training on different ITGs from the first phase of this project to conduct demonstrations on the IGTs. Also some leaflet/folder would be developed with the help of experts of relevant IGTs. The leaflets would be distributed among the villagers who will attend the meeting at demonstrations and the relevant NGO workers and SAAO of the Upazilas.\r\nThe final report will be composed with all the activities done related to conduction of demonstration and development and distribution of extension materials.\r\n', '', '', 'BARC-ATTP', 0, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
