(2407, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agronomy', 'Project', 'Effect of poultry manure, urea super granules and prilled urea on the growth, yield and quality of transplant aman and boro rice', 'Laboratory and Field laboratory, Department of Agronomy, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2010', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2010', 'a.To find out the performance of both transplant Aman and Boro rice varieties.\r\nb.To find out the suitable depth of placement of USG for both transplant Aman and Boro rice cultivation.\r\nc.To find out the suitable spacing of transplanting of both transplant Aman and Boro rice.\r\nd.To find out various interactions among variety, spacing of transplanting and depth of placement of USG in transplant Aman and Boro rice.\r\ne.To find out the effect of USG on the yield and yield attributes of transplant Aman and Boro rice varieties.\r\nf.To find out the effect of PM on the performance of both transplant Aman and Boro rice varieties and \r\ng.To evaluate the combined effect of USG and PM; and Prilled urea and PM on the yield and yield attributing characters of transplant Aman and Boro rice varieties.\r\n', '', '', '', 'AU-UGC', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2410, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Pharmacology', 'Project', 'Therapeutic efficacy of some indigenous drugs against coccidiosis in poultry. ', 'Department of Pharmacology lab. BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-08-1993', '31-07-1994', '01-08-1993', '31-07-1994', 'a.To study the efficacy of crude watery extracts of fresh leaves/fruits of Akanda, Pudina, Chutra and Thankuni against coccidiosis in chicks and\r\nb.To investigate the comparative efficacy of the crude watery extracts of fresh leaves of most effective plants with that of modern patent drug esbz or embazine against coccidiosis in chicks.\r\n', '1.The leave s of the selected plants were dried and pulvorised in a grinding machine and preserved in an air tight bottle. 10 grams ground powder from each sample was taken in a beaker, mixed throughly and boiled for 15-20 minutes. The contents were filtered by passing through fine mosline and then the watery extract was placed in a sterilized air tight bottle for further use.\r\n2.Forty infected chicks were randomly divided into 8 groups each consisting of 5 chicks, 6 groups of chicks received crude watery extracts of pudhina, Thankun I at 3 different doses (3, 6 and 12) for 12 days twice daily at same dose and route and following parameters were studied: a. clinic al examination of the treated chicks, b. Microscopic examination of the faces. \r\n', '', '', 'University Grants Commission of Bangladesh', 35000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2668, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Soil Science ', 'Project', 'Integrated and  balanced use of manures and fertilizers for sustenance of soil fertility and crop productivity in the Rice-Rice and Wheat-Rice system. ', 'Soil Science field laboratory, Dept. of soil science, BAU, My-2202', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2013', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2013', '1.	To maximize the yield of rice and wheat through integrated and balanced use of manures and fertilizers.\r\n2.	To determine the contribution of cow dung, poultry manure and compost of soil fertility and organic matter build up the in rice and wheat based cropping patterns.\r\n3.	To estimate improvement of soil environment resulting from increase in soil organic matter content as well as improvement in soil physical and chemical properties due to integrated nutrient management. \r\n', '', '', '', 'BAU', 339800, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Fertility', 'Soil', '', '', ''),
(2669, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agronomy', 'Project', 'Development of technology for reducing for reducing weed seed-bank by adopting appropriate cropping sequence. ', 'Department of Agronomy Field, BAU.', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2013', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2013', '1.	To estimate the total number of weed seed, species composition and dominant weed species present in the soil seed bank and above ground weed flora in each crop.\r\n2.	To predict future weed infestation by making correlation of seed population in soil with above ground weed flora.\r\n3.	To evaluate the influence of weed management treatments on soil seed bank dynamics, weed population and crop productivity in different cropping sequence. \r\n', '', '', 'Crops, Seed-bank, Seed processing, ', 'BAU', 240000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Seed technology', 'Crops', '', '', ''),
