(2671, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Soil Science', 'Project', 'Development of a rapid in field colorimetric method for soil organic matter determination. ', 'Department of soil science, BAU, Mymensingh-2202', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2013', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2013', '1.	To develop a rapid, easy, cheap and in-field method for soil organic carbon determination for farmer.\r\n2.	To improve the quality and economical value of BAU soil testing kit by including soil organic matter determination method which is now lacking of this method. \r\n', '', '', '', 'BAU', 240000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Organic Matter', 'Soil', '', '', ''),
(2672, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Irrigation and water management', 'Project', 'Estimation of crop co-efficient (Kc) of HYV Rice and Wheat', 'BAU farm, Mymensingh-2202', 'High', 'Applied', '', '01-07-1993', '30-06-1994', '01-07-1993', '30-06-1994', '1) To determine the reference crop eva-potranpiration ET (Potential eva-potranspiration) from standard meteorological observation and actual eva-potranspiration ETa of the crops based on IW/CPE rations.\r\n2) To estimate the values of crop co-efficient (Kc) at various stages of growth and development of HYV rice and wheat.\r\n ', '1) To select the experimental plots.\r\n2) To find out the values of Field capacity (FC) and wilting point (WP) of the experimental soil.\r\n3) To lay out the experimental field plots (4.0 m X 3.0 m) with 3 replications and to identify the number of the treatments.', '', 'eva-potranspiration, Field capacity, Meterological ', 'BAU-UGC', 209480, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Irrigation and water management', 'Rice and wheat', '', '', ''),
(2673, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of farm power and machinery', 'Project', 'Study on tillage systems related to the cropping systems round the calender year', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-1994', '30-06-1995', '01-07-1994', '30-06-1995', '1) To study the tillage pattern for different crops that can be grown round the year.\r\n2) To study the soil physical and mechanical properties during tillage operation for different crops that will be produced in the same plot of land.\r\n3) To study the total energy requirement per ha for different crop production per year.\r\n4) To assess the total amount of crop production per unit energy per year.\r\n5) To find out the total amount of crop production per year per ha in the prevailing cropping pattern and tillage cycle.', '1) Crop rotation calender will be scheduled before biggening of the cropping season for the year round.\r\n2) Tillage activities (seedbed preparation, crop management, tillage, weed control and post-harvest tillage) for various crops will be conducted according to the crop orientation pattern.\r\n3) Draft power output of bullocks and the energy requirement for the total tillage activities during the year round crop production system will be measured.\r\n4) The soil moisture content, density and soil penetration resistance will be measured during the tillage activities dictates by the crop rotation.\r\n5) Accordingly, the total amount of energy requirement per ha per year and the total crop production per ha will be estimated.\r\n6) The total amount of crop production per unit energy per year will be estimated.\r\n7) Analysis of various crop production in the tillage cycle will be made with a microcomputer for a recommendation of energy requirement per ha round the year.', '', 'Tillage pattern, crop production, Draft power, Soil moisture content', 'BAURES', 130795, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Tillage pattern development', 'Cropping systems development', '', '', ''),
(2674, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Irrigation and water management', 'Project', 'Improvement of some selected indigenous divices for low lift irrigation', 'Department of Irrigation and water management, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-1997', '30-06-1999', '01-07-1997', '30-06-1999', '1) Identification of all the defects and problems associated with the performance and operation of the pumps.\r\n2) Reconstruction of the blower pump with different dimensions to find out relationship among the sizes of suction box, discharges, head, efficiency and power requirement to evaluate the optimum size and shape of the pump chamber and flapper valves.\r\n3) Reconstruction of wheel pump at different dimensions to find out relationship among cylinder diameter, stroke length, discharges, efficiency and power requirement in order to fixed up the appropriate size of the pump.\r\n4) Study on economical viability of both the blower and wheel pumps and preparation of a ranking list on the basis of economical merits for all available traditional and low cost lifting devices.', 'The materials to be used for the fabrication of the proposed wheel and blower pumps are as follows:\r\nPVC cylinders, PVC sheets, Steel sheets, M.S. rods, G.I. pipes, Angle bars, Flat bars, Ball bearings, Nut and bolts, Hinge, Joint screws, Elbow, wheels, Gaskets, Tyre inner tubes, Sand, Cement, Khoa, Woods etc.\r\nConstruction of Wheel Pumps: The following parts as needed to manufacture the wheel pump will be constructed in the laboratory\r\n1) Concrete Base\r\n2) Cylinder\r\n3) Pump Support\r\n4) Crankshaft and wheel\r\n5) Plunger', 'Indigenous lifting devices like swing baskets and done are being widely used throughout the country to irrigate small rice, wheat and vegetable plots. These traditional methods are labour intensive, low-cost and simple in operation and within the competence of unskilled lkabour using hand tools. But efficiencies of these Devices are very low and can not be used under all situations especially when lifting head is more than one metre. The principle of design and construction of both wheel and blower pumps appears to be very attractive. There is a great scope of further studies on the design and reconstruction of these two lifting devices for the substantial improvement of their performance. With this idea in mind, the present study programme is planned to redesign and reconstruct wheel and blower pump in order to remove the existing defects and problems associated with their operation and maintenance. ', 'Cylinder, Wheel Pmump, Crankshaft, Plunger', 'BAURES', 368950, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Development of indigenous irrigation Devices', 'Low Lift Irrigation Pump', '', '', ''),
(2675, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agricultural Extension Education', 'Project', 'Knowledge of vegetables growers on health perspective of pesticide exposure. ', 'Pakundia and Fulbaria Upazila under Kishorgonj and Mymensingh district.', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-07-2012', '30-06-2013', '01-07-2012', '30-06-2013', '1.	Determi8ning vegetable growers knowledge on health and environmental perspective of pesticide exposure. \r\n2.	Identifying the present trend of pesticide use by the vegetable growers.\r\n3.	Identifying important characteristics of vegetable growers.\r\n4.	Identifying vegetable growers, problems using pesticide\r\n5.	Determining reasons behind the excessive use of pesticides by the vegetable growers. \r\n', '', '', 'Vegetable, Environment, Pesticide', 'BAU-UGC', 150000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Environment', 'Vegetables', '', '', ''),
