(2726, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Technology', 'Project', 'Improvement of existing Fish Drying Processes Practicing in the Coastal Area of Bangladesh', 'Faculty of Fisheries, BAU, Mymensingh-2202', 'High', '', 'On-going', '01-07-2012', '30-06-2013', '01-07-2012', '30-06-2013', '1.	To improve the traditional fish drying techniques for the sustainable production of health hazard chemicals free safe dried products.\r\n2.	To determine the optimal conditions for drying process for different fish species.\r\n3.	To evaluate the product quality and storage life to dried products under various packaging and storage conditions.\r\n4.	To ensure the expire data of possessed products through shelf life study.\r\n5.	To disseminate the improve drying and storage techniques to the fishers community involved with this drying industry. \r\n', '', '', 'Fish, Harvest process, Fish Storage', 'BAU-UGC', 50000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Harvest Process', 'Fish', '', '', ''),
(2727, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Crop Botany', 'Project', 'Ex-situ conservation and Characterization of rare and endangered wild leafy vegetables and minor cereals', 'Botanical Garden, BAU, Mymensingh-2202', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2008', '30-06-2010', '01-07-2008', '30-06-2010', '1) To document taxonomic identification and genetic diversity in wild vegetables and minor cereals.\r\n2) To contribute to the conservation of rare and endangered wild leafy vegetables and minor cereals for achieving a foundation for long-term security and sustainability of agriculture and environment of the country.', 'a) Collection of plant species.\r\nb) Evaluation and characterization.\r\nc) Propagation and multiplication of germplasm\r\nd) Monitoring of plant survival and growth', 'Traditional leafy vegetables and minor cereals are crucial to food security and nutrition, particularly during famines or natural disasters. But unfortunately, these important plant species remain inadequately documented and neglected by formal research and conservation. Also, these important PGR are now in greatest threat to extinction due to overexploitation and loss of natural habitats. The decline of these crops and their wild relatives may erode the genetic base and prevent the distinctive and valuable traits being used in crop adaptation and improvement. The erosion of these species can have immediate consequences on food security and well-being of the poor.\r\nConsidering the threats from the loss of plant species, the primary challenge is to conserve these neglected and underutilized species to secure their survival and environmental adaptation.', 'Traditional leafy vegetables, Conservation, Food security, PGR', 'BAURES', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Wild crop conservation', 'Vegetables and minor cereal crops', '', '', ''),
(2728, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Farm Power and Machinery', 'Project', 'Feasibility study for promotion of oil palm cultivation in Bangladesh towards self sufficiency in edible oil and food security.', 'Department of FPM, BAU, Agricultural farm, and BINA crop phisiology lab. Mymensingh', 'High', 'Evaluation /Impact studies ', 'On-going', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2013', '01-07-2011', '30-06-2013', '1.	To identify a policy and institutional framework and develop a strategy for the cultivation of oil palm plantation. \r\n2.	To develop the oil palm garmplasm center (GPC) /road side plantation at BAU campus as a facility fro education, research, training and commercial purpose.\r\n3.	To develop strategies for more effective extension intervention.\r\n4.	Produce a toolkit for extension officers plantation manager, oil palm growers, nursery owners and trainers. \r\n', '', '', 'Oil, Oil palm cultivation.', 'BAU', 240000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Production', 'Oil seeds', '', '', ''),
