(2731, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Plant Pathology', 'Project', 'Seed quality as affected by chemical seed treatment and fumigation at different level of moisture content of the seeds.', 'Laboratory, Department of Plant Pathology, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-03-2010', '28-02-2012', '01-03-2010', '28-02-2012', '1) To know the effect of provex on seed borne and storage pathogens at different moisture content of rice seeds in the store house.\r\n2) Establish relationship between moisture regimes of stored seeds with incidence of seed borne pathogens and infestation of stored grain pests of rice.', 'The seed samples of rice will be collected from the farmers immediately after harvest of aman rice. The moisture content of the seed lots will be dertermined by oven dry method. Seed lots with moisture content 10, 10.5, 11, 11.5, 12, 12.5, 13, 13.5, 14, 14.5 and 15 will be selected. Twenty kg of seeds of each seed lot will be used for seed treatment with provex following the standard procedure at recommended concentration and duration. Same quantity of seeds will be used for fumigation by phostoxin using fumigation sheet. The seeds will be preserved in the BADC store house, Bolashpur, Mymensingh. Random samples will be collected from each lot at 30 days interval for health, germination, moisture and viability tests. The incidence of seed borne pathogens of each sample will be determined by blotter and agar plate method. Germination and purity test will be done as per ISTA rules.', 'Lack of quality seeds is one of the factors responsible for low yield of rice. Healthy seeds must be sown to produce disease free seedlings. Rice seeds are being stored for more than six months. During storage the quality of rice seeds deteriorate because of attack of different storage fungi (Asperigillus niger) and insects (rice weevil, red flour beetle etc.). Their metabolic activities produce heat and increase moisture of seeds that can lead to growth of micro-flora. Heavily infested seeds are unit for sowing. Rice seeds are frequently fumigated to prevent insets and treated by fungicide to control pathogens on the stored seeds. Rice seeds are recommended to store at 12% moisture content. But high relative humidity during rainy season changes the moisture content, as result, the moisture content become higher than 12% even can goes up to 16%. At this stage the seed become vulnerable to invasion of stored pest. There is no update research on the effect of fumigation and treatment was done at different levels of moisture content of seeds and seed quality was assayed. Seed health and germination was tested after storage of the seeds for 4 months. Four hundred seeds were tested for each replication of the treatment. ISTA procedure for health and germination test was followed. The incidence of storage fungi was high on the seeds having moisture content higher than 12% during the storage period. The percentage of Aspergillus Niger was the highest at 18% moisture content of seeds. The lowest I incidence was found in 12% moisture content of seeds. High moisture content of seed was also favorable for the invasion of penicillium spp. The percentage of Penicillium spp was comparatively lower than that of Aspergillus spp. Fumigation at higher moisture content affected seed germination. The incidence of seed-borne fungi and invasion of storage fungi was low in the seeds treated with the fungicides even at high moisture content but the germination and seedling vigor was affected. The rate of reduction of germination was inversely proportional to the moisture content of seeds. Fumigation did not have any effect on the incidence of seed-borne and storage fungi. The incidence of seed-borne fungi and invasion of storage fungi was low in the seeds treated with the fungicides. Some of the fungicides know to be effective as foliar spray was also effective against the seed-bone and storage fungi. Invasion of storage fungi was low in the seeds treated with fungicide even at high moisture content of seeds; but be germination was affected.', 'Seed treatment, Fumigation, Moisture content', 'BAU-UGC', 120000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Quality seed production', 'Rice', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, Volume-22, 2011.  Proceedings of the workshop of BAU Research Progress, 02-03 April 2012.'),
