(2756, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Biochemistry', 'Project', 'Nutritional status of Raintree fruit and its utilization as feed for fish and poultry', 'Laboratory and Field, Department of Biochemistry, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2010', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2010', '1) Study the nutrient composition of pod meal of Albizia/Sumanea saman.\r\n2) Study the antinutritional factors available in this fruit.\r\n3) Evaluate the nutritive value of pod meal as protein and carbohydrate supplement in fish and poultry feed.', 'Following steps were followed in the methodology:\r\n1) Moisture determination\r\n2) Ash preparation\r\n3) Crude fat/oil determination\r\n4) Crude fibre\r\n5) Crude protein\r\n6) Non protein nitrogen\r\n7) Iodine Value\r\n8) Starch\r\n9) Calcium and Phosphorus\r\n10) Carotene\r\n11) Antinutritional factor\r\n12) Feeding trial\r\n13) Quality assessment', 'Production of animal protein in our country is quiet low. To raise protein production, intensive farming of fish and poultry is essential. This inspired our farmers to become increasingly interested in fish and poultry farming as a profitable agricultural practice. Presently, our farmers are dependent costly feed ingradients which are imported from abroad. At present, a lot of Raintree had been planted in our country and these are producing lot of fruits which has no use. T have observed that a medium sized plant can produce several maunds of fruit. These fruit may be an option to use as protein and carbohydrate as fish and poultry feeds.', 'Crude protein, Rain Tree, Crude Fibre, ', 'BAU-UGC', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Rarietal Improvement', 'Raintree fruit', '', '', ''),
