(2761, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Biochemistry', 'Project', 'Organoleptic atributes and biochemical evaluation of Jack fruit pulp as affected by cryopreservation', 'Laboratory, Green house, Horticulture farm etc., BAU', 'High', 'Applied', '', '01-05-2010', '30-04-2011', '01-05-2010', '30-04-2011', '1) To observe organoleptic attributes and biochemical changes of fruit juice/pulp in storage.\r\n2) To use this result in the food industries to facilitate long time preservation.\r\n3) To make the fruit available year round.', 'First of all, fruit juice will be extracted by blending the pulps. Next, the extract will be divided into four plastic bottles. Then the organoleptic attributes will be evaluated by a panel of educated, uneducated and highly educated people; and biochemical analysis will be carried out by the following methods. Moisture, dry matter, fibre, fat, starch, titrable acidity and ash contents will be determined by the methods described in the manual of Analysis of fruit and vegetables products by Ranganna. PH of the pulp will be determined by Fischer PH meter, TSS by using refractometer and protein content by Kjeldahl method.', 'Characteristically, Jackfruit is highly perishable and seasonal as well. Because of monsoon rainfall and poor transport facilities, marketing of this fruit throughout the country becomes very difficult. As a result, the growers fail to get a remunerative return of their produce and large portion of harvested fruit is sold at a throw away price. On the other hand, people from far area of growing place do not get the taste of this fruit. Therefore, finding out the way of storing this fruit is inevitable, which needs the assessment of quality and biochemical changes of both fresh and stored condition. If the excess fruits in the season are preserved by any means ensuring the quality, consumers would have the taste of this seasonal fruit all the year round. Jackfruit processing industries may generate opportunity to alleviate unemployment problems in Bangladesh. Again the processed fruits could be exported to earn foreign currency.', 'Jackfruit, Pulp, Organoleptic, fruit juice', 'BAU-UGC', 120000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Fruit preservation', 'Jackfruit', '', '', ''),
