(2767, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Crop Botany', 'Project', 'Development of somaclones through in vitro regenerated plantless for improved cultivar of Taro', 'Plant tissue culture lab and Field Lab, Department of Crop Botany, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', '', '01-07-2008', '30-06-2010', '01-07-2008', '30-06-2010', '1) Initiation, maintenance and plantlet regeneration from callus under drought stress to produce mass somaclones for selection.\r\n2) Selection of somaclones for suitable cultivar in terms of high yield under drought stress.\r\n3) To use of different plant growth regulators and Standardization for suitable somaclones.', 'Following experiments will be conducted in the methodology:\r\n1) Callus induction, proliferation and plantlets regeneration.\r\n2) Effect of medium on callus induction, proliferation and regeneration.\r\n3) Plants regeneration under induced in vitro stress conditions.\r\n4) Selection of somaclones and study their characters.\r\n5) Morpho-physiological evaluation of somaclones in field under stress conditions.', 'Taro is an important vegetable crop in Bangladesh, because it is harvested during rainy season when other vegetables supply in the market is scanty. Taro being propagated vegetatively by corms or cormlets, about 10% of the yield from previous cropping is used. Being vegetatively propagated and extremely heterogenous as a group, selection of high yielding and stress tolerant cultivar is very difficult and time consuming process in taro. Lack of new clone, low yield of existing cultivar, diseases infestation and changing environmental conditions have been threatening taro production in Bangladesh.\r\nThe technique of plant tissue culture is being routinely used for producing large number of clonal plants by in vitro culture of explants from wide range of species throughout the world. The proposed research is framed to regenerate somaclones through in vitro plant regeneration system for screening potential somaclones/cultivar suitable for high yielding or stress tolerant.', 'Somaclones, Taro, Callus', 'BAU-UGC', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Crop Production', 'Taro', '', '', ''),
