(2797, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Biology and Genetics', 'Project', 'Study of a new and revolutionary type of fish meal containing bamboo charcoal on fish growth and elimination of nitrogenous excretion in pangasiid catfish pond.', 'Department of fisheries Biology and Genetics, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '', '', '', '', '1.	To determine the effect of dietary BC on the growth and digestibility of P. hypophthalmus. \r\n2.	Comparison of growth of fish using two diets I(commercial feeds containing BC and handmade feed containing BC) for the minimization the production cost.\r\n3.	To determine the level of elimination of ammonia nitrogen excretion due to use of diet containing BC in the culture environment.\r\n', '', '', 'Fish, Production, ', 'BAU', 150000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Production', 'Fish', '', '', ''),
(2798, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Horticulture', 'Project', 'Collection, characterization and conservation of important vegetable and fruit plant genetic resources of Bangladesh.', 'CVFB farm and Laboratory, Department of Horticulture, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2009', '30-06-2011', '01-07-2009', '30-06-2011', '1) Collection of cultivars/landraces/wild relatives of different important vegetables viz. brinjal, cowpea, country bean, cucumber, okra, and five important fruits viz. mango, lime, lemon, pummelo, oranges and other citrus fruits from different parts of Bangladesh.\r\n2) Evaluation and characterization of the collected cultivars/landraces/wild relatives of the above mentioned vegetables and fruits for desired traits using morphological traits and molecular techniques.\r\n3) Conservation of the collected cultivars/landraces/wild relatives in Bangladesh Agricultural University system and in the national gene bank where possible.', 'Following activities were performed:\r\n1) Collection of landraces and wild relatives of different vegetables and fruits of Bangladesh.\r\n2) Morphological and molecular characterization of the collected PGRs\r\n3) PCR amplification\r\n4) Data analysis\r\n5) Diversity analysis\r\n6) Correlation and Path Coofiiicient analysis\r\n7) Conservation of the PGRs', 'Bangladesh is very rich in plant genetic resources (PGRs) of different vegetables and fruits due to her climatic conditions, cropping system and agricultural tradition. However, here erosion of PGRs (cultivars, landraces and wild relatives) of different vegetables and fruits is taking place rapidly due to introduction of modern and iniform varieties of crops, encroachment of natural land for crop cultivation and natural calamities like devastating floods and droughts. PGRs are the sources of genes for many desired traits and play a vital role for breeding new varities as well as in crop improvement work through modern biotechnology. Therefore, erosion of PGRs is a great loss for the mankind. So, for future food security, genetic diversity and use in crop improvement programme. PGRs (cultivars, landraces and wild relatives) of our indigenous vegetables and fruits like brinjal, cowpea, country bean, cucumber, okra, mango, lime, lemon, pummelo, oranges, and other citrus fruits are to be properly collected, evaluated, characterized and conserved.', '', 'BAURES', 240000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Plant conservation', 'Vegetables and fruits plant', '', '', ''),
