(2815, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Surgery and Obstetrics', 'Project', 'Somatic cell count and bacterial characterization as tools for diagnosis and identification of risk factors of bovine mastitis. ', 'Mymensingh, Serajgonj, Satkhira and Chittagong district.', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-08-2012', '31-07-2013', '01-08-2012', '31-07-2013', '1.	Adoption and standardization of techniques for somatic cell count (SCC).\r\n2.	Isolation and identification of bacterial species and colony count and relating that with SCC.\r\n3.	Identification of risk factors for mastitis.\r\n4.	Formulating of a mastitis control strategy by relating data on SCC and bacterial colony count (BCC) with identified risk factors\r\n', '', '', 'Diseases, Somatic, Cell Count, Mastitis Diagnosis', 'NATP-SPGR', 4696640, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Diseases Prevention and Congtrol', 'Livestock', '', '', ''),
