(2818, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of  Pathology', 'Project', 'Development of on Effective PPR vaccine seed from local isolate and its molecular characterization', 'BAU, Compound', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '05-01-2012', '31-12-2013', '05-01-2012', '31-12-2013', '1.	Development of PPR vaccine seed from local isolates.\r\n2.	Molecular genetic analysis of field and vaccine isolates.\r\n3.	Development of serologic and nucleic acid based diagnostic methods to determine the immune response of vaccine seed from the early diagnosis of PPR infections and their comparative efficacy.  \r\n', '', '', 'Vaccine seed, Livestock, Effective PPR Vaccine seed', 'NATP-SPGR', 12995000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Vaccin seed', 'Livestock', '', '', ''),
(2819, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Crop Botany', 'Project', 'Characterization and exploitation of biological nitrification inhibitors (BNI) in sorghum to control nitrification in agricultural systems.', 'Crop Botany Laboratory and farm, BAU and BINA central laboratory.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2009', '30-06-2011', '01-07-2009', '30-06-2011', '1) Evaluation of sorghum germplasms (from JIRCAS, Japan; ICRISAT, India and Bangladesh) on the release of MHPP\r\n2) Physiological studies on the mechanisms of MHPP release; mode of action of MHPP release from roots.\r\n3) To check the ability and stability of MHPP from sorghum in the soil environment.\r\n4) To determine the percentage of saving urea using MHPP.', 'Following steps were followed in the methodology:\r\n1) Screening of sorghum genotypes for BNI capacity\r\n2) Physiological study on MHPP release in sorghum\r\n3) Stability of BNI compound in soil', 'Nitrogen use efficiency (NUE) for global cereal production is approximately 33%. The unaccounted 67% represents a $US 16.7 billion annual loss, assuming fertilizer-soil equilibrium. Some of the major concerns of modern cereal production in the developing country like Bangladesh are the high level of N-pollution and low efficiency of N utilization. Nitrification of NH4+ to No3 results in the transformation of the relatively immobile NH4 to highly mobile no3, that can result in large N losses form denitrification and nitrate leaching. This result in environmental pollution and inefficient use of both soil N and applied N, as shown by the lower fertilizer-N recovery and N utilization during crop production. Suppression of nitrification and keeping N in the NH4 form can be a key strategy in extending N residence time in the soil, thus increasing N recovery and improving nitrogen use efficiency.', 'BNI, Sorghum, Nitrification, MHPP', 'BAURES', 240000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Low BNI genetic crop selection', 'Sorghum', '', '', ''),
(2820, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Farm Power and Machinery', 'Project', 'Improved potato Storage Facility for Farm Household.', 'Entire Bangladesh', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-01-2012', '31-12-2013', '01-01-2012', '31-12-2013', '1. To reduce storage loss of potato of household level.\r\n2. To develop and test an improved evaporative cooled potato store for farm household.\r\n3. To identify the optimum storage design structure using data analysis and modelling.\r\n', '', '', 'Potato, Imporve Potato storage, storage loss of potato', 'NATP-SPGR', 3836400, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Post Harvest technology', 'Potato', '', '', ''),
(2821, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Microbiology and Hygine', 'Project', 'Isolation and Molecular Characterization of egg drop syndrome (EDS76) virus in Bangladesh.', 'Throughout Bangladesh', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-07-2012', '30-06-2013', '01-07-2012', '30-06-2013', '1.	Sero Prevalence of EDS in chickens of commercial poultry farms. \r\n2.	To isolate and identify EDS-76 virus from the samples of seropositive flocks.\r\n3.	To characterize the isolate virus biologically and molecularly.\r\n', '', '', 'Egg, Drop syndrome virus, Livestock, Chickens', 'NATP-SPGR', 2481000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Egg drop syndrome virus', 'Livestock', '', '', ''),
(2822, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Soil Science', 'Project', 'Coordinated project on soil fertility and fertilizer management for crops and cropping patterns: BAU component.', 'AEZ- 1, 2, 3, 9, 11 &amp; 12', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2013', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2013', '1.	Delineation of the present status of Micro-nutrients in calcareous, Piedmont and Tista floodplain soils.\r\n2.	Evaluation of the effect of Micro-nutrient fertilization on the yield and quality of cereals and vegetable crops in these soils.\r\n3.	Evaluation of the methods of Micro-nutrient application of the yield and quality of cereals and vegetables crops at BAU farm (AEZ-8).\r\n', '', '', 'Soil, Water, Fertilizer management, Soil Fertility.', 'NATP-SPGR', 7234012, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Fertility and Fertilizer Management', 'Soil and Water', '', '', ''),
(2823, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Food Technology and Rural Industries', 'Project', 'Technology development of Soybean products processing to mitigate the malnutrition and improve livelihood of rural and urban poor.', 'Department of food technology and rural industries', 'High', 'Applied', '', '01-07-2009', '30-06-2010', '01-07-2009', '30-06-2010', '1) To develop soybean products processing technologies to produce value added soybean products of industrial importance.\r\n2) To assess the shelf life of soybean products at different storage conditions\r\n3) To assess the proximate composition and nutritive value of the processed soybean products.\r\n4) To assess the sensory attributes of soybean products.\r\n5) To organize practical training on soybean products processing for rural poor and other beneficiaries.', 'Different steps were followed which are given below:\r\n1) Processing of Soybean products\r\ni) Soymilk processing\r\nii) Cleaning and selection\r\niii) Washing and soaking\r\niv) Grinding\r\nv) Milk separation\r\nvi) Formulation\r\nvii) Sterilization\r\nviii) Packaging\r\n2) Tofu Processing\r\n3) Miscellaneous soyfood processing', 'Soybean has become a very important food crop because of its high content of quality protein, fat, vitamins and minerals. It is the richest source of vegetable proteins known to man. Soybean seeds contain 43.2% protein, 19.5% fat, 20.9% carbohydrate and a good amount of calcium, phosphorus, iron, and vitamins. Protein is essential for proper development and maintenance of the human body. The common people of Bangladesh can not afford to provide adequate animal protein in their daily diet because of the high cost of egg, milk, meat and fish. Soybean can play a vital role as a cheap supplement to pertinacious of food. It is also called as &quot;the miracle golden bean&quot; because its protein content is about 2 times of the other pulses, 4 times of wheat, 6 times of rice grain, 4 times of egg and 12 times of milk. Soybean has 3% lecithin, which is helpful for brain development. It is also rich in Ca, P and vitamins.', 'Soybean, Soymilk, Milk separation', 'MOSICT', 1281200, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Food processing and nutrition', 'Soybean', '', '', ''),
