(2843, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Genetics and plant breeding', 'Project', 'Screening of groundnut varieties for drought tolerance and high methionine content', 'Department of Genetics and Plant Breeding and Department of Biochemistry, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-02-2001', '31/01-2003', '01-02-2001', '31/01-2003', '1) Collection of groundnut germplasm from home and abroad.\r\n2) Screening of the groundnut and other legume seed for high methionine content.\r\n3) Screening of drought tolerant groundnut and other legume seeds by biochemical assessment. The parameters of biochemical assessment include abscisic acid and proline\r\n4) Field evaluation of the identified drought tolerant lines/varieties by IW/CPE method\r\n5) Performance test of the drought tolerant lines with the standard one\r\n6) Development of regeneration protocol from callus tissue, derived from the different explant of groundnut.', 'Biochemical Component\r\n(a) Material \r\n1) Groundnut varieties collection from BARI and ICRISAT\r\n(b) Design: RCBD\r\n(c) Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives.\r\nBreeding and bio-technology Component\r\na) Material collection\r\nb) Design of experiments: Split-plot\r\nc) Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives.', 'A large number of groundnut genotype could be screened by assessing their ability to synthesize proline as well as abscisic acid in the vegetative part of the plant where the plant would be grown in water deficit condition. Besides groundnut, other locally available legume genotype of different genus and species such as Lathyrus sativus would be subjected to this kind of screening procedure. Finally in considering the whole plant response in water deficit condition, the screened out plants will be grown in field in water deficit condition for final selection.\r\nGroundnut is one of the most important oil-crop of Bangladesh, cultivated mostly in the marginal land where no other crops can be grown more profitably. Very little attention is being paid by the different national research institutions for the development of oilseed crop like groundnut. Bangladesh Agricultural University, a seat of higher learning and research, may include this crop in its research program with specific objectives.', 'Groundnut, Screening, Oil seed crop, Proline', 'BAURES', 512800, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Growth Media', 'Groundnut', '', '', ''),
(2844, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Aquaculture', 'Project', 'Introducing BAU Aquaponics and sac bag  for fish and vegetable cultivation to climate change adaptation on south-western coastal region of Bangladesh.', 'Dacope upazila- Khulna district. ', 'High', 'Applied', 'On-going', '01-09-2012', '31-05-2013', '01-09-2012', '31-05-2013', '1.	BAU developed technologies will be transferred among the climate induced vulnerable communities in coastal region for fish and vegetable production.\r\n2.	To evaluate the adoption process and rate of adoption of the above technologies by the communities; and \r\n3.	Extension materials such as leaflet, poster, banner and videos will be developed for dissemination the technology to the wider audiences.  \r\n', '', '', '', 'Planning Commision of Bangladesh', 1200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Fish &amp; Vegetables', 'Climate Change', '', '', ''),
(2845, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Plant Pathology', 'Project', 'Biological control of seedling diseases of vegetables.', 'Department of Plant Pathology', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2002', '30-06-2005', '01-07-2002', '30-06-2005', '1) To determine the potentiality of Trichoderma in controlling seed borne pathogens of vegetables seedling\r\n2) To determine the potentiality of Trichoderma in controlling soil borne pathogens in the seed bed for growing vegetable seedlings.', '(a) Material collection\r\n(b) Laboratory study\r\n(c) Pot experiment\r\n(d) Evaluation of potentiality of Trichoderma on seedling diseases of vegetables in seed bed.', 'The findings of the proposed study on use of Trichoderma as a biocontrol agent for controlling seed borne pathogens and seedling diseases of vegetables may help in three dimentional ways: 1) It will provide a direction for controlling the seed borne pathogens and seedling diseases of vegetables without disturbing the natural microbes. 2) Its use will reduce the cost of using costly chemicals and soil environment will be intact. 3) Farmers will be benefited of getting higher seedling stand in seed bed will reduce the cost of cultivation. As a result, farmers will earn more money. It will help in the development of protocol for use of Trichoderma as biocontrol agent ', 'Biological control, seed borne pathogen, soil borne pathogen, Trichoderma', 'BAURES', 225000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Biological pest control', 'Vegetable seedlings', '', '', ''),
