(2882, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agronomy', 'Project', 'A study on the Performance of regenerative Rice crop as Affected by Agronomic Practices. ', 'Department of Agronomy, BAU, Mymensingh-2202', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-04-2002', '31-03-2004', '01-04-2002', '31-03-2004', '1.	To evaluate the ratoon ability of modern rice varieties (Hybrid and Inbred) through agronomic practices.\r\n2.	To see the effect of cutting height on ratoon production.\r\n3.	To evaluate the plant spacing of primary crop on the productivity of ratoon crop of rice.\r\n4.	To know the influences of fertilizer and water management practices on ratoon performances.\r\n5.	To find out a suitable harvesting time of primary crop for growing a ratoon crop with optimum productivity.\r\n6.	To assess the yield potential and economics of the ratoon crop in boro rice.\r\n', 'a.	Productivity assessment \r\nb.	Effect of variety on ratoon ability, \r\nc.	Clipping/culm cutting height \r\nd.	Fertilization, \r\ne.      Spacing/Plant population\r\nf.	Time of harvest. \r\nG.      Water management \r\n', 'Rice is the staple food on Bangladesh. It is a round the year crop and is grown in three different seasons namely aus, aman and boro. Still the country is not self-sufficient in rice production. Ratooning means the production of a second crop from the stubble through formation of new tillers and branches from at the base and nodes of the harvested plant of the previous crops with or without land tillage being done. In Bangladesh boro rice crop often is damaged by nor-westers and hail storm. This damage could be partially compensated by rationing. In ratoon rice crop, grain yield considerable vary from 3.3 t/ha at IRRI to 8.7 t/ha in Ethiopia. In Bangladesh study on rationing in rice is very limited and it has not yet attracted the attention of researchers, whereas in some advanced countries o the world like USa, China, Japan, India, Philippines, Dominican Republic tc. The ratooning of rice is being practiced to some extend and its advantage realized.', '', 'BAURES', 226800, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
