(2892, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Parasitology', 'Project', 'Epidemiology and pathology of amphithomiasis (Rumen fluke infestation) in cattle, sheep, goat and buffaloes in Bangladesh. ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1.	To undertake a though investigation on the prevalence of paramphistome/amphistome species affecting cattle, sheep, goats and buffaloes in Bangladesh.\r\n2.	To incriminate the most potential intermediate snail hosts of amphistome flukes in Bangladesh.\r\n3.	To assess the various factors governing the epidemiology of paramphistomiasis in Bangladesh. For example, host species involved; their age, sex, breed, nutritional status, etc; climate and the abundance of snail population in different topographic/zoogeographic region as in the country. \r\n4.	To determine the overall picture on the pathology of amphistomiasis in cattle, sheep, goats, and buffaloes in Bangladesh. With particular emphasis on amphistomiasis caused by the adult parasites, it any. \r\n', 'a. Materials; b. Design of experiments; c. Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives; d. ', 'Epidemiology is a field oriented investigation concerning distribution and determinants of a particular disease in a defined population. the pathogenesis of parasitic diseases is dependent upon the imbalance on the host parasite relationship and the reaction of one or both parties to that imbalance. Therefore, pathology is the changes in the tissues/organs or in the body systems. It is imperative to conduct a detailed investigation on the epidemiology and pathology of parampistomes/amphistome flukes in Bangladesh. This will ultimately help to assess the economic importance of the disease caused by the amphistome flukes in Bangladesh and device sustainable control strategies.', '', 'BAU', 408200, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
