(2897, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Physics', 'Project', 'Investigation on nucleation growth and characterization of pure urea (NH2CONH2), Thiourea (H2NCSNH2) and thiourea doped urea mixed single crystals and the feasibility study of mixed crystals to use as fertilizer.', 'Department of Physics, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2006', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2006', '1) To study the effect of PH on the formation of urea, thiourea and thiourea doped urea crystals and to characterize them.\r\n2) To know the softening nature and Vickers Micro-hardness of the crystals\r\n3) To examine the defects, behaviour and yielding information about the defect density and distribution of the crystals\r\n4) To use thiourea doped urea mixed crystals as fertilizer.', '1) Material: Urea, thiourea, double distilled water, acetone, petri-dish, glass apparatus, filter paper, photographic coloured film, silver paste etc.\r\n2) Design of experiment\r\n3) Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives.', 'Urea, thiourea and thiourea doped urea mixed single crystal can play vital role in industry and agriculture. Single crystals of thiourea and thiourea doped urea crystal are to be used as polarization filter, electric light shutter, optical volt meter etc. Since the volatility of urea is very high and shulphur is an essential nutrient element for young crops, therefore, the present investigation can fulfill our purpose. Because, successful formation and production of high quality thiourea doped urea mixed crystals can reduce the volatility of nitrogen and further it contains sulphur, an essential plant nutrient. In Bangladesh, Scientists are conducting researches in agricultural field with different forms of nitrogen. The effects of different forms of nitrogen on the yield contributing characters were found to be significant. It can also be expected that the application of thiourea doped urea mixed crystals in agricultural field can play vital role on the yield contributing characters of crop. ', 'Urea, Thiourea, Thiourea doped urea mixed crystals', 'BAURES', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Fertilizer Management', 'Urea and thiourea', '', '', ''),
(2898, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Soil Science', 'Project', 'Utilization of organic wastes through composting', 'Department of soil science', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '31-05-1999', '30-04-2001', '31-05-1999', '30-04-2001', '1) Selection of effective compost starter\r\n2) Identification of suitable composting time.\r\n3) Identification of suitable combination of organic wastes for composting\r\n4) Determination of nutritive value of different composted materials.', '1) Materials: Crop residues, Straw, Town wastes, Weeds, Water Hyacinth, Household refuses\r\n2) Method: Pit Method\r\n3) Location and site: Soil Science Field Laboratory, BAU, Mymensingh\r\n4) Compost starter\r\n5) Composting time\r\n6) Compost maturity test\r\n7) Experimental design\r\n8) Intercultural operation\r\n9) Chemical analysis', 'In Bangladesh, we have huge organic wastes which can easily be composted and effectively used in maintaining the fertility status of the soil. Identification of the best compost starter, shorter maturity period and proper combination of composting materials will definitely play vital role in increased use of composts for better yields.', 'Composting, Compost starter, composting time', 'BAURES', 452850, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Organic fertilizer management', 'Compost', '', '', ''),
(2899, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Management', 'Project', 'Effect of duckweed on production of fishes in mono and polyculture.', 'Department of Fisheries management, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-09-2004', '30-08-2006', '01-09-2004', '30-08-2006', '1) To evaluate the effects of duckweeds as supplementary feed on the survival and growth of some selected species of fishes in monoculture.\r\n2) To evaluate the effects of duckweed as supplementary feed on the survival and growth of some selected species of fishes in polyculture.\r\n3) To develop a polyculture system in which duckweed will be used as supplementary feed and that can be used by the poor fish farmers of Bangladesh.', '1) Development of technique of duckweed culture\r\n2) Monooculture of fish using duckweed as supplementary fish feed.\r\n3) Selection of spp. of fishes for polyculture of fishes using duckweed as supplementary fish feed.', 'Duckweed has been shown to be readily consumed by a variety of herbivorus fish such as grass carp, tilapia and rajputi. Although duckweed seems to hold great potential as a cheap fish feed, very few data are available on conditions that stimulate duckweed production and on feeding rates and growth of fish.\r\nThe high specific metabolic activity is also reflected in the extremely rapid reproduction rate of duckweed. Under ideal conditions of temperature, nutrient supply and sunlight, duckweed plants have been reported to double their biomass within 2 to 3 days. The soil, water and climatic conditions of Bangladesh are very favourable for commercial scale duckweed production.  ', 'Duckweed, herbivorus, grass carp', 'BARC', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Fish Culture', 'Mono and polyculture', '', '', ''),
(2900, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of food technology and rural industries', 'Project', 'Comparative studies on processing and quality parameters of semi-fermented foods', 'Department of food technology and rural industries, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-1997', '31-12-1998', '01-01-1997', '31-12-1998', '1) To develop process for preparation of pickles from fruits and vegetables\r\n2) To assess the effect of processing aid and preservatives on keeping quality of pickles.\r\n3) To observe the effect of spices and covering oil on quality and acceptability of pickles\r\n4) Taste panel evaluation of processed products\r\n5) To maximize the utilization of fruits and vegetables.\r\n6) To assess the shelf life of processed pickles.', 'Following procedures were taken in the methodology\r\n1) Materials collection\r\n2) Methods\r\n2.1) Olive pickles\r\n2.2) Green and ripe mango pickle\r\n2.3) Brinjal pickle\r\n2.4) Green Ginger pickle', '', '', 'BAURES', 191000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Food Processing', 'Semi-fermented foods', '', '', ''),
(2901, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Parasitology', 'Project', 'Studies on in vitro culture, isolation and visibility of free-living infective larvae of gastrointestinal nematodes of ruminants and their applications in screening pesticides. ', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-02-2000', '31-02-2001', '01-02-2000', '31-02-2001', '1.	To device a simple and effective culture method using parasite eggs for harvesting the free-living L3 of g/I nematodes of ruminants.\r\n2.	To determine the survibility of free-living L3 under different conditions.\r\n3.	To screen the toxic effects of a wide variety of pesticides on larval development to the L3 stage, their survibility and infectivity.\r\n4.	To know the impact of indiscriminating and repeated use of pesticides in the agricultural sector on the ecologic habitats of L3 of g/I nematodes if any.\r\n5.	To suggest better control measures against g/I nematodes of ruminants based on the present findings.\r\n', '1.	Collection of feces: Feces from helminth-infected young cattle/calves/goats will be obtained in fresh condition from the surrounding villages of BAU, and brought to the laboratory for culture. \r\n2.	Collection of adult parasites: Gravid females of g/I nematodes belonging to the genera Haemonchus, Mecistocirrus, Trichostronglhylus, Coperia, Oesophagostomum and Bunostomum will be collected from abomasum/intestine of cattle/goats obtained from the slaughter house.\r\n3.	Cultujre of L3: A known volume of fresh feces will be dissolved in tapwater to make it a semisolid suspension and mixed with charcoal and placed in a widemouth glass bottle. The culuture bottle will be maintained at different temperatujre in incubator and also at room temperature for the development of L3. \r\n4.	Isolation of L3 from culture media: Using modified Baermann method, suspended in saline for examining survival period and screening pesticides.\r\n5.	Screening of  pesticides:\r\n6.	Infectivity of larvae:\r\n', 'The production performances of livestock are considered very low in Bangladesh as compared with other neighboring countries. This is mostly because of widespread occurrence of harmful parasites (Rahman and Razzak, 1973; Qadir, 1981). Rahman (1997) reported that various helminth parasites may kill about 5% of ruminants in Bangladesh annually. Since, these parasites can cause severe anemia and diarrhea through sucking profuse blood and inducing gastroenteritis (Soulsby, 1982). So sufficient knowledge on the biology of free-living stages of these parasites may contribute to device an appropriate control measures, this research project is proposed.', '', 'BAU', 75000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2902, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Parasitology', 'Project', 'Control of Chicken Coccidiosis in Bangladesh.', 'Mymensingh Municipality Area', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '15-03-1998', '14-03-2000', '15-03-1998', '14-03-2000', '1.	To investigate the effect of immunizing chicks with stored oocysts for controlling coccidiosis in floor pen trials.\r\n2.	To compare this immunological method of control with chemo-prophylaxis.\r\n3.	To investigate the level of resistance against different isolates of E. tenella &amp; E. acervulina to be obtained from poultry farm in and around Mymensingh Municipal area. \r\n', '1.	Material: i. For the study of immunization of  chicks with stored oocysts, monospecific strains (Karim and Trees 1990) of all the seven pathogenic species of Eimeria will be used. Broiler chicks  from one-day-old will be used for this study.  \r\nIi. Ten field isolates each of E. tenella, the most pathogenic species and E. acervulina, the most common species, to be obtained from poultry farms in the around the Mymensingh Municipal area. \r\n2.	Design of Experiments: Design of experiments on control by immunization.\r\n', 'Coccidiosis in arguably the most important protozoa of animals and birds with a enormous effect on the poultry industry all over the world. Because of the widespread acceptance of potential value of poultry industry all over the world. The economic loss due to chicken coccidiosis in Bangaldesh is not exactly known. Effective control of chicken coccidiosis is therefore the demand of the time to boost the rapidly growing but vulnerable poultry industry in Bangladesh. ', 'Chicken, Poultry farm.', 'BAU', 379000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Poultry Production', 'Chickens', '', '', ''),
(2903, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of food technology and rural industries', 'Project', 'Processing and preservation of CASSAVA.', 'Department of Food Technology and Rural industries, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-10-1998', '30-09-2000', '01-10-1998', '30-09-2000', '1) Collection of fresh cassava roots from Madhupur growing area. Cleaning of cassava roots by washing in fresh water.\r\n2) Analysis of cassava for its moisture content, protein, fat, ash, starch and other constituents.\r\n3) Preparation of sun-dried and mechanically-dried cassava products such as chips, cubes and shreds.\r\n4) Preparation of flour from cassava from dried chips, cubes or shreds.\r\n5) Preparation of chips and french fries, jam, sauce and from fresh cassava\r\n6) To determine the level of cyanide content in various products developed as mentioned\r\n7) Isolation and purification of starch from raw cassava', '1) Materials: Cassava roots\r\n2) Cassava analysis\r\n3) Cassava processing\r\n4) Cassava flour preparation\r\n5) Different products preparation from cassava\r\n6) Sensory evaluations of the various products', 'Almost entire quantity of cassava produced in Bangladesh is consumed directly as supplementary staple food except a small quantity is being used for the manufacture of starch. Processing of this crop into storage-stable products is unknown to growers. Moreover, cassava being a highly perishable crop, a large proportion of it is wasted and spoiled due to lack of processing facilities in growing areas. Thus need for upgrading the use of cassava to more valuable purposes is thus warranted. Processing of cassava into various products by using appropriate technologies will enhance availability of the products throughout the years.\r\nNext to rice, the products based on wheat flour are important foodstuffs in Bangladesh. Since the production of wheat in Bangladesh is limited, supplies must be imported necessitating expenditure of foreign currency which is very scare.\r\nBangladesh imports about more than 2 million mt of wheat every year. Thus the research involving the use of non wheat flour such as cassava flour could save a good deal of foreign exchange by importing wheat every year. ', 'Cassava, Processing, preservation', 'BAURES', 212650, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Food Processing', 'CASSAVA', '', '', ''),
(2904, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Parasitology', 'Project', 'Studies and effects of Facioliasis in the organ liver of cattle and goat and its control. ', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University, Mymensingh.', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-10-1995', '30-09-1996', '01-10-1995', '30-09-1996', '1. To determine the parasitic load in the animal and in the live and determine meat quality.\r\n2. To collect the liver of highly infected animals due to facioliasis.\r\n3. To take the weight of the liver and grossly observe the organ.\r\n4. Pathological studies of liver.\r\n5. Threat the affected animal with anthelmenthis like Facinex and observe the liver and take the weight of liver and the animal\r\n', 'The Project Methodology are given bellow:\r\n1.	Written Materials (Published or Unpublished)\r\n2.	Field Study\r\n3.	Laboratory/Experimental work\r\n4.	Combination of a, b, c and d.\r\n', '1.	The main objective is to study the effects of Facioliasis in the Vital organ like liver and to control this disease to prevent loss of production in terms of meat and milk. \r\n2.	Given details of the work already done on this subject in this country elsewhere now.\r\n', '', 'BAU-UGC', 63000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2906, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Farm Power and Machinery', 'Project', 'Development and performance studies of solar pond for generating low heat suitable for hatching eggs in rural areas of Bangladesh', 'Department of Farm Power and Machinery, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-11-1998', '31-10-2000', '01-11-1998', '31-10-2000', '1) To construct model solar pond and incubator\r\n2) Charging the pond with salt water\r\n3) Performance test of the solar pond and incubator\r\n4) To determine the optimum size of the pond and incubator suitable for small holder farmers in the rural areas\r\n5) Economic analysis and compare the result with the existing egg hatching methods.\r\n6) Recommendation of the use of solar pond to the ministry of agriculture for its wide scale adoption in the rural areas.', 'Experimental solar pond will be constructed in the sunny area of the workshop of the Department of Farm Power and Machinery where sunshine can come throughout the day. If necessary, the efficiency of the pond will be enhanced  using mirrors. The bottom of the pond will be made black with suitable black substances.\r\nA solar meter will be installed near the pond to record the solar radiation.\r\n', 'In the developed countries the natural hatching has been replaced by electric incubators having automatic controls. Large numbers of egg can be hatched with these devices at a time. Though it is economic in the long run, but it requires costly instruments and skilled technicians for its operation. Besides, there is still no access to electricity for the majority of rural people of Bangladesh.\r\nIn this context, a new approach will be applied to the problem of developing a suitable solar powered incubator with the use of locally available materials in the proposed research project.', 'Solar pond, salt water, Egg hatching', 'BAURES', 669600, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Farm Machinery Development', 'Egg hatching machine', '', '', ''),
(2909, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Pharmacology', 'Project', 'Efficacy of indigenous medicinal plants and establishment of a medicinal plant garden and a herbarium', 'Department of Pharmacology, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-09-2002', '30-06-2009', '01-09-2002', '30-06-2009', '', '', '', '', 'BARC', 0, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Development of medicinal plants for effective drugs of animals', 'Herbal animal drugs', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `research_info` (`research_id`, `org_name`, `ddcr_name`, `ppe_type`, `r_title`, `r_location`, `r_priority`, `r_type`, `r_status`, `plan_sd`, `plan_ed`, `actual_sd`, `actual_ed`, `r_objective`, `r_method`, `r_abstruct`, `r_keywords`, `fund_source`, `total_budget`, `total_expenditure`, `total_refund`, `d_technology`, `p_organize`, `p_trained`, `r_programarea`, `commodity`, `outcome`, `impact`, `reference`) VALUES
(2910, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Microbiology and Hygiene', 'Project', 'Characterization of PPR-virus and production of tissue culture vaccine with its local isolate.', 'Department of Microbiology and Hygiene, BAU.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-03-1998', '14-03-2001', '01-03-1998', '14-03-2001', '1.	Isolation and identification of PPR-virus from the field outbreaks.\r\n2.	Characterization of PPR-Virus.\r\n3.	Selection of suitable strain and preparation of tissue culture vaccine.\r\n4.	Study on the comparative efficacy of the vaccine prepared from PPR-virus and the vaccine which is  being used for the prevention of PPR in goat of Bangladesh. \r\n', 'Isolation and identification of the virus: For this various samples (blood, nasal and oral discharges, mucous membrane of rectum, lymph node, lung tissue and spleen) from the infected and dead animals will be collected aseptically. Blood and other fluidy discharge will be used directly as inoculum after processing and adding of antibiotics, but for tissues it will be needed proper processing and adding of antibiotics, but for tissues it will be needed proper trituration and grinding with pestle and moter to get release of virus from the cells. A 20% suspension of the ground tissue will be made with phosphate buffer saline (PBS). Then the tissue suspension will be needed to centrifuge at 5000 r.p.m. for 30 minutes to settled sown the tissues debris and other coarse materials from the fluid. The virus particles containing supernatant fluid will be treated with antibiotics to make the fluid free from bacterial contamination. As inoculum the antibiotics treated supernatant could be used directly to the host or tissue culture system or could be preserved at 20&deg; for future use. After 48-72 hours of post infection of the cells with the virus the supernatant fluid of the cultured medium will be collecte3d as a source of virus for the identification and characterization of the PPR-virus.\r\nCharacterization of the virus: Antigenicity and pathogenicity of the isolated PPR-virus will be determined for their characterization. The antigenicity of one field isolate of PPR-virus will be compared with the other isolates or the viruses of other related strains of the same family using various serological tests, i.e. serum neutralization test (SNT), complement fixation test (CFT)l, immunodiffusion test (IDT), enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) and animal protection test (APT). \r\n', 'The peste-des-petits ruminants (PPR) is an emerging viral disease of goat in Bangladesh. It is a serious threat to the goat population of this country. Due to lack of proper and effective vaccine it become difficult to control the devastating viral disease. Tissue culture vaccine is now being used to protect and control effectively many viral diseases of man and animal. The aim of the present effort is to prepare such an effective vaccine with attenuated PPR-virus to save our total population. Keeping this in view the present research project is proposed. ', 'Goat, Animal, Hygiene, Production', 'BAU', 656950, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Production', 'Animals', '', '', ''),
(2911, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Genetics and plant breeding', 'Project', 'Breeding rice for yield and grain character (BRYGC)', 'Department of Genetics and plant breeding, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2002', '30-06-2004', '01-07-2002', '30-06-2004', '1) To evaluate germplasm for their yield and grain character\r\n2) To evaluate promising advanced generation lines for their yield and grain character\r\n3) To screen out the aromatic germplasm from the total lot as well the advanced generation lines including BAU 125.\r\n4) To collect, grow and evaluate germplasm for their grain character, aroma and yield and finally to include them in the crossing program\r\n5) To select desirable potential plants from the segregating generations', '1) Materials collection\r\n2) Design of experiments\r\n3) Procedure to be followed in achieving the stated objectives', 'Though by now we are self sufficient in food and we have a little surplus food grain as well. But we have sufficient demand for quality grain like Kalizira and Kataribhog if not for Bashmati. At the moment we have large number of high yielding varieties and only a few of them are fine and aromatic. We all know BAU is the only leading Agricultural University of the country which has a mandate for education and research. As such the present work was undertaken mainly:\r\n1) To categories aman rice germplasms including the advanced generation lines according their size and shape.\r\n2) To screen out the aromatic germplasm from the total lot as well the advanced generation lines including BAU 125\r\n3) All this will be done to develop slender long grain rice with good yield and aroma.', '', 'BAURES', 224975, 0, 0, 'Report', 'BAURES', 0, 'Plant breeding', 'Rice', '', '', ''),
(2912, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of agricultural statistics', 'Project', 'Estimation of gross and net technical efficiencies of wheat production in Bangladesh under two alternative functional forms', 'Department of Agricultural Statistics, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2003', '31-12-2003', '01-01-2003', '31-12-2003', '1) To estimate gross and net technical efficiencies of wheat farmers in Bangladesh\r\n2) To estimate returns to scale of wheat production\r\n3) To measure the productivity and profitability of wheat production\r\n4) To identify factors influencing technical efficiency of wheat production.\r\n5) To suggest some policies to increase productivity and technical efficiency of wheat. ', '1) Material', 'In Bangladesh, where resources are scarce and opportunities for new technologies are lacking, efficiency studies will be able to show that it is possible to raise productivity by improving efficiency without new investment or developing new technology. It is generally assumed that in Bangladesh farmers are inefficient at producing wheat and there are significant efficiency differences among regions, among farm groups and also among crops. After the measurement of efficiency differences, proper measures can be undertaken to reduce them. It is equally important to identify farm specific factors, which influence inefficiency effects or efficiency. However, the accuracy of the identification of the impact of different factors on the inefficiency effects or efficiencies depends on factors including the functional form of the production technology, the nature of the random error component the distribution of the inefficiency component and the nature of the production function. After the measurement of efficiencies on various dimensions, different components of agricultural policy can be adopted.', 'Wheat , Functional forms, ', 'BAURES', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Crop production', 'Wheat', '', '', ''),
(2913, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Surgery and Obstetrics', 'Project', 'Improvement of calf health through blood transfusion. ', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-10-1998', '30-09-2001', '01-10-1998', '30-09-2001', '1.	To study the therapeutic value of blood transfusion in anemic calves for the improvement of health. \r\n2.	To study the haemato-biochemical changes in the transfused calves.\r\nto investigate compatibility of cross matching in blood transfusion technique.\r\n3.	To record complications of blood transfusion in calves.\r\n4.	To record the influence of blood transfusion on body weight gain. \r\n', 'Following Methodology have been taken for this project: \r\n1.	Material: Twelve calves of 6 months to 1 year old will comprise the major material for the study. Blood samples collected from these animals will be subjected to various laboratory analyses.\r\n2.	Design of experiments: The data obtained will be analyzed by ANOVA and Studentst test. Blood samples (5 ml) at 0 hours and thereafter every day after transfusion for 10 days will be collected for various haemato-biochemical analyses.\r\n3.	Experimental animals: \r\n4.	Collection of bold for transfusion:\r\n5.	Transfusion in the recipient:\r\n6.	Haematology:\r\n7.	Biochemical parameter:\r\n8.	Nutritional  status:\r\n', 'Increased calf mortality is a constraint to cattle development (Anon, 1993). The mini dairy farms which developed so rapidly in the country over the recent years have been sharply declining due to this problem. The mortality has been reported to be 15-20% (Anon, 1993). Calf health, therefore, needs to be improved.  Blood transfusion in these animals might contribute significantly in promoting health status and thereby reduces mortality. This technique, therefore, needs to be evaluated in promoting calf health and in reducing calf mortality in Bangladesh.', '', 'BAU', 318350, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2914, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of cooperation and marketing', 'Project', 'Impact of poultry development programmes on poverty alleviation-A socio economic analysis', 'Department of cooperation and marketing, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2003', '30-06-2005', '01-07-2003', '30-06-2005', '1) To assess the impact of DLS and RD-12 (under BRDB) projects provided inputs like fund and training and other inputs on the economic and social development of elected participants of the study areas.\r\n2) To assess the BKB and RAKUB provided credit for the socioeconomic development through poultry raising by the participants in the selected areas. ', '1) Materials\r\n2) Design of experiments\r\n3) Procedures to be followed in achieving stated objectives\r\n4) Selection of the study area\r\n5) Selection of population\r\n6) Selection of sample\r\n7) Constructing data collection instruments\r\n8) Collection of data\r\n9) Computing and analyzing of data\r\n10) Selection of variable', 'Like other development programmes of many non-government organizations in Bangladesh poultry development programmes supported by DLS, BRDB, BKB and RAKUB have been contributing a lot to the poverty alleviation of the rural people of Bangladesh. Assessing the impact of these programs for sustainable development of the poor is important. The government of Bangladesh have been spending hundreds of millions of taka on this purpose. Our rural poor and land less constitute about half of our total population without whose development the country''s development can not be sustained. Our government supported poultry development programmes for this section of people are known to have imparted a significant impact in terms of increase in the income generation and employment and social benefits in various forms. ', 'Poultry Development Programme, Poverty alleviation, BRDB', 'BAURES', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Poultry Development Programme', 'Poverty alleviation', '', '', ''),
(2915, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Surgery and Obstetrics', 'Project', 'The effect of retention of afterbirth on subsequent fertility in cows.', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-1993', '30-06-1994', '01-07-1993', '30-06-1994', '1.	To identify the predisposing factors responsible for the occurrence of retention of placenta.\r\n2.	To study the incidence of retained placenta among different breeds of cow.\r\n3.	To study the effect of parity of the occurrence of retention of placenta.\r\n4.	To study the effect of seasons on retention of placenta.\r\n5.	To study the effect of the use of different therapeutic measures on subsequent fertility. \r\n', '1.	Materials and Methods: The proposed research project will be done in three phases within the stipulated 3 years periods.\r\n2.	Design of experiments.\r\n3.	Experimental animals.\r\n4.	Drug trial: \r\n5.	Data collection: Published reports, b. data collected from the fields, c. Results from Laboratory work, d. or combination of a, b and c. \r\n6.	Nutritional status.\r\n7.	Statistical analysis.\r\n\r\n3.	Data collection: Published reports, b. data collected from the fields, c. Results from Laboratory work, d. or combination of a, b and c. \r\n', 'Resumption of postpartum sexual cyclicity is very important in maintaining desirable calving interval of 12 month. Any abnormalities which occur following parturition especially retention of afterbirth interfere successful fertility of the concerned animals. Economic loss due to impaired reproductive function become considerable as the calving to calving interval exceeds 365 days (James and Esslemont, 1979). Manual removal of placenta is a common practice in Bangladesh which results uterine infection more frequently and extending the interval of calving to conception (Bolinder et al., 1988). However, there is no comprehensive evaluation of effects of retention of fetal membranes on fertility in cows has not yet been done in Bangladesh. ', 'Cow, Production, Animal', 'BAU-UGC', 32000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Production', 'Cows', '', '', ''),
(2916, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of  Pharmacology', 'Project', 'To study the efficacy of medicated blocks to attain sustainable control. ', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-08-1997', '31-07-2000', '01-08-1997', '31-07-2000', 'In Bangladesh, there is acute shortage of milk and every year huge amount of foreign currency is spent to import milk.  The imported milk is not even allows safe for human consumption. In recent years, there was great concern among Bangladeshs to establish dairy farms in private sector to fulfil the demand of milk. But in dairy industry there are several problems that are still facing the farmers among them major constraints are internal parasites and feed crisis. Farmers are not aware about sustainable parasite control. Trials with medicated blocks will be a preliminary approach in Bangladesh to attain sustainable parasite control and also give supplement to nutrition.', '1.	Material: dairy cattle, urea, molasses and anthelminatics animal feed, larvae of Haemonchus, laboratory, animals shed, vehicle etc.\r\n2.	Design of experiments: Selection of anthelmintics.\r\n3.	Preparation of medicated urea molassess blocks.\r\n4.	Anthelmintics will be added in 3 different concentration so there will be 3 formulations.\r\n', 'In Bangladesh most of the farmers are not aware of gastro-intestinal parasitic disease of cattle but the farmers to the veterinarians when their animals life are at risk. Anthelmintic therapy at this stage is worthless. In dairy farms, farmers are aware of the disease but field veterinarians are not always aware about choice of anthelmintic and also they have no idea about slow release delivery system, but the field veterinarians have increasing demand for parasite control during monsoon, when the parasite challenge is peak. Farmers and veterinarians are very much aware about decreased productivity due to parasites.', '', 'BAU', 408000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2917, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Cooperatives and Marketing', 'Project', 'Prospects of Bee keeping in Bangladesh', 'Department of Cooperatives and Marketing, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2005', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2005', '1) To determine the cost and return from beekeeping\r\n2) To determine the impact of beekeeping\r\n3) To examine the scope of beekeeping in Bangladesh\r\n4) To identify the problems of beekeeping and to make suggestions for the development of beekeeping in our country.  ', 'Beekeeping activities are done intensively in sadar Upazila of Bagerhat and Bhuapur Upazila of Tangail district. For this reason, this two areas are purposively selected for the study. The favorable season of honey productionis winter because of producing huge quantity of mustard crop in that time. Data will be collected from the month of October to March although honey is produced all over the year. Seventy beekeepers from Bagerhat and 30 beekeepers from Tangail will be selected. A draft schedule will be tested with some beekeepers of two areas. After making necessary adjustments, a final survey schedule will be prepared. Primary data will be collected witha set of interview schedules designed for this study. Secondary data will be collected from BBS. Data will be analyzed with a view to achieving the objectives of the study. Mainly tabular method will be followed in analysis. ', 'This study will determine the cost and return, impact and problems of beekeeping. If the problems can be identified and given solution properly then it will be helpful for the beekeepers as well as for the policy making organization. This study is expected to provide valuable information to the policy makers and concerned personnel involved in honey production and trade.', 'Bee keeping, ', 'BAURES', 74940, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Bee keeping in Bangladesh', 'Honey', '', '', ''),
(2918, 'Sher-e-Bangla Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Biology and Genetics', 'Project', 'Study of biodiversity of endangered species Puntius sarana and its genetic improvement. ', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2003', '31-12-2005', '01-01-2003', '31-12-2005', '1.	The study of genetic variability using allozyme marker is the only genetic technique to know the genotype.\r\n2.	To revive our endangered native fish species and to achieve the production.\r\n', '1.	Collection and compilation of scattered information on the endangered, vulnerable and rare fishes.\r\n2.	Systematic study among brood, F1 and F2 generation of sarpunti (P. sarana).\r\n3.	Growth comparison among brood, F1 and F2 generation sarpunti (P.sarana).\r\n4.	Study of heterozygosis of brood, F1 and F2 generation of sarpunti (P. sarana).\r\n5.	Study of inbreeding rate of brood, F1 and F2 generation of sarpunti (P. sarana).\r\n', 'Many research works re3ported that there anre many native fish species of Bangladesh such as Sarpunti, Meni, shol, Gajar, Koi, Taki, Pangas, Chital, Baim, Bele etc. which are going to be endangered  situation. In this situation, present work is proposed first, to find out what ecological factors are affecting their existence in nature and second to study them using genetic marker for the genetic improvement.', '', 'BAU', 225000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Genetic', 'Fishes', '', '', ''),
(2919, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agricultural Economics', 'Project', 'Socioeconomic impact of backward and forward linkages of power tiller adoption in some selected areas of Mymensingh district.', 'Department of Agricultural economics, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2005', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2005', '1) To identify the socioeconomic characteristics of PT owners, users, mechanics and drivers.\r\n2) To estimate the costs and returns of PT owners and users.\r\n3) To identify the activities of different actors in the operation of PT and determine backward and forward linkages\r\n4) To assess the policy implication on the basis of the research finding. ', 'The proposed study will be confined in some selected areas of Mymensingh district in Bangladesh due to the availability of data and convenience of the researcher. In order to satisfy the objectives of this study, number of PT owners, PT users, PT drivers, PT mechanics and PT repairing workshops were listed from the selected areas. The data will be collected from 30 PT owners, 30 users, 20 drivers, 10 mechanics and 10 workshops, which will be selected randomly from the listed samples. The investigator will collect the data following survey methods. Tabular, statistical and econometric analysis will be done to meet the objectives of the research.', 'The back of strong backward and forward linkage in agriculture is one of the most typical characteristics of underdeveloped country. This linkage can generate oppotunities for employment and incomes in the rural non-farm through effects on the demand for i) irrigation equipment and other modern inputs produced in the non-agricultural sectors. ii) Services for processing and marketing of additional agricultural surplus and iii) trade and transport services arising out of purchase of non-farm products induced by the growth of agricultural incomes. Due to the severe land constraints, growth in agriculture depends on technological progress and on supporting investment for facilitating the adoption of improved technologies. However, the capacity of the agricultural sector to absorb an increased labour force is very limited in most countries. Therefore, backward and forward linkage of power tiller technology is now generating employment opportunities, increasing incomes, adopting modern technology among the farmers and is making the market very comparative. It is the time to know the economics of PT technology, various dimensions of forward and backward linkages of PT and its impact on our rural economy. The proposed study will help the farmers of the rural areas, the planners and will help the extension workers to understand the importance of PT to increase the growth of agriculture and non-agriculture sectors.', 'PT, PT owners, PT users, Mechanics', 'BAURES', 75000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Farm Machinery use in the farm level', 'Power tiller', '', '', ''),
(2920, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of agricultural statistics', 'Project', 'Economic aspects, employment potential and consumption pattern of dairy milk production in selected areas of Mymensingh district.', 'Department of agricultural statistics, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-04-2001', '31-03-2004', '01-04-2001', '31-03-2004', '1) To estimate the milch cattle stocking rates and milk output and hence the efficiency of milk production\r\n2) To analyze the economic aspects of rairying and to draw a linkage between feed input and milk output.\r\n3) To estimate the employment potential and the extent of income generation in rural households through dairying.\r\n4) To determine the consumption pattern of milk and to examine the nature of problems encountered in marketing of dairy milk. ', '1) Materials collection\r\n2) Design of Experiments\r\n3) Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives', 'This study has a particular necessity in the present condition of dairy production in Bangladesh. Since no comprehensive study has been made so fat to evaluate the efficiency of milk production and employment potential of rearing dairy cattle, a formal research in this areas was found to be necessary. Moreover, the results of the feed input and labour employment may be useful for economically profitable dairy farming in Bangladesh. The findings of the study are expected to be useful to the subsidized dairy farm owners by providing valuable insight into the problems and potentials of dairying. It is believed that the proposed study would contribute significantly towards achieving the above objectives. The present study will be helpful to provide guidelines for recognition of dairying for the overall improvement of Bangladesh. ', 'Dairy milk, Milk production, rearing dairy cattle', 'BAURES', 224160, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Economic aspects of dairy rearing', 'Dairy Milk', '', '', ''),
