(2930, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Aquaculture', 'Project', 'Development of commercial low cost diets and optimization of culture practices for fresh water prawn', 'Department of Aquaculture, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-04-1998', '31-03-2000', '01-04-1998', '31-03-2000', '1) To formulate and prepare series of test diets to find out a cost effective pelleted diet for mono culture of M. rosenbergii through growth trial in earthen ponds.\r\n2) To develop a suitable supplemental feed mixes for polyculture of M. rosenbergii\r\n3) To find out a optimum stocking ratio of M. rosenbergii with Indian and Chinese carp in polyculture\r\n4) To study the feasibility of culturing M. rosenbergii in net cage\r\n5) Finally to recommend cost effective commercial diets and culture techniques for both mono and polyculture of M. rosenbergii.', 'The potential feed ingradients such as fish meal, shrimp meal, soybean meal, mustard oilcake, sesame oilcake, blood meal, silkworm pupae, rice bran, wheat bran etc. will be collected and analyzed for their proximate composition.\r\nSix different experimental diets will be formulated according to the nutritional requirement of M. rosenbergii using the above mentioned local feed ingradients. Post larvae of M. rosenbergii will be collected from govt. fish farm at Mashkanda, backyard hatchery of fresh water station, FRI, or Zalak fish farm at Gouripur, Mymensingh.\r\nSix experimental diets made for monoculture of M. rosenbergii will be evaluated through growth trial in 12 earthen miniponds.\r\nFeasibility of culturing M. rosenbergii in net cages will be tested in the Brahmaputra river near University campus during January-May since during this period there exists slight or no current in the river and also there is no turbidity in water. Twelve net cages of high density ploythene material of the proper mesh size will be constructed and used for the trial. Four different stocking densities will be tried with 3 repl