(2931, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of  Pathology', 'Project', 'Optimization of DNA vaccine delivery system using bacterial and viral vectors in order to formulate vaccines against gonadotrophin releasing hormone (GnRH-1).', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2010', '31-12-2010', '01-01-2010', '31-12-2010', '1.	Development of DNA vaccine against a reproductive hormone GnRH-1:\r\ni.	Bacterial and viral vector formulation in order to enhance immunogenicity of the vaccine.\r\nii.	Standardization of PCR technique towards detecting vaccine genome following transfection in host tissues.\r\niii.	Immunization of mice and rats in order to explore best antigen delivery response following vaccination.\r\niv.	Standardization of ELISA protocol to measure serum immune response following vaccination.\r\nv.	In vivo fertility assay of the vaccinated animals.\r\n2.	Enhance immunoefficacy in terms of dose, route, vectors, species and duration.\r\n', '', '', 'Animal, Biology, DNA vaccine, PCR', 'MOSICT', 300000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Biology', 'Animals', '', '', ''),
(2932, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Microbiology and hygiene', 'Project', 'Investigation on Avian salmonellosis and preparation of biologies from selected isolates.', 'Department of Microbiology and Hygiene, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-08-2000', '31-07-2003', '01-08-2000', '31-07-2003', '1) Isolation and identification of salmonella, specific and non-specific species from selected poultry farms and hatcheries.\r\n2) Selection of salmonella isolate to prepare antigen for rapid blood plate test\r\n3) Determination of immune competence of selected isolates for prophylactic use.', 'The samples will be collected from different selected poultry farms and different feed mills for the isolation and identification of salmonella\r\nThe sample will be inoculated into tubes containing 5 ml of tetnathionate broth and tubes containing 5ml of selenite broth and will be incubated for 24 hours at 37.5 c. One half-plate of each of the solid media will be steaked with one standard bacteriological loop of material from each tube of enrichment media. After 24 hours of incubation, one or two calories grossly resembling salmonella will be selected from each plate and inoculated into lactose carbohydrate broth.\r\nAfter isolation and identification of salmonella the organism will be grown in tubes of broth culture for 24 hours at 37.5 c. After that it will be heated for inactivation of the organisms at 60 c for 30 minutes. The tube will be centrifuged at 5000 rpm for 15 minutes. Inactivation of the organism will be confirmed by inoculation into culture media.', '', 'Salmonella, inoculation, Inactivation', 'BAURES', 507425, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Livestock disease', 'Avian salmonellosis', '', '', ''),
