(2934, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Microbiology and Hygiene', 'Project', 'Isolation and characterization of salmonella serovars from meat of livestock and poultry origin and development of their remedial measures.', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2010', '31-12-2010', '01-01-2010', '31-12-2010', '1.	To isolate and identify Salmonella serovars from the market meats of cattle, goat sheep, buffaloes and poultry using cultural, morphological and biochemical examinations.\r\n2.	To study the Serological characteristics of the isolated Salmonella serovars.\r\n3.	To characterize the isolated Salmonella serovars using Molecular techniques (PCR and PFGE).\r\n4.	To analyze the plasmid profile of the isolated Salmonella serovars.\r\n5.	To study the zoonotic aspect of Salmonella servovars.\r\n6.	To evaluate the efficacy of various types of antibacterial substance on the isolated Salmonella serovars in order to develop remedial measures.\r\n', '', '', '', 'MOSICT', 300000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Diseases', 'Livestock and Poultry', '', '', ''),
