(2978, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Management', 'Project', 'Comparative studies on the feeding responses to various food concentrations of filter-feeding zooplankton.', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-04-1998', '31-03-1999', '01-04-1998', '31-03-1999', '1.	To determine optimal and potential food items for zooplankton culture.\r\n2.	To find out critical food concentration &amp; optimum food concentration for culturing of zooplanktons.\r\n3.	To find out the relationship between dissolved oxygen and pH with filtration rate.\r\n4.	To make a study between ingestion rate in response to various food concentrations of zooplanktons.\r\n5.	To enhance our understanding the knowledge of biological production in the natural aquatic ecosystem to support our life by supplying food and also to protect a comfortable environment for our life.\r\n', '', '', '', 'BARC', 513000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2979, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Animal Nutrition', 'Project', 'Evaluation of cattle trace mineral status and effect of mineral supplementation in indigenous cattle', 'Department of Animal Nutrition', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2006', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2006', '1) To determine the trace mineral contents of soil, feed, liver, blood, rib bone etc.\r\n2) To evaluate the trace mineral status of cattle in Mymensingh district\r\n3) To improve the mineral status of growing cattle by supplementation.', 'a) Methods of sample collection\r\nb) Collection of samples\r\nc) Methods of Laboratory analysis\r\nd) Statistical analysis\r\nExpt. 1) Effect of levels of feeding copper (Cu) supplements on the copper status and performance of growing bull\r\nExpt. 2: Effect of levels of feeding Zinc (Zn) supplements on the zinc status and performance of growing bull\r\nExpt. 3: This experiment will be conducted on the basis of results obtained from expt. 1 to 2 and same parameters mentioned in Expt. 1 to 2 will be studied for final recommendations.\r\nParameters will be studied:\r\ni) Growth performance\r\nii) Balance\r\niii) Plasma\r\n', '', 'Cattle, Mineral status, rib bone, supplementation', 'BAURES', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Livestock production', 'Mineral supplementation to cattle', '', '', ''),
(2980, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Management', 'Project', 'Effects of duckweed on production of fishes in mono and polyculture', 'Dept. of Fisheries Management, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '011-09-2004', '31-08-2006', '011-09-2004', '31-08-2006', '1.	To evaluate the effects of duckweed as supplementary feed on the survival and growth of some selected species of fishes in monoculture.\r\n2.	To evaluate the effects of duckweed as supplementary feed on the survival and growth of some selected species of fishes in polyculture.\r\n3.	To develop a polyculture system in which duckweed will be used as supplementary feed and that can be used by the poor fish farmers of Bangladesh.\r\n', 'The main Methodology of the research Project have been given below:\r\na.	Material:\r\nb.	Design of Experiments:\r\nc.	Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives:\r\nd.	Data collection\r\ne.	Data analysis: Free C)2 will be determined by titrimetric method, pH will be determined by a digital pH-meter, Dissolved oxygen will be determined by a D.O. meter, Water depth will be determined with a wooden depth meter, Water and air temperature will be recorded by a Celsius thermometer, Water transparency will be determined by a Secchi disc. \r\n', '', '', 'BAU', 150000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Production', 'Fish', '', '', ''),
(2981, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Biology and Limnology', 'Project', 'Effects of periphyton on fish culture', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-1996', '31-12-1996', '01-01-1996', '31-12-1996', '1.	Different artificial substrates, such as bamboo poles, low-cost wooden splits, low-cost tree branches, and low cost bamboo branches will be used to find out which ones is/are suitable and economical.\r\n2.	To find out the spp. Of fishes which will prefer periphyton as for in monoculture and also in polyculture systems. \r\n3.	To determine the periphyton qualitatively and quantitatively grown on different artificial substrates.\r\n4.	To observe the feeding behabour of the spp. of fish on the periphyton grown on artificial substrates.\r\n5.	To investigate into other benefits and problems of this new system of fish culture. \r\n', 'The main Methodology of the research Project have been given below: \r\na.	Material:\r\nb.	Design of Experiments:\r\nc.	Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives:\r\nd.	Data collection\r\ne.	Data analysis\r\n', '', '', 'BAU', 150000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(2982, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Animal Breeding and Genetics', 'Project', 'Preservation of Buck semen and their use in artificial insemination for rapid genetic improvement of rural goats population', 'Department of Animal Breeding and Genetics', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2006', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2006', '1) Collection of superior bucks selected phenotypically with their body weight and daily gain.\r\n2) Evaluation of diluted semen for maintaining their keeping quality and optimum fertility\r\n3) Study the conception rate with AI in does around the BAU campus and familiarize AI in goats to the rural farmers for the genetic improvement of goat population.\r\n4) Selection of superior bucks produced out of the AI services and distributed them to the rural farmers for their economic gain. ', '1) Material and procedure\r\nThe combination of EYC would be as follows:\r\nEgg yolk = 25 ml\r\nSodium citrate buffer (2.94%) = 50 ml\r\nPenicillin = 1000iu/ml\r\nDihydro streptomycin = 1000 mg/ml\r\nSulphanelamide = 0.6gm/100ml\r\n\r\nParameter for raw semen:\r\n- Volume\r\n- Colour\r\n- Motility\r\n- Concentration\r\n- Morphological tests\r\nParameter for diluted semen:\r\n- Motility (%)\r\n- Live spermatozoa (%)\r\n- Normal Spermatozoa (%)\r\nParameter for AI work:\r\n- Conception rate of 1st, 2nd and 3rd day service with preserved semen\r\n- Number of service per conception\r\n- Gestation length', '', 'Buck, semen, rural goats, optimum fertility, phenotypically', 'BAURES', 369400, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Genetic improvement of livestock', 'Rural goats', '', '', ''),
(2983, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Aquaculture', 'Project', 'Improvement in the nursery rearing and production phase of freshwater prawn, Macrobrachium rosenbergii through the use of artificial substrates', 'Wet laboratory of dept. of Aquaculture and experimental ponds belongs to PI.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2006', '30-06-2008', '01-07-2006', '30-06-2008', '1.	To investigate the effects different artificial substrates on the growth and survival of M. Rosenbergii PLs in recirculating system.\r\n2.	To evaluate the effects of different artificial substrates in improving the growth and survival of M. Rosenbergii PLs in nursery ponds.\r\n3.	To observe the effects of different artificial substrates on the growth, yield, survival and economics of production of M. Rosenbergii in grow-out ponds.\r\n', 'The main Methodology of the research Project have been given below: \r\na.	Material:\r\nb.	Design of Experiments:\r\nc.	Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives:\r\nd.	Data collection\r\ne.	Data analysis: ', '', '', 'BAU', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', 'Fish', '', '', ''),
(2984, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agricultural Statistics', 'Project', 'A study on constraints of native cattle genetic resource conservation with particular reference to profitability assessment', 'Department of Agricultural Statistics, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2006', '31-12-2007', '01-07-2006', '31-12-2007', '1) To find out the socioeconomic conditions of the cattle owners and its impact on cattle production\r\n2) To identify the causes of reduction in the number of native cattle\r\n3) To determine the different factors that contribute the milk yield both for native and crossbreed cows.\r\n4) To find out net profit from market price for the native and crossbreed cows\r\n5) To build up strategies for cattle genetic resource conservation', 'A two stage probability sample design will be used. The rationale behind selecting two stage stratified cluster sample with its principle of simplicity, low cost and case of operation. Each of the selected farm households will be interviewed twice at random through redesigned questionnaire. Five study sites will be selected purposively from all over the country. They will be i) Coastal region ii) Hill sites iii) Nothern region iv) Mid region of the country and v) Industrial zone having high employment opportunity. Finally 400 livestock farm households will be selected from five thanas of different categories.\r\nThe filled-in questionnaire will be checked to search for errors such as legibility, range, skip and consistency. The checked data will be coded and tabulated by the data collector. The tabulated data will be employed to edit in computer. Researchers will verify the questionnaire, tabulation and edits. If any inconsistency of the data observed, it will be corrected even the households will be interviewed further. The computerized data will be tabulated on the computer and computation of appropriate results will be undertaken according to the objectives of the research. After that, final analysis will be done and final report will be made along with policy implications and recommendations.', '', 'Native cattle, conservation, Crossbreed cows', 'BAURES', 112500, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Livestock resource conservation', 'Cattle', '', '', ''),
(2985, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of agricultural economics', 'Project', 'Contribution of household goat farming to sustaining rural livelihoods in Bangladesh', 'Department of agricultural economics, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2006', '01-09-2004', '31-08-2006', '1) To identify the major socioeconomic characteristic of the goat keepers\r\n2) To assess the viability of investment in small scale goat farming\r\n3) To estimate the contribution of small scale goat farming on the household income and generating employment, women in particular; and\r\n4) To identify major problems associated with small scale goat farming.', '150 samples will be purposively selected from three districts (Mymensingh, Tangail and Kishorganj) for the study. No household farms having less than 2 adult female goats will be considered for the study. The viability of goat keeping has been expressed through several common units such as: a) per farm having 2 female goats; b) per farm having 4 female goats c) per farm having 6 goats. A set of questionnaire for the selected goat keepers will be prepared before conducting the field survey for collecting data. Primary data will be collected from the household head of goat farmers. The collected data will be coded, summarized and processed for the analysis. Processed data will be inserted in computer using the concerned software.\r\nThe method of project appraisal suggested by Gittinger (1994) will be followed. To determine the financial profitability of a goat farm, the cost and benefit streams over the life of the project must be discounted at the appropriate discount rate. By discounting, future cash flows can be reduced to their present worth. Three principal measures such as BCR, NPV and IRR will be employed to measure the viability of the selected goat farmers.', '', 'Goat farming, goat keepers, income, Mymensingh, Tangail', 'BAURES', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Livelihoods improvement through livestock farming', 'Goat', '', '', ''),
(2986, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of agricultural economics', 'Project', 'Poverty Reduction through women employment in farms and rice parboiling mills in some areas of Dinajpur district', 'Department of agricultural economics, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2006', '30-06-2007', '01-07-2006', '30-06-2007', '1) To examine the socio-economic profiles of women participated in farms and rice parboiling mills activities;\r\n2) To examine contribution of women to household income which reducing their poverty; \r\n3) To identify the factors influencing the level of family income in farms and rice parboiling mills workers\r\n4) To identify the problems and constraints of farms and rice parboiling mills. ', 'The area in which a farm business survey is to be carried out depends on the particular purpose of the survey and the possible co-operation from the farmers. To achieve the objectives of the present study a preliminary survey will be conducted in sadar Upazila of Dinajpur district to understand the broad socioeconomic characteristics of the area. On the basis of preliminary information, reasonable sample of farm and rice parboiling mills under sadar Upazila of Dinajpur district will be selected finally for the study area. It is always convenient to choose the sampling technique at the palnning stage of the farm household survey. Considering the objectives, time, availability of fund, manpower and availability of mill proprietors, mill women labourer and farm women labourer mentioned above will be selected randomly. The sample frame will be prepared by classifying the households according to their farm and rice parboiling mill activities. Sixty mill women labourer, 60 farm women labourer will be selected randomly from a list of total number.', '', '', 'BAU-UGC', 70000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Women employment', 'Rice parboiling mills', '', '', ''),
