(2993, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Cooperation and Marketing', 'Project', 'Sericulture industry in Bangladesh: Impact on poverty Alleviation', 'Department of Cooperation and Marketing, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-09-2004', '30-08-2006', '01-09-2004', '30-08-2006', '1) To estimate the cost, return and profitability at different stages of sericulture.\r\n2) To measure the impact of sericulture programme on employment and income at different stages.\r\n3) To examine the marketing system of silk and silk product\r\n4) To identify the problems at different stages and thereby suggests measures to solve these problems.', 'Sericulture requires several levels of activities. Major activities are: a) nursery b) mulberry plantation c) rearing of silkworm d) reeling and e) weaving. Among these activities rearing of silkworm activity is more important and success of all activities largely depends on this activity. The present study mainly investigates the rearing, reeling and weaving activities. For this study, 5 different areas such as Rajshahi, Natore, Sirajganj, Bogra and Jessore will be selected and from each area 30 rearers will be chosen randomly. Among 30 rearers, 15 from Bangladesh Sericulture Board and 15 from BRAC will be selected. Besides, 30 workers from reeling centre and 30 weavers both from BSB and BRAC will be selected randomly. That means total 210 participants will be interviewed with pre designed questionnaires  for this study. For each group of respondent separate questionnaire will be prepared. Detailed information concerning income, employment, saving, education, housing, sanitation etc. of the respondents before and after involvement in sericulture programme will be gathered in order to examine the impact of the program on different aspects of the participants in the study areas. ', '', 'Sericulture, BSB, BRAC, reeling', 'BAURES', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Seliculture Development', 'Poverty alleviation', '', '', 