(2999, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Animal Nutrition', 'Project', 'Development of feeding system for indigenous growing cattle using non conventional feedstuffs', 'Animal nutrition field laboratory and analytical laboratories, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-10-2005', '30-09-2007', '01-10-2005', '30-09-2007', '1) To determine the nutritive value of unconventional and by-product animal feed stuffs in terms of their chemical composition, digestable organic matter and energy values.\r\n2) To formulate rations based on unconventional feed stuffs for local growing cattle and their evaluation using in vitro techniques.\r\n3) To establish a standard feeding system for our indigenous growing cattle.', '1) Material: feedstuffs, in vitro digestion set, cannulated animal, metabolic crates and growing cattle\r\n2) Feed resources: Agricultural by products, aquatic plants, tree leaves and seed of forest plants.\r\n3) Design of experiments: Randomized Block Design\r\n4) Analysis of experimental data: Using statistical packages', '', 'Feedstuffs, ', 'BAURES', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Animal farming', 'Conventional feedstuffs', '', '', ''),
