(3014, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Farm Power and Machinery', 'Project', 'Demonstration and Transfer of BAU seed fertilizer Distributor Technology', 'Department of Farm Power and Machinery, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2002', '30-06-2003', '01-07-2002', '30-06-2003', '1) To construct ten units of BAU seed-fertilizer distributor\r\n2) To demonstrate the devices among potential users, manufacturers and traders in Mymensingh, Jamalpur, Kishorganj, Netrokona, Sherpur, Tangail and Gazipur districts\r\n3) To take necessary initiative to transfer of technology to interested manufacturers and traders.', '1) Ten BAU seed-fertilizer distributors will be fabricated in the Department of farm power and machinery following the same design of the device developed by Ziauddin (2000).\r\n2) The Devices will be demonstrated among farmers in 21 villages in greater Mymensingh, Jamalpur, Kishorganj, Netrokona, Sherpur, Tangail and Gazipur districts.\r\n3) The devices will be demonstrated among 7 manufacturers and 7 traders in the 7 districts.\r\n4) Five thousands extension materials (Leaflet) will be prepared and distributed to concern people, DAE, NGOs throughout Bangladesh.\r\n5) Take necessary initiative to transfer the technology to interested manufacturers and traders.\r\n6) Preparation of final report for the sponsor.', '', 'Seed-fertilizer distributor, Manufacturer, Traders, sponsor', 'BAURES', 75000, 0, 0, 'Report', 'Field days', 0, 'Farm Mechanization', 'Seed and Fertilizer Distributor', '', '', ''),
(3015, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Farm Structure', 'Project', 'Conservation of traditional storage structures by improving the existing structures in rural areas of Mymensingh district.', 'Department of Farm Structure, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-11-2002', '31-10-2003', '01-11-2002', '31-10-2003', '1) Survey of the traditional storage structures\r\n2) Quantify the factors affecting the structures\r\n3) Development of existing traditional structures for safe storage', '1) Material: Woven bamboo splits container, soil, cement, ash, cow-dung etc.\r\n2) Design of experiments: Woven bamboo splits storage structures is of circular shaped with 100 cm dia, capable of storing 375 kg will be constructed in the laboratory and it will be improved by using soil-cement, soil-ash and soil-cowdung mixture.\r\n3) Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives: A questionnaire will be given to the farmers to know the type, merits and demerits of traditional storage structures and some suggestions will be collected from the farmers to satisfy their storing requirements.\r\nSurvey works on traditional storage structures will be completed within two months in more than two selected thanas of Mymensingh district.\r\nThe main experimental works will be started from the 4th month and will be continued till 10th month of the project life. Preparation of report will start from the month to the end of the planned project life of one year.', '', 'Storage structure, Rice, Traditional storage', '', 75000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Development of Storage Structure', 'Rice', '', '', ''),
