(3043, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Irrigation and water management', 'Project', 'Level basin design for rice based irrigation system', 'Department of Irrigation and water management, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2000', '30-06-2003', '01-07-2000', '30-06-2003', '1) Determination of irrigation stream sizes for different sizes of land holdings depending on soil types, topography, basin, flow hydraulics and crop stages.\r\n2) Obtaining of relationship between basin/holding sizes and water distribution efficiencies for a number of stream sizes and soil intake characteristics.\r\n3) Developing design charts and tables for different intake families, plot and stream sizes so that irrigation planners and users can use these tables and charts for designing a basin water distribution system efficiently.\r\n4) To make a comparative study of rice yields grown under different water levels with a view to assess the potentiality of rice cultivation without allowing standing water and deep percolation losses in order to control ground water pollution and mosquitoes hazards.\r\n5) Determination of economic level of water requirement at different crop growth stages to cultivate irrigated rice profitably.\r\n6) To work out the water losses belo the root zone under different irrigation regimes for the determination of storage efficiency.', 'Different stages are the following:\r\n1) Safe water requirement\r\n2) Rice basin design\r\n3) Lateral spread of irrigation water in the basin\r\n4) Water front advance in the basin\r\n5) Intake characteristics of basin soils\r\n6) Percolation losses and application efficiency', '', 'Irrigation, Level Basin Design, Percolation, Basin soils', 'BAURES', 225000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Irrigation management', 'Rice', '', '', ''),
