(3047, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Animal Science', 'Project', 'Quantification of locally available feed resources and feeding systems of animal in different regions of Bangladesh', 'Department of animal science', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '24-01-1998', '23-12-2000', '24-01-1998', '23-12-2000', '1) To provide an updated information on the sources and availability of feed resources.\r\n2) To quantify the available feed resources in different areas in Bangladesh\r\n3) To study the seasonal variation on the availability of feed resources.\r\n4) To provide an updated information on the sources on the feeding system in different seasons.\r\n5) To collect a detailed information of what is available, where and when and their current prices.\r\n6) To collect information on the growing pattern and utilization of different types shrubs and tree fodder in the homestead.\r\n7) Acceptability of different feeds and fodder available in the village\r\n8) To assess the quantify of res.\r\n9) To suggest the ways and means to overcome the scarcity of animal feed/feeds if prevailed in a specific region.', 'Feed resources available within the farms, village, country or region will be classified on both seasonal and geographical basis, including recording the types and species of feeds and fodder, prices, pattern of growing and utilization in individual farms concerning size and production system. It is expected to do a preliminary nutritive assessment of the most common feed resources present in the area to evaluate the potential for increasing their supply or utilization. The data will be collected from following sources:\r\na) Through a survey questionnaire to be prepared in due time\r\nb) Available Government Statistics\r\nReports from different research institutes/organizations\r\nVisiting field level and scientific worker\r\nc) Chemical analysis: dry matter, crude protein, crude fibre, ash, fat and degradability in the rumen through chemical analysis.