(3052, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Irrigation and water management', 'Project', 'Judicious irrigation for increasing water productivity of rice and improvement of minor irrigation project performance', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Farm and adjoining farmer''s field', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2006', '30-06-2008', '01-07-2006', '30-06-2008', '1) To increase the water productivity of rice at BAU farm and adjoining farmers fields.\r\n2) To improve the performance of minor irrigation projects\r\n3) To analyze the GW level fluctuation trend at BAU.', 'Experiments will be conducted both at BAU farm and adjoining farmers fields on the basis of BRRI recommended irrigated rice production technologies.\r\nWater users association will be formed through motivation and PIM approach, which will help develop water saving techniques, reduced land use and labour required for on-farm water distribution.\r\nEvaluation of performance of the selected DTW and STW schemes will be carried out using a standard set of performance indicators namely, Delivery performance ratio (DPR), Water delivery performance (WDP), Conveyance loss ratio (CLR), Relative water supply (RWS), Overall reliability (OR), Irrigation area ratio (IAR), Yield ratio (YR), Production ratio (PR), and Sustainability of irrigated area (SIA).\r\nField data will be collected through direct measurements and questionnaire surveys. Secondary data on GW level fluctuation available in the department of IWM and BINA will be analyzed to prepare guidelines for using suction mode or force mode pumps for GW abstraction.', '', 'Judicious irrigation, Water productivity, Minor irrigation project', 'BAURES', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Irrigation and water management', 'Rice', '', '', ''),
