(3057, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Parasitology', 'Project', 'Pathological and parasitological investigation of an emerging tracheal fluke infection in ducks.', 'Laboratories of the department of Pathology and department of Parasitology, BAU, Mymensingh, Kamlakanda and Barhatta upazillas of Netrokona  district of Bangladesh', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2005', '30-06-2006', '01-07-2005', '30-06-2006', 'Pathology and parasitology of tracheal fluke of ducks will be studied. ', 'Kamalkanda and Barhatta upazillas of Netrokona disgtrict are duck rearing areas, which are selected to conduct the study. Twenthy duck keepers will be selected from these two upazillas to record their problems and other information in duck rearing. side by side, to study the duck mortality pattern, the sick and dead ducks collected from the areas will be subjected to through necropsy to find out the causes of illness and to observe the presence of tracheal flukes if any. the fluke will be collected and preserved in 10% formalin. ', '', '', 'BAURES', 75000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Medicine', 'Birds', '', '', ''),
(3058, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of agricultural economics', 'Project', 'Impact of Homestead Agro-forestry on Livelihood of rural poor in Mymensingh District.', 'Mymensingh sadar, Muktagacha, Trishal and Gouripur', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2008', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2008', '1) Development of eco-friendly homestead agro-forestry\r\n2) Conservation of homestead biodiversity\r\n3) Restoration of endangered species\r\n4) Mass awareness development for biodiversity conservation\r\n5) Improvement of livelihood of the poor people through income generation activities (IGA).\r\n6) Enrichment of the agro-ecosystem of the research areas.', 'Four Upazilas of Mymensingh district will be selected for the study. Two villages from each Upazila will be selected for the study. One interview schedule will be developed and pre-tested for necessary modification before starting final survey. The schedule will be used for collection of data related to socio-economic aspects covering income, gender issues, farmer''s attitude towards homestead agro-forestry etc. Qualitative data will be processed, analyzed using SPSS. ', '', 'Homestead agroforestry, Rural poor, ', 'BAURES', 99500, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Livelihood improvement of rural poor', 'Homestead Agro-forestry', '', '', ''),
