(3068, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Aquaculture', 'Project', 'Argulosis in farm fishes of Mymensingh area', 'Mymensingh area', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', 'a. Study the taxonomic characters with systematic importance and identification of Argulus. \r\nb. Histopathological study of diseased fish caused by Argulus.', 'For the study collection of samples of both fish louse and fish will be made by several field visits to different parts of Mymensingh district. The investigation will be conducted from two years during 2007  2008 information will be noted. The speciments will be preserved in alcohol/formalin or F. A. A. The fish sample or tissue will be collected from live fish and will be preserved in 10% buffer formalin for histological purpose. Histopathological works will be done after fixation in neutral buffered formalin processing of automatic tissue processor, cutting sections and finally staining in haemtoxylene and eosin. Both taxonomic works of argulus and histopathological works will be done in the laboratory. Reports of the study will be prepared at the end of the work.', '', '', 'BAURES', 196500, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(3069, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of farm power and machinery', 'Project', 'Extension and Dissemination of Direct seeder to rural poor', 'Workshop of the department of farm power and machinery, Bangladesh Agricultural University farm, One Upazila of Jamalpur district, one Upazila of Comilla district and one Upazila of Munshiganj district.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-09-2005', '31-08-2007', '01-09-2005', '31-08-2007', '1) To improve the livelihoods of the poor farmers\r\n2) Transferred direct seeder technology to farmers in four selected areas in Bangladesh', 'i) Local manufacturers from different areas will be identified and trained to manufacture the drum seeder.\r\nii) Drum seeders developed by the manufacturers will be tested in the laboratory and BAU farm to determine the field capacity, field efficiency, performance of crop establishment etc. A field of 32 decimal will be ploughed by a tractor after removing the weeds. The field will be divided into 8 plots. Seven plots will be seeding with germinated seed by the 7 developed seeders. Rest plot will be distributed germinated seed for making seedling and using transplanting on the same plot after 21 days. The crop will be established without standing water for 3to 4 days. Other agronomic management will be done as necessary.\r\niii) Training modules will be designed and produced. Training modules will be distribute to the trainee to better use of seeders.\r\niv) Four thanas will be selected from the four districts. Training program will be conducted for selected farmers/operators. Drum seeders dedeloped by manufacturers will be distributed among the selected farmers to establish the crop in their fields.\r\nv) Data will be collected from the farmers.\r\nvi) Extension materials such as poster and booklet will be designed and produced and distribute to the different stakeholders.', '', 'Seeder, Drum seeder, poster, booklet', 'BAURES', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Farm Mechanization', 'Seeder', '', '', ''),
(3070, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agronomy', 'Project', 'Rice cum vegetable production in the same plot', 'Agronomy field laboratory, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-10-2003', '30-09-2006', '01-10-2003', '30-09-2006', '1) To select the most suitable and adaptive type of vegetables from among the different vegetable crops that could be reaised on ails of growing rice crops.\r\n2) To increase the overall production of vegetables and rice from the same plot of land at a time.\r\n3) To observe the relative profitability of rice + vegetables production compared to sole rice production.', 'Arrangements will be made to produce trellis vegetables on the ails of both T. aman and Boro rice crops. For this, rice crops will be established in both the seasons. Several vegetables, which are generally cultivated by providing trellis or stakes, would be selected for experimentation. The important aspects of investigation would include a) The vegetable species those could be grown in trellis on the ails of rice plots b) the dimension of the ails appropriate for production of vegetable species c) the size of the trellis which could support vegetable production with having little affect to rice crop and  d) The slant of the trellis, which will have little or insignificant affect on the rice crops grown underneath.', '', 'Rice cum vegetable, trellis, ail, ', 'BAURES', 225000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Crop production', 'Rice and vegetables', '', '', ''),
(3071, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Management', 'Project', 'Population dynamics of a freshwater small indigenous fish chela, cachius and its management policy implications in Bangladesh.', 'Fish specimens are to be sampled from a particular perennial habitat possibly in/near Bangladesh Agricultural University, Mymensingh.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2005', '30-06-2007', '01-07-2005', '30-06-2007', '1.	To determine age and growth of chela cachius in the perennial ponds/reservoirs;\r\n2.	To determine the recruitment pattern, length frequency, size variation in respect of pond productivity;\r\n3.	To determine the spawning period, frequency of spawning, length of spawning season and fecundity of the species;\r\n4.	To determine their survival strategies in response to fishing pressure and natural mortality;\r\n5.	To suggest the management measures towards sustained production in the rural ponds and in the open water habitats. \r\n', 'The main Methodology of the research Project have been given below: \r\na.	Material:\r\nb.	Design of Experiments:\r\nc.	Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives:\r\nd.	Data collection\r\ne.	Data analysis.\r\n', '', '', 'BARES', 150000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(3072, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Aquaculture', 'Project', 'Monogenetic ectoparasites of freshwater fishes.', 'Department of Aquaculture, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-08-1997', '31-07-2000', '01-08-1997', '31-07-2000', '1) The identification, prevalence and intensify of infestation of monogenean parasites on certain Puntius, carps and catfishes.\r\n2) Determination of host-parasite interactions with regard to size, sex and seasons of the year.\r\n3) Pathology associated with monogenean infection.  ', '1) Three ponds will be selected for sampling. Sampling will be continued for 8 months in each year.\r\n2) Four species of Puntius, 3 species of carps and 5 species of catfishes will be selected for study.\r\n3) Data on hosts and parasites will be taken for prevalence and intensity\r\n4) Gills and skin of sampled fish will be examined.\r\n5) Tissue samples will be fixed in 10% neutral buffered formalin for histopathological study\r\n6) Farm management data will be noted. ', '', 'Ectoparasites, Puntius, catfishes, carps', 'BAURES', 250900, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Fish production', 'ectoparasites', '', '', ''),
(3073, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Biology and Genetics', 'Project', 'Study of growth performance and genetic variation of Thai and local koi', 'Main research will be conducted in the Fisheries Field Laboratory Complex, BAU and genetic work will be done in the genetic laboratory of Department of Fisheries Biology and Genetics, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2007', '31-12-2008', '01-01-2007', '31-12-2008', '1) Comparative growth study between Thai and local Koi and development of easy culture technique.\r\n2) Study of morphological and genetic variation of Thai and local Koi.', 'Following experiments were conducted:\r\n1) Comparative growth study between Thai and local koi.\r\n2) Study of morphological variation between Thai and local koi.\r\n3) Study of genetic variation between Thai and local koi.', '', 'Thai Koi, local Koi, Genetic variation', 'BAURES', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Fish Production', 'Thai and local Koi', '', '', ''),
(3074, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Soil Science', 'Project', 'Screening of rice genotypes for low grain arsenic content', 'Net house, Department of Soil Science, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2006', '30-06-2008', '01-07-2006', '30-06-2008', 'To screen out potential rice genotypes having good yield coupled with low arsenic in rice grain grown in arsenic contaminated soils.', 'The experiment will be conducted at the net-house of the department of soil science of Bangladesh Agricultural University, Mymensingh. In the first year, only the modern rice varieties released by the BRRI and the BINA will be tested. Thus the varieties for T. aman rice: BR4, BR10, BR11, BR22, BR23, BRRI dhan30, BRRI dhan31, BRRI dhan32, BRRI dhan33, BRRI dhan34, BRRI dhan37, BRRI dhan38, BRRI dhan39, BRRI dhan40, BRRI dhan41, Binashail, BINA dhan4, BINA dhan5 and the varieties for boro rice: BR2, BR3, BR6, BR7, BR8, BR9, BR12, BR14, BR15, BR16, BR17, BR18, BR19, BR26, BRRI dhan28, BRRI dhan29, BRRI dhan35, BRRI dhan36, BINA dhan6 and IRATOM 26. Twelve kg of air dry soil will be taken into each pot having size of 43 cm diameter and 40 cm height. There will be two treatments consisting of 0 and 15 mg As kg per soil, each treatments replicated thrice. Arsenic will be added as sodium arsenate in solution. All the pots will receive a blanket dose of 100 mg kg-1 n, 25 mg kg-1 P, 40 mg kg-1 K and 25 mg kg-1 S from urea.', '', 'Arsenic, Rice genotypes, Low grain arsenic', 'BAURES', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Rice production', 'Rice', '', '', ''),
(3075, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Aquaculture', 'Project', 'Efficacy of medicinal herbs against some fish pathogens and their application in fish health management.', 'Fish disease laboratory and the relevant facilities under the department of aquaculture, faculty of fisheries, BAU, Mymensingh', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-09-2005', '31-08-2007', '01-09-2005', '31-085-2007', '1.	Identification and gradi8ng of available native medicinal plants effective against the growth and survival of common bacterial and fungal pathogens affecting cultured fished.\r\n2.	Investigation of the therapeutic effects of effective plants against the infectivity of selected bacterial and fungal fish pathogens.\r\n3.	Dissemination of useful findings through distribution of a prepared leaflet.\r\n', 'The main Methodology of the research Project have been given below: \r\na.	collection of various indigenous plants:\r\nb.	Collection of crude extracts:\r\nc.	Screening of  high virulent:\r\nd.	Collection of new  bacterial and fungal:\r\ne.	Efficacy test of the extracts:\r\nf.	Selection and grading of effective plants:\r\ng.	Determination of minimum inhibitory dose:\r\nh.	Annual progress report:\r\n', '', '', 'BAURES', 150000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Diseases', 'Diacrisia obliqua walks', '', '', ''),
(3076, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Surgery and Obstetrics', 'Project', 'Production of in vitro fertilized embryos of bovine in Bangladesh', 'Department of Surgery and Obstretics, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2006', '31-06-2007', '01-07-2006', '31-06-2007', '1) Establish an effective in vitro maturation (IVM) technique of local zebu oocytes.\r\n2) Establish an effective in vitro fertilization (IVF) technique of IVM oocytes.\r\n3) Establish the in vitro culture (IVC) technique for routine production of transferable IVM-IVF embryos of bovine.', 'In vitro maturation (IVM): Ovaries of local zebu cows will be collected from the slaughter house in normal saline at 37 degree centigrade and transported to the laboratory within 2 hours of slaughtering.\r\nIn vitro fertilization (IVF): The IVF will be performed according to the method described elsewhere (Bhuiyan et al., 2004).\r\nIn vitro culture (IVC): Denuding of presumptive zygotes will be performed by vortexing for 2 min in Ca.\r\nEvaluation of blastocyst quality: The quality of blastocysts  will be assessed by differential staining of the inner cell mass and the trophectoderm according to the staining procedure of Thouas et al. (2001) after modification (Bhuiyan et al., 2004). ', '', 'Embryos, bovine, IVM, IVF, IVC', 'BAURES', 150000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Livestock Development', 'Animal embryos', '', '', '');
