(3077, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Cooperative and Marketing', 'Project', 'Case studies on Successful BKB and BRDB poverty reduction poultry development programmes in selected areas of Bangladesh.', 'Sadar, Mymensingh and Shripur, Gazipur where the successful poultry farm operators exist.', 'High', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-09-2005', '28-02-2007', '01-09-2005', '28-02-2007', '1.	To make deep and intensive case studies on the extent of success and factors of success of the cases of poverty reduction poultry development farms is the main purpose of the project.\r\n2.	To find out some issues for further research study for considering whether the graduation process of successful poultry farm owner households could be the strategy of reducing poverty among the poor of Bangladesh.\r\n', 'The main Methodology of the research Project have been given below: \r\na.	Material:\r\nb.	Design of Experiments:\r\nc.	Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives:\r\nd.	Data collection\r\ne.	Data analysis.', '', '', 'BAURES', 129000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(3080, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of animal breeding and Genetics, BAU', 'Project', 'Identification of best genotype of Buffalo for dairy purpose in Bangladesh and to improve their productivity.', 'Department of animal breeding and Genetics, BAU and Animal Production Research Division, BLRI, Savar, Dhaka', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '18--8-1997', '17-07-2000', '18--8-1997', '17-07-2000', '1) Identification and characterization of Buffaloes used for dairy purpose in Bangladesh\r\n2) Evaluation of the genetic merit of Buffaloes used for dairy purpose in Bangladesh\r\n3) Identification of best genotypes of Buffalo for dairy purpose in Bangladesh.\r\n4) Improvement of productivity of Buffaloes used for dairy purpose in Bangladesh through improvement of environment factors.', '1) Characterization of dairy buffaloes.\r\n2) Evaluation of genetic merit of dairy buffaloes.\r\n3) Identification of best genotype for dairy purpose.\r\n4) Improvement of productivity ', '', 'Genotype, Buffalo, Dairy purpose, dairy Buffaloes', 'BARC', 21245000, 0, 0, 'Report', 'Field days', 0, 'Livestock production', 'Buffalo', '', '', ''),
(3078, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Technology', 'Project', 'Proximate composition and micro-nutrient contents of small indigenous freshwater fishes of Bangladesh and their role in human nutrition.', 'Department of Fisheries Technology, BAU, Mymensingh-2202', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-1999', '31-12-2001', '01-01-1999', '31-12-2001', '1.	To find out the major chemical composition/proximate composition i.e. moisture, crude protein, crude lipid and ash from mature fishes of\r\ni. Small indigenous species (SIS) of fish of fresh water of Bangladesh.\r\nii. Other important large fresh water fish species and shell fishes.\r\n2.	To determine proportion of edible and inedible parts of the body, dressed yield, training losses, gonadosomatic index (GSI), in order to categories the fish for usage in different purposes depending on the profitability.\r\n3.	 To determine the important micro-nutrients such as Calcium, Magnesium, Phosphorus, sodium, Potassium, etc. and some important vitamins.\r\n4.	To determine variation of proximate composition of fresh water small fishes as well as large fishes as a factor of the size and seasonal variation to get precise current/update information.\r\n5.	To determine the composition of major fatty acid and amino acid composition by using HPLC and other suitable methodology available in Bangladesh.\r\n', 'The main Methodology of the research Project have been given below: \r\na.	Material:\r\nb.	Design of Experiments:\r\nc.	Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives:\r\nd.	Data collection\r\ne.	Data analysis.', '', '', 'BAURES', 281845, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(3079, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Animal Nutrition', 'Project', 'A study on the promotion of rabbit meat as a conventional food item and income generation of destitute women by rabbit raising.', 'Department of Animal Nutrition', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-11-1998', '31-10-2001', '01-11-1998', '31-10-2001', '1) To study environmental, social and breeding behaviors and food habits of rabbits.\r\n2) To study the requirements of feed for reproduction and production and feed efficiency of rabbit.\r\n3) To determine the quality of rabbit meat by chemical analysis and panel tests and to highlight its importance through seminars, discussion meetings etc.\r\n4) To determine the cost of meat production\r\n5) To motivate the people to include rabbit meat in their menu as a conventional food item.\r\n6) Income generation of the destitute women through rabbit raising.', 'Forty female and ten male rabbits will be collected from Pirgassa Christian missionary farm at Madhupur or other local sources. Study will be conducted with these animals on their environmental, social and breeding behaviours and food habits. Feed requirements for growth, reproduction, lactation, production and feed efficiency will be determined. Suitable statistical design will be followed in conducting these studies. ', '', 'Rabbit, meat, lactation, ', 'BAURES', 485000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Livestock Development', 'Rabbit', '', '', ''),
(3081, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Animal Science', 'Project', 'Beef cattle fattening with locally available feed resources', 'Department of Animal Science, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', '', '01-07-2000', '30-06-2003', '01-07-2000', '30-06-2003', '1) To study the effect of different ration on beef cattle fattening made from locally available feed resources.\r\n2) To estimate the growth rate of beef cattle on stall feeding\r\n3) To study the relationship of carcass and non carcass parameters with live weight of cattle.', '1) Material: there would be three phases of this research. First year for first experiment on beef fattening and 1.5 years for second and third experimental research on beef fattening and last six months for data analysis and report writing. The present research will be a scientific approach to develop a cattle fattening program.\r\n2) Design of experiments: Three experiments will be conducted for 2.5 years. Each experiment will have two treatment having three applications per treatment. The animals would be same breed, age, weight and sex group. Data on growth rate, feed intake, feeding behaviour and carcass and non carcass parameters will be studied and examined. Collected data will be compiled, tabulated and analyzed as per Gomez and Gomez (1984).\r\n3) Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives: The research work will be for 3 years. Three appropriate experiment will be conducted for 2.5 years. Last 6 months will be used for data compilation, analisis and report writing. ', '', 'Beef cattle fattening, Feed resources, carcass, ', 'BAURES', 225000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Livestock production', 'Beef cattle fattening', '', '', ''),
(3082, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Pharmacology', 'Project', 'Determination of pesticide level in the environmental samples and their residual effect on animal samples.', 'Mymensingh, Dinajpur and Brahman Baria', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-02-2000', '30-06-2001', '01-02-2000', '30-06-2001', '1) Collection of environmental samples i.e. water, soil, plants, grasses and food stuff from different areas of at least 3 selected districts of Bangladesh and detection of pesticide level in the collected samples.\r\n2) Collection of blood, urine and milk from cattle &amp; goats of above mentioned 3 selected districts and detection of pesticide level in those samples.\r\n', '1) Collection of environmental samples and pesticide determination: water, soil, plant, grasses and food stuff will be collected from different areas of 3 selected districts of Bangladesh and pesticide level will be measured as per selected method.\r\n2) Collection of blood, urine and milk: These samples will be collected from cattle and goats of different areas of 3 selected districts as mentioned above and determination of pesticide level in those samples as per selected method.', '', 'Pesticide, Residual effect, environmental pollution', 'BARC', 593000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Residual effect of pesticide', 'Animal', '', '', ''),
(3083, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Parasitology', 'Project', 'Role of hypobiosis in the epidemiology of Haemonchus contortus in goats and the study of anthelmintic resistance', 'Department of Parasitology, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2001', '30-06-2004', '01-07-2001', '', '1) To investigate the degree and pattern of larval inhibition in H. contortus in goats.\r\n2) To identify the factor(s) responsible for larval inhibition.\r\n3) To identify the season(s) of the year when maximum inhibition occurs.\r\n4) To know the number of generation(s) of H. contortus per year.\r\n5) To define the means of transmission and population expansion of this common stomach worm from one season to the next.\r\n6) To detect the level of resistance in gastrointestinal nematodes against the commonly available anthelmintics.  ', '', '', 'H. contortus, Anthelmintic, Hypobiosis', 'BAURES', 225000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Livestock production', 'Goat', '', '', ''),
(3084, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Anatomy and Histology', 'Project', 'Studies of Ig (immunoglobulin) containing plasma cells in the lymphoid organs and mucosa associated lymphatic tissues in the prenatal and postnatal stages of indigenous chickens of Bangladesh.', 'Laboratory of the Department of Anatomy and Histology, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '', 'Steps followed in the methodology:\r\n1) Chicken of prenatal stages\r\n2) Chickens of postnatal stages\r\n3) Samples for the study\r\n4) Histological study\r\n5) Immunohistochemistry Histoplanimetry\r\n6) Statistical analysis', 'Gross anatomy, histology and immunohistochemistry of embryonic lymphoid organ of native chickens were studied during embryonic stages of development.  Bursa was developed from a proliferation of endodermal epithelium of dorsal caudal region of embryonic cloaca. By the 10 days of incubation the plicae become shorter and wider and the bursal cells were started to organize to form follicle within the plicae. One day 14 incubation bursal follicles were already formed, and the cells were started to organize to form cortex and medulla and developing capillary loops are observed in high magnification. Finally on day 20, the bursal follicles are clearly organized into cortex and medulla. The thymus of chick embryo was found as a chain of irregular shaped lobes along the jugular vein on both sides of the neck. At embryonic day 10, the budding of thymus was seen. At day 12, fiber network of thymus was formed to create a basement of cells of thymus. At embryonic day 14, the cells were begun to organize to form a fiber network and capillary beds. At embryonic day 20, thin connective tissue capsule was clearly visible. The darker cortex and lighter medulla can be observed and the cortex was packed with large number of lymphocytes. Spleen was small rounded; reddish brown colored spleen was found in the junction between the proventriculus and gizzard. At embryonic day 10, very thin capsule was seen and larger number of granulocyte formed to observe rather than lymphocyte. During embryonic day  12, very few white pulps with increased number of granulocyte were observed in the spleen. By embryonic day 14, purple colored white pulp and pinkish red pulp were visible and small amount of lymphocytes began to appear. At embryonic day 20, the thickness of capsule was increased, red pulp and white pulp were more distinguishable and the number of lymphocyte was greatly increased. Among the prenatal lymphoid organ of native chickens of Bangladesh bursa of Fabricius contained more lgs-positive cells and lgM-positive cells were the first appearing plasma cells. There were few lgG-positive cells were present in bursa of Fabricius and spleen at the end of embryonic stages but there was lacking of lgA-positive plasma cells were developed the prenatal lymphoid organ of the present study.  ', 'Anatomy, Histology, Indigenous chicken, Histological, prenatal, postnatal', 'BAURES', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Livestock production', 'Indigenous Chicken', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress. Volume 20. Proceedings of the Workshop of Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, 07-08 March, 2010. Bangladesh Agricultural University Research System (BAURES), BAU, Mymensingh.'),
