(3106, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Agronomy', 'Project', 'Agronomic Characteristics and productivity of buckwheat under different management practices. ', '', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2000', '30-06-2003', '01-07-2000', '30-06-2003', 'In Bangladesh, buckwheat is cultivated in the north-west region only. Most of the farmers in the east and south are not familiar with the consumption and use of buckwheat. As such a detail cultivation procedure of this crop is urgently needed which is presently not available.\r\nThus development of agronomic management practices for higher production in buckwheat is the main objective of the proposed plan of work. Research will be conducted to find out the optimum levels of the following agronomic management practices: \r\na.	Planting time\r\nb.	Seed rate\r\nc.	Weeding time\r\nd.	Fertilizer dose\r\ne.	Inter-cropping etc.\r\n', 'The main Methodology of the research Project have been given below: \r\na.	Material:\r\nb.	Design of Experiments:\r\nc.	Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives:\r\nd.	Data collection\r\ne.	Data analysis.\r\n', '', 'Buckwheat, Management practices,k ', 'BAURES', 225000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(3107, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Microbiology and Hygiene', 'Project', 'Studies on the impediments of commercial production of different breeds of pigeon in Bangladesh', 'Department of Microbiology and Hygiene, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2000', '30-06-2002', '01-07-2000', '30-06-2002', '1) Collection of 20 pairs of different breeds of pigeon from different parts of Bangladesh which have distinctive characteristics.\r\n2) To study the rearing methods and managements in intensive intensive cage and confined scavenging system\r\n3) To study the incidence of diseases, zoonotic disease in particular, affecting the pigeon in different seasons and their prevention and control.\r\n4) To evaluate production, potentials of different breeds in different management system.\r\n5) To study the socio economic impact of pigeon rearing for commercial production in Bangladesh condition.', '1) Physical facilities\r\n2) Factors in study:\r\ni) Housing and cage rearing, pattern of cages, pattern of pens\r\nii) Feeding and watering\r\niii) Bath arrangement\r\niv) Ration\r\nv) Production records\r\nvi) Feed consumption', '', 'Pigeon, Ration, Bath arrangement', 'BAURES', 149600, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Livestock Production', 'Pigeon', '', '', ''),
