(3144, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Cooperative and Marketing', 'Project', 'Study on size and pattern of crop diversification programs in selected areas of Bangladesh  ', 'Department of Cooperative and Marketing, BAU', 'High', 'Adaptive', 'Completed', '01-07-1998', '30-06-2000', '01-07-1998', '30-06-2000', '1.To examine the socio-economic and tenurial status of the crop diversifying farmers in the areas under study.\r\n2.To find out the size and pattern of crop diversification programmes of the farmers under study including considering the socio-economic impact of the additional output on the standard of living of the farmers.\r\n3.To identify the problems, such as economic, customary, family and group farming aspects that are related to the crop diversification programmes in the areas under study. \r\n4.On the basis of these findings to make some suggestions towards the policy makers for sound crop diversification programmes in the country in future.\r\n', 'The study would conveniently convers six villages based on one village from each division of Bangladesh. Each village would be considered as a cluster. So, cluster sampling method would be followed in selecting the respondents of the proposed study. From each cluster 50 farmers would be sampled at random for the study. Thus, the total number of samples would be 300 farmers. A well-developed interview schedule would be used in collecting the necessary data. The data thus, collected after editing &amp; coding would be tabulated for further analysis. The analysis would be diverted towards the specified objectives. In addition to the tabular representation an endeavor would also be taken to develop some relationships and tests in the proposed study.', 'diversification', 'Diversification, Crops, Polichy makers', 'BAURES', 202360, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Diversification', 'Crops', '', '', ''),
