(3175, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Aquaculture', 'Project', 'Investigation of catfish diseases in Mymensingh area through histopathological techniques. ', 'Department of Aquaculture, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-08-1997', '31-07-2000', '01-08-1997', '31-07-2000', '1) To survey the existing literature on various disease of catfish.\r\n2) To investigate the nature and extent of catfish disease from the two recommended areas of Mymensingh district.\r\n3) To develop disease investigation technique through histopathology and to ascertain the causative agents of disease.\r\n4) To compare occurrence of catfish disease at various seasons of the year and between the farms.\r\n5) To provide remedial measures of catfish disease.', '1) Material collection\r\n2) Design of experiment\r\n3) Procedure to be followed in achieving stated objectives.\r\ni) Preparation of a detailed bibliography on the existing literature following detail of an extensive survey is a necessary preequisite before initiating any research programme. Therefore, a survey of the available literature on diseases of catfish will be made.\r\nii) Before going to investigate the catfish diseases, it of almost importance to known about the nature and extent of diseases, that has occurred in the previous years. This will provide some clues about the diseases of catfish.\r\niii) All the experiments mentioned under the heading &quot;Experimental Design&quot; will be performed properly where from, it is expected, a suitable technique for disease of catfish will result.\r\niv) From the data obtained following the heading &quot;Experimental Design) it would be easy task to compare the occurrence of catfish disease at various seasons of the years and between the farms.\r\nv) Preventive measures will be sortedout depending upon the nature and extent of catfish diseases and there causative agents which would be investigated in the present experiment.', '', 'Catfish, histopathology, dise