(3181, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Farm Structure', 'Project', 'Design and development of environment-friendly and income-generating poultry housing systems at farmers'' level', 'Mymensingh, Dhaka and other places.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2008', '30-06-2010', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2010', '1.	To identify and characterize the safe and environmental factors for confined poultry housing systems.\r\n2.	To design and develop and environmentally controlled and functional low-cost model poultry house for rural area.\r\n3.	To develop hygienic and economically viable compost preparation technique using the poultry litters.\r\n', 'The work will be started with routine visit of some selected commercial and small stakeholders poultry farms for collecting information of materials and equipment currently being used in the farms through structural components, ventilation syste4ms, hygienic situation operating systems and size of farms depending on the investment capacity of the rural people. The effectiveness of the model farms will be estimated considering the sage environmental factors, suitability to establish in the rural areas, social acceptability to adoption of such farms etc. in furthering the work, a hygienic and economically viable compost preparation technique will be attempted using the solid wastes from the poultry farms (Rashid &amp; Abedin, 1991). The effectiveness and utility of using organic fertilizer will be studied. ', '', 'Chicken, Poultry farm., Development', 'BAURES', 200000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Development', 'Poultry Farm', '', '', ''),
