(3356, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Aquaculture', 'Project', 'Aetiopathology and Control Measures of Ulcer Disease in farmed Fishes.\r\n', 'Department of Aquaculture, BAU', 'Medium', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-10-2000', '30-09-2003', '01-10-2000', '30-09-2003', '1) To isolate bacteria and fungi from the ulcer affected fish;\r\n2) To characterize the suspective bacterial pathogens for specific identification;\r\n3) To characterize isolated fungal pathogen.\r\n4) Histopathological studies of the affected fish;\r\n5) Pathogenicity test of the selected suspective bacterial and fungal pathogen; and\r\n6) Trial for control measures:\r\na) Therapeutic measures - Chemotherapy\r\nb) Preventive measures - trial for antibody production and vaccination against the specific pathogen.', 'a) Materials:\r\n1) Bacteriological tools.\r\n2) Fungus isolation protocols.\r\n3) Culture media and chemicals.\r\n4) Pathogenic test protocol.\r\n5) Chemotherapeutic and preventive materials.\r\nb) Design of experiments:\r\n1) Isolation of suspective bacterial pathogens from affected organs including kidney of diseases fish.\r\n2) Isolation of fungul pathogen at the same time following mycological techniques.\r\n3) Characterization and identification of selected bacteria and fungal isolates.\r\n4) Histopathological examination of the sampled fish tissues.\r\n5) Challenge tests for detection of pathogenicity of the selected isolates.\r\n6) Trial for chemotherapy with different drugs and chemicals.\r\n7) Trial for vaccination.', 'Disease is one of the major problem in aquaculture in Bangladesh. In every year both fish and shrimp production are hampered by the incidence of the disease as a result, our national economy are severely affected. In most cases freshwater fishes have been found to be affected by ulcer type of disease caused by various causative agents. In our previous studies it has been found a number of bacterial species are associated with the epizootic ulcerative syndrome. However, in the recent studies it has been found that a fungus plays a major role to cause the disease associated with other causative agents such as bacteria. Still it is highly controversial to recognize its primary invader. Although the disease occurs in epizootic forms in Asian countries but still its effective control measure is yet to be established.\r\nIn Bangladesh Fisheries, various ulcer type of diseases are now confused with the EUS which are found to occur throughout the year in both farmed and wild fishes. So, it becomes a great problem to diagnose the specific cause and to suggest the possible control measures. On the basis of our previous studies, it is very important to take further studies on ulcer disease of fish in Bangladesh.', 'Aetiopathology, Farmed Fishes, Histopathological studies', 'BAURES', 226200, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Fish diseases management', 'Farmed Fishes', '', '', ''),
