(3367, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Aquaculture', 'Project', 'Health Management of Cultured Fishes using Low cost Chemotherapeutic and Medicinal plants', 'Fish Disease Laboratory of the Department of Aquaculture, BAU, BFRI and private fish farms in Mymensingh.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '01-07-2007', '30-06-2009', '1) Trial for the application of the selected low cost effective chemotherapeutic and local medicinal plants (based on the previous studies) against diseased fishes under laboratory and field condition.\r\n2) To suggest for making a package in favour of combined treatment methods using effective, safe chemotherapeutic and medicinal plants.\r\n3) Dissemination of useful findings through prepared leaflets for the use fish culturists, farmers, relevant officers and scientists.', 'The research works will be accomplished in two phases. Methodology for each phase is given below:\r\nPhase I\r\n1) Collection and screening of low cost effective chemotherapeutic viz. salt, lime, antibiotics, stains, mild insecticides etc. would be selected based on our previous studies for a package program.\r\n2) Efficacy of these chemotherapeutic would be verified under in-vitro condition on bacterial and fungal fish pathogens.\r\n3) Effective chemotherapeutic would be applied against experimentally infected fish and rate of recovery will be monitored.\r\n4) Low cost most effective chemotherapeutic would be applied to the naturally infected fish at farmers field level of the facilities available.\r\n5) Annual report writing and presentation.\r\nPhase II\r\n1) Efficacy of the selected medicinal plants would be checked under in vitro condition against bacterial and fungal fish pathogens.\r\n2) Effective medicinal plants would be applied on the experimental infected fish with bacteria or fungi under laboratory condition.\r\n3) Combined/mixed effects of effective chemotherapeutic and medicinal plants will be evaluated on the experimental infection of fish or natural infection case if available.', 'Previous studies provided some basic information about the control measures of some of the diseases caused by the pathogens. Fish farmers and culturists showed interest on these chemotherapeutic and medicinal plants. They demanded more effective and easily available medicinal plants that can save their fish from diseases under eco-friendly environmental condition. With this noble objective, a great demand initiated to prepare a suitable package for the control of common infectious fish diseases, especially caused by bacterial and fungal pathogens by the use of low cost effective safe chemotherapeutic and effective medicinal plants.', 'Chemotherapeutic, Medicinal plants, bacterial and fungal pathogens.', 'BAURES', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Disease management', 'Fish', '', '', ''),
