(3386, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of fisheries management', 'Project', 'Annual gametogenic pattern and pathologic condition of fresh water mussel, Lamellidens marginalis collected from Boyra, Mymensingh using biometry and histology.', 'Sampling site: Boyra, Mymensingh\r\nLaboratory Analysis: Histology laboratory and water quality &amp; pond dynamics laboratory, BAU, Mymensingh', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2009', '30-06-2010', '01-07-2009', '30-06-2010', '1) To know the seasonal changes in condition index of the clams to harvest quality mussels;\r\n2) To determine the spawning time and duration of this clam for the establishment of the hatchery.\r\n3) To correlate the water quality parameters with the annual gametogenic pattern of this mussel;\r\n4) To investigate the presence of parasites in the histological preparations.', 'Fresh water mussel, Lamellidens marginalis samples will be collected monthly from the pond located at Boyra, Mymensingh during July 2009 to June 2010. Upon the arrival in laboratory, the shell length of the mussels will be measured. Mussels will be dissected and the weight of the soft body will be taken. The soft tissues of twenty mussels will be processed for histology. The shells of all the dissected mussels will be allowed to dry for calculation of condition index. The condition index of the analyzed mussels will be calculated by dividing the wet tissue weight by dry shell weight. Water quality parameters, viz. water temperature, dissolved oxygen, PH and chlorophyll-a concentration will also be monitored during sampling time.\r\nThe soft tissue of the mussels will be fixed in Davidson''s solution and a transverse section will be cut through the middle of the body which will contain gonad, digestive gland, mantle and muscular foot tissue. The tissue will be subsequently dehydrated and embedded in paraffin. Paraffin blocks will be sectioned and stained with Harris''s haematoxylene and counter stained in eosin Y. After mounting, the histological preparations will be examined under a light microscope to determine sex and gametogenic stage as well as to investigate the presence of parasites in the clams. The reproductive maturity of the gonads observed in the histological preparations will be categorized into six stages using the maturity scale described by Park and Choi (2004). The stages are 1) Early developing 2) Late developing 3) Ripe 4) Spawning 5) Spent and 6) Indifferent.', 'Fresh water mussels, Lamellidens marginalis are abundant in inland water bodies such as lakes, rivers and ponds of Bangladesh. In our country, mussels collected solely from natural sources are predominantly used for the production of line, poultry and aqua feeds. To counter balance the stress exerted by exploitation of natural stock, technologies can be developed for culturing them in the ponds that will ensure the conservation of its natural stock as well as meeting the demand of rapidly expanding poultry and aqua feeds. In Bangladesh, most of the families, especially in the villages, own ponds near their houses which are used for domestic purposes, such as washing clothes, bathing, as a source of drinking water and also for cultivating fish. To establish the fresh water mussel hatchery system for the timely supply of adequate spats, knowledge on their reproductive strategy, spawning time and duration as well as the precise information on favourable ecological conditions for their reproduction is indispensable.', 'Boyra, Gametogenic pattern, Harris''s haematoxylene', 'BAU-UGC', 118500, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Disease management', 'Fish', '', '', ''),
