(3392, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Biology and Genetics', 'Project', 'Impacts of aquatic pollution on fishes in different rivers.', 'Survey: Buriganga, Shitalakshya and Turag rivers and wet laboratory, Department of Fisheries Biology and Genetics, BAU-2202\r\n', 'Medium', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2010', '30-06-2012', '01-07-2010', '30-06-2012', '1) Survey to know the fish population in the Buriganga, Shitalakshya and Turag rivers and toxicity effect of these rivers'' water on fishes.\r\n2) Determination of the toxicity of commonly used pesticides on fish in laboratory conditions.\r\n3) Histological study of internal organs of pesticide treated fishes;\r\n4) Evaluation of the residual effects of pesticide by the study of producing F1 generation.', '1) Survey\r\n2) Laboratory toxicity test\r\n3) Histopathological effects\r\n4) Generation study\r\n5) Egg quality evaluation\r\n6) Sperm count\r\n7) Fertilization\r\n8) Fry survival and growth', 'As being a burning issue, river pollution particularly, Buriganga, Turag and Shitalakkhya have addressed as most of the sewage and industrial effluents in Dhaka and its surrounding somehow ends up to those rivers thereby, water quality and seasonal plankton availability of these ricers were recorded. 0.7-1.9 ppm dissolved oxygen and 21-26 plankton genera were recorded at alean period which is mentionably low. On the other hand agricultural organophosphates (OP) finding their way to aquatic ecosystem by surface run off adversely affects the biota of that system.  The LC50 of Envoy 50 SC, Samcup 50 EC and Darsban 20 EC were estimated as 0.116, 0.192 and 0.765 ppm for L. rohita and 0.458, 0.073 and 0.269 ppm for B. gonionotus. To assess the effects of river pollution and (OP) at cellular and molecular level, histopathology and acetylcholine esterase (AChE) activity measurement were performed. Both the pollutants and organophosphate pesticides abruptly alter the normal structure in various fish organslike skin muscle, gills, kidney, liver and gonads. A significant (P&amp;#8804;0.01) inhibition of AChE activity in Heterophneustes fossilis brain due to pollutants were observed with following order of potency 102.00 &plusmn; 5.00 nmol/min/mg protein (Turag) &amp;#8805;104.00 &plusmn; 5.00 nmol/min/mg protein (Buriganga) &gt; 130.67 &plusmn; 3.51 nmol/min/mg protein (Shitalakkhya). Furthermore, pesticide treated Labeo rohita shows higher enzymatic inhibition recorded as 46.67 &plusmn; 5.51 nmol/min/mg protein 221.67 &plusmn; 60.3 nmol/min/mg protein than Barbonymus gonionotus recorded as 221.67 &plusmn; 60.3 nmol/min/mg protein. However, cholinesterase inhibition in pesticides exposed fish brain is a dose depended manure. This study implies that both pollution and pesticides poses a great threat to vulnerable aquatic biota. ', 'Aquatic pollution, toxicity effect, ', 'BAU-UGC', 240000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Aquatic Pollution and its Impact', 'Fish', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, Volume-22, 2011.  Proceedings of the workshop of BAU Research Progress, 02-03 April 2012.'),
