(3406, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Fisheries Biology and Genetics', 'Project', 'Genetic conservation and quality seed production of indigenous catfishes (Heteropneusstes fossllis and Clarias batrachus) through cryogenic gene banking.', 'Main research will be conducted in the laboratory. Fish will be reared in ponds in the Field Laboratory Complex and also in ponds beside the Fisheries Faculty Building, BAU.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2008', '30-06-2010', '01-07-2008', '30-06-2010', '1) To develop and standardize the cryopreservation techniques for H. fossilis and C. batrachus sperm.\r\n2) Availability of milt without killing male fish.\r\n3) To establish a cryogenic gene bank from where cryopreserved sperm can be supplied to the users.\r\n4) To disseminate the cryopreservation techniques among hatchery operators.', '1) Experimental Fish\r\n2) Dilution and preparation of milt for cooling.\r\n3) Freezing of milt and thawing', 'Cryopreservation is a potential technique for genetic improvement of catfish, no cryopreservation work on H. fossilis and C. batrachus has been done so far in Bangladesh and elsewhere. However, there are some reports available on successful development of cryopreservation procedures of other catfishes such as African catfish, Clarias gariepinus (Hovarth and Urbanyi, 2000), channel catfish, Ictalurus punctatus (Christensen and Tiersch, 1997), blue catfish, Ictalurus furcatus (Lang et al. 2003) and striped catfish, Pangasius hypophthalmus (Kwantong and Bart, 2003). Considering the potential application of cryopreservation technique in catfish, the present research work has been proposed for funding by BAURES and if so cryogenic gene bank will be possible to establish which will ensure the production of quality seeds and genetic conservation of the catfish.', '(Heteropneusstes fossllis and Clarias batrachus), ', 'BAURES', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Fish production', 'Catfishes (Heteropneustes fossilis and Clarias batrachus)', '', '', ''),
