(3409, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Aquaculture', 'Project', 'Effect of stocking density on growth and production performance of mono sex (male) tilapia (Oreochromis niliticus)', 'Ponds around Faculty of Fisheries/Lab. complex, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2010', '01-01-2009', '31-12-2010', '1) To determine the proximate composition of supplemental diet.\r\n2) To estimate the effects of stocking density on growth and production of the fishes.\r\n3) To estimate the food conversion ratio (FCR)\r\n4) To recommend the optimum stocking density of the fishes in which in highest growth and production would be achieved.', '1) Study area selection\r\ni) The pond banks and embankments will be raised and repaired properly in broken places.\r\nii) The ponds will be cleared off aquatic vegetation by repeated cutting. Predatory and other undesirable species will be removed by use seine and cast nets.\r\niii) Rotenone will used in ponds to make sure about the complete removal of unwanted fishes and other species.\r\niv) The ponds will be limed at a dose of 250 kg/ha.\r\n2) Experimental design, fertilization, stocking and feeding\r\n3) Water quality parameters\r\n4) Growth and production of the fishes\r\n5) Food conversion ratio (FCR)\r\n6) Statistical analysis', 'The main purpose of aquaculture is to improve the production of aquatic biomass. Tilapia feeds in the low food web in pond ecosystems. This allows increased production using only the natural foods produced in ponds and/or low grade supplementary feeds. The expansion of culture of tilapia will not only help in earning foreign exchange but also improve the nutrition and increase income of the rural population in developing countries. One of the major problems for the culture of tilapia is the frequent breeding, which resulted in over population and lead to stunting growth rate. In order to reduce such problem mono sex (Male) culture of tilapia is to be adopted. The stocking density and growth rate are very much related. If the proper stocking density is not maintained if will exerts many negative impacts on production. Therefore, it is important to optimize the stocking density of the fishes, which will ensure sustainable growth and production. ', 'Stocking density, mono sex tilapia, Food conversion ratio (FCR)', 'BAU-UGC', 200000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Stocking density on growth and production of Fish', 'Mono sex tilapia (male)', '', '', ''),
