(3456, 'Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute', 'APRD, BLRI', 'Project', 'Maximizing HYV fodder production of different species through improved management practices', 'Chandina and Daudkandi (Comilla), Bhuapur (Tangail) and Dakope (Khulna)', '', 'Adaptive', 'On-going', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2014', '01-05-2011', '30-06-2014', '1) To increase HYV fodder (napier, german, para and splendida) production in four selected Upazilas.\r\n2) To increase milk production of small scale dairy farmers and thereby generates income through selling milk and fodders.', '', '', 'Fodder production, napier, para, german', 'Krishi Gobeshona Foundation (KGF)', 4475000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Livestock Development', 'Fodder crop', '1) Utilization of 450 acres of fallow land, embankmemt and roadsides that will produce 10,000 tones of green fodder.\r\n2) About 200 smallholders farmers will directly be involved in fodder production and income generation activities. Expected net economic return (NER) from fodder production will be Tk. 24,000.00 year per smallholder farmer.\r\n3) Supply of green fodder will reduces feed cost and this will be allowed to save Tk. 5,000.00 per animal from the total cost of feed during 235 days lactation period.\r\n4) One Ph.D student will be involved to carry out his/her research programme on HYV fodder production and feeding technology.', '', ''),
(3457, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Aquaculture', 'Project', 'Entrepreneurial growth of pangas (Pangasius hypophthalmus) farming in Mymensingh area: an understanding of social and environmental impacts.', 'Pangas farming area at Trishal, Mymensingh\r\nDepartment of Aquaculture, Faculty of Fisheries, BAU', '', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2008', '30-06-2010', '01-07-2008', '30-06-2010', '1) To figure out extent of pressure of pangas farming on cropland in a temporal scale.\r\n2) To assess dynamics of ground water use for pangas farming and existing condition of nutrient rich water of pangas farm.\r\n3) Impacts due to the discharge of nutrient rich water to the surrounding people irrespective of farm owner and non farmer\r\n4) Recommend a strategy to use nutrient rich water of pangas farms for crop production.', '', '', '', 'BAURES', 176000, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Fish production', 'Pangas', '', '', ''),
