(3480, 'Sher-e-Bangla Agricultural University', 'Department of Horticulture', 'Project', 'Characterization &amp; Chromatographic fingerprint analysis of some locally available medicinal plants', '', 'High', 'Adoptive', 'Completed', '01-06-2008', '31-12-2009', '01-06-2008', '31-12-2009', '1.	To collect plant samples form different locations of Bangladesh and conserve it in the horticulture farm. SAU and multiply the plants for further research and confirmation.\r\n2.	To identify the active ingredients or chemicals that are present in the collected plant materials but yet to identified or characterized in our herbal industry. The aim is to find out the specific ingredient from specific target through this present proposed project. \r\n3.	To find out or make the pharmacologically active constituents or principle marker constituents to assess the quality and authenticity of herbal medicines.\r\n4.	To standardize the chemical fingerprint of commonly used medicinal plants in herbal medicine.\r\n5.	To develop and validate an HPLC and HPLC-MS method for fingerprint analysis of locally available and popular medicinal plants.\r\n6.	For making a computerized database or documentation of the commonly used medicinal plants in herbal industry.\r\n', 'Sample preparation: Collected sample (Aloe, Basok, Cannon ball, Datura, Kalomegh. Etc.) were air dried and few of them are dried in the hot air oven (Binder, Germany at room temperature. Dried samples were then blend through a Blender (Miyako, Japan). Blended samples were poured in a samples bottle to dissolve them in different solvents. \r\nSolvents used: a. n-Hexane (Merck-Germany): solvents were used to isolate non polar compound \r\nb. Ethyl Acetate (Fisher Scientific-UK) for compounds that are semi poplar.\r\nc. Ethanol (Fisher Scientific-UK)- for polar compounds.\r\nd. methanol (J.T. Baker-USA)_ for high polar compounds.\r\ne. Evaporation:\r\nf. Sample stored:\r\ng. Reference standard:\r\nh. Development of fingerprint- to standardize the fingerprint, collected and selected samples have been analyzed with developed PHLC-MS analysis procedure.\r\n', 'The total methods for NMR and PHLC have to be validated to achieve the satisfactory precision and recovery. Relative retention time and relative peaks were to identify the common peaks for fingerprint analysis. There are a lot of peaks would be found in the different medicinal plant samples fingerprints. A method incorporating high performance liquid chromatographic separations have to be performed on Shimadzu C 18 (4.6mm x 200 mm, 5 um) column with water/ammonium acetate/2% acetic acid or other solvents can be used as the mobile phase. At this stage, methanol part of Basok, 4 parts (N-hezane, EA. Ethanol, Methanol) of Aloe vera, 4 parts of cannon ball (PE, EA, Butanol, Methanol), 4 parts of Kalomegh (n-hexane, EA, Butanol and methanol) are ready to do antimicrobial, Antibiotic test. Already 5 single compounds of petroleum ether (PE) part are ready to do NMR.', 'Herbal, Medicines, Germplasm, Bio-markers, Medicinal plants', 'SAURES', 316850, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Secondary Compund Analysis', 'Medicinal Plant', '1.	A reserved medicinal plant germplasm center has partially established in horticulture farm of SAU campus. \r\n2.	We well be able to produce bio-markers for the specific medicinal plant and also validate a protocol to find out the specific compound which is responsible for those specific reason/diseases so that it will not be necessary to use the traditional crude extract.\r\n3.	We can supply the protocol to the herbal industry for producing specific medicine.\r\n4.	Hopefully, few decisions can be made in minimizing the import of foreign herbal medicines/products and will also help export of those after validation and successful completion of the project.\r\n', '1.	A medicinal plant Germplasm center has established in SAU Campus.\r\n2.	We able to produce bio-markers for the specific medicinal plant and specific reason/diseases.\r\n3.	We can product herbal medicinal raw materials for herbal industries.\r\n4.	We can reduce of importable herbal products and in future we also help to export some herbal medicines.   \r\n', ''),
