(3509, 'Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Agricultural University', 'Department of Agricultural Extension and Rural Development', 'Project', 'Rice Production in Drought Prone Areas of Bangladesh. ', 'Nachole, Badalgachi, Kalai, Pirgacha, Sonatala and Gobindagonj Upazila', 'Medium', 'Adaptive', 'On-going', '30-05-2011', '30-04-2014', '30-05-2011', '30-04-2014', '1.	To identify factors responsible for lower yield of rice in the study areas;\r\n2.	To adapt rice varieties of drought condition;\r\n3.	To improve soil fertility level for sustainable rice production; and \r\n4.	To improve knowledge on drought management and create awareness among the farmers on vulnerability in rice production. \r\n', 'The department of Agricultural Extension and Rural Development and soil Science of the lead agency, BSMRAU and the division of Statistics, BRRI along with the associate agencies, SSURDA and PHKS have been conducting field level research under the close supervision of lead departments through participatory approaches and experimental trials in the drought prone areas. A total of 192 field trials were conducted taking twelve rice varieties, six in each T. aman and six in Boro season and four management practices in seven locations of the project areas including the on-station trial at BSMRAU. Thirty four field days and eight training programs were conducted to create farmers awareness on rice production under drought condition.', '', 'Rice, Drought, Management Practices', 'Krishi Gobeshona Foundation (KGF)', 9788900, 6514809, 0, 'Report', 'Training, Field Days', 240, 'Crop Production', 'Rice', '', '', '');
