(3519, 'Sher-e-Bangla Agricultural University', 'Department of Agronomy', 'Project', 'Successive cultivation of rice using clonal tillers', 'Agronomy field, SAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2012', '31-01-213', '01-07-2012', '31-01-213', '1) To compare the performance of local, inbred and hybrid rice varieties.\r\n2) To determine the suitability of using clonal tillers to increase rice yield.\r\n3) To calculate the economics of using rice clonal tillers for successive generation.\r\n4) To find out a complete package of using clonal tillers for rice cultivation.', '\r\nThe experiment will be consisted of two factors as variety and planting material:\r\nA) Main plot (Variety):3\r\ni) BRRI dhan29 (Inbred)\r\nii) Heera (hybrid)\r\niii) Bhajan or any other local variety\r\nB) Sub plot: (Planting materials): 5\r\ni) Nursery seedling\r\nii) 1st generation clonal tillers collected from nursery seedling\r\niii) 2nd generation clonal tillers collected from 1st clonal\r\niv) 3rd generation clonal tillers collected from 2nd clonal\r\nv) 4th generation clonal tillers collected from 3rd clonal.\r\nExperimental Design and Layout\r\nDesign of the experiment: Split-plot\r\nMain plot treatment: Variety\r\nSub plot treatment: Planting materials\r\nNumber of replication: 3\r\nTotal treatment combination: 15\r\nTotal number of plot: 45\r\n1) Raising and Transplanting of Seedling\r\n2) Manure and Fertilizers application\r\n3) Data collection\r\n4) Data analysis', '', 'Successive cultivation, rice, Clonal tillers', 'MOSICT', 300000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agriculture (Biological Science)', 'Rice', 'One student completed MS thesis on the technology.', 'Rice can be cultivate throughout the year with one time minimum true seeds.', ''),
(3520, 'Sher-e-Bangla Agricultural University', 'Department of Horticulture', 'Project', 'Genetic Diversity, correlation, Morphological and Molecular Characterization of Capsicum (Capsicum annum L.).', '', 'Medium', 'Adaptive', 'On-going', '01-07-2012', '30-06-2013', '01-07-2012', '30-06-2013', '1.	To study the genetic variability n Capsicum germplasm for quantitative and quality traits.\r\n2.	To study the nature and extent of genetic diversity for productivity traits and identification of molecular polymorphism in capsicum germplasm.\r\n3.	To determine the nature and magnitude of correlation among different quantitative traits and their direct and indirect effects on fruit yield.\r\n4.	To identify the genotypes for export purpose and developing varieties.\r\n', '1.	Expt. No.      (i) Collection and evaluation of capsicum germplasm\r\n(ii) Studies on the genetic diversity of capsicum using morphological characters\r\n(iii) studies on the genetic diversity of capsicum using Randomly Amplified polymorphic DNA (RAPD) markers.\r\n(iv) Studies on the character association and path analysis capsicum.\r\na.	To evaluate the capsicum germplasm for yield and different physiomorphological characters.\r\nb.	Treatments: Capsicum germplasm\r\nc.	Design: RCBD\r\nd.	Spacing: 60 x 45 cm\r\ne.	Replication: 3\r\n2.	Data will be recorded: (i) Days to 50% flowering (DFF), (ii) plant height, (iii) 1000 seed weight, (iv) Fruit weight, (v) Fresh fruit yield per plant, (vi) Diameter of fruit, (vii) ascorbic acid content (viii) yield/plant\r\n3.	Method of analysis: data will be analyzed using MSTAT and SPSS computer program.\r\n\r\n', '', 'Capsicum, fruit, yield, plant and seed', 'MOST', 300000, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'Agriculture', 'Capsicum', '', 'After completion of data collection, compilation and statistical analysis is to be done accordingly.', ''),
