(3677, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Anatomy &amp; Histology', 'Project', 'Molecular detection of cellular prion protein from brain tissues of Black Bengal goast', 'Mymensingh district.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2010', '30-06-2012', '01-07-2010', '30-06-2012', '', '', 'The cellular prion protein (PrPC) is a membrance-bound glycop0rotein mainly present in the central nervous system. The scrapie prion protein (PrPSc) is an abnormal isoform of PrPC, and it is responsible for transmissible spongiform encephalopathies (TSEs), a group of neurodegenerative diseases affecting both humans and animals. The presence of the cellular from is necessary for the establishment and further evolution of prion diseases. But no study has for been successfully done for the molecular identification of PrPC gene in Bangladesh. This study was undertaken for the detection of PrPC gene in the brain tissues of indigenous black Bengal goat in Bangladesh. For that reasons total samples (brain tissues) were collected from different slaughter houses of Mymensingh district, during January to February, 2011. All the samples of brain tissues were preserved at -800C for molecular detectin by Polymerase Chain Reaction (PCR). DNA was extracted from the brain tissues using WizardR Genomic DNA Purification Kit (Promega Corporation. 2800 woods Hollow Road. Madison, USA). PCR was done by commercial PCR kit (PCR Master Mixture Kit, GeNei TM, Banglore Genei, BDA Industrial Suburb, Peenya, India) using PRPC (F) and PRPC &reg; primers. The PCR products were visualized by electrophoresis using 1 % agarose gel stained with ethidium bromide. A product of expected 1204bp was successfully amplified by PCR. Therefore, it may be concluded that, PCr technique could be a useful tool for the detection of PrPC gene. However, it needs further study for the gene sequence of PrP and analysis PrP gene polymorphisms in the black Bengal goats for the risk assessment of goat scrapie in Bangladesh. ', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
