(3694, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Microbiology and Hygine', 'Project', 'Livestock and poultry vaccine research and production centre', 'Overall Bangladesh ', 'High', '', 'Completed', '01-07-2010', '30-06-2012', '01-07-2010', '30-06-2012', '', '', 'During the period from 01-07-2010 to 30-06-2011 a total number of 12, 01, 000 doses (1,201 vials) of fowl cholera vaccine were produced and sold to different poultry farms of Bangladesh. The vaccine are produced and tested in the laboratory follow the process of OIE Manual 1992.\r\nThe chronological procedure followed was culturing of seed strain of P. multocida serotype 1 (X-73) on Blood Agar (BA) and incubated at 37&deg; C for 24 hours and then purity of culture was tested by Grams straining. Subsequently the pure culture was grown in BA for overnight. The isolated colonies were inoculated in to sterile nutrient broth with the supplement of yeast extract and beef extract and then incubated at 37&deg; C for 24 hours. Afterwards, formalin was added to the broth culture to inactive the culture and after 24 hours alum was also added as adjuvant. Finally, it was dispensed in vials and stored at room temperature for sale. \r\nThus, the inactivated alum precipitated fowl cholera vaccine contains P. multocida bacteria at the dose rate of I ml of 5x105 colony forming unit (CFU). The vaccine was subjected to safety test to the experimental birds satisfactorily. In addition, potency test of the vaccine was performed to determine its efficacy and a significant level of immunity was recorded to the experimental birds. It may be mentioned that during the period no untoward reports of the supplied vaccines were recorded from the farmers.\r\n', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
