(3764, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of  Horticulture', 'Project', 'Studies on the improvement of garlic and onion in Bangladesh and USA through varietal Development and biotechnology', 'Farmers of GO (DAE, BADC) and NGO (Caritas, World vision, BRAC, Proshika, CARE etc.', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '01-07-2010', '30-06-2011', '01-07-2010', '30-06-2011', '', '', 'A series of experiment were done to achieve the objectives: i) to identify high yielding short-day cultivars with long shelf life and higher allicin content, ii) to develop variety (ies) through positive selection iii) to develop varieties through mutation breeding, iv) to standardize the production technology of developed varieties, v) to train scientist, Extension officials, farmers of GO (DAE, BADC) and NGO (Caritas, World vision, BRAC, Proshika, CARE etc.) and vi) alleviate poverty under the project. Two garlic varieties BAU garlic-1 and BAU garlic-2 has been developed. The average yield of the newly developed varieties are 10-15 t/ha against the national average yield, 4-5 t/ha.  Different systematic approaches like research, training, quality seed distribution, demonstration and field day were taken up for implementing the project. One of the major activities of the project was training and demonstration for the beneficiaries. These activities were carried out by the participation of BAUEC registered farmers, CARE, CARITAS, BRAC and WORLD VISION beneficiaries, scientist of Spices Research Centre and agricultural extension personnel. A series of experiments were also conducted during 2010-2011, at the USDA Alliums field laboratory to develop a package of production methods and low cost preservation technologies for garlic and onion. In an experiment twenty germplasm were evaluated for their growth and yield. The results on the experiment revealed that germplasm G19 gave the highest yield (20.93 t/ha) followed by germplasm G20 (15.52 t/ha). A number of experiments were also carried out to identify the effects of organic manures, whose showed that organic manures were significant influence on growth and development of garlic. Cowdung is the best for organic garlic production. From an experiment it was revealed that GA3 (200ppm) gave the best results for the seed production of summer onion. The variety BARI Piaz-2 produced higher yield and quality than the variety N-53. ', 'Garlic, Onion, Spices', '', 0, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Development', 'Garlic and Onion', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, Volume-22, 2011.  Proceedings of the workshop of BAU Research Progress, 02-03 April 2012.');
