(3798, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Pharmacology', 'Project', 'Comparative efficacy of indigenous medicinal plant dadmardan (Cassia alata) and Ata (Annona reticulata), Neem (Azadirachta indica) with a patent drug against skin diseases (Ringworm, scabies and ectoparasites) in Cattle.', 'Department of Pharmacology, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'The aim of this project was to investigate the comparative efficacy of indigenous medicinal plants. Dadmardan (Cassia Alata), Neem (Azadirachta indica) and Ata (Annona reticulate) against skin lesion in cattle. The comparative efficacy was observed by the topical application of the combined ointment (Dadmardan, neem and Ata leaves) twice daily for 21 days and Dadmardan ointment twice daily for 24 days against skin lesions cattle. The combined ointment completely cured the lesions within 21 days and Dadmardan ointment twice daily for 24 days against skin lesions in cattle. The combined ointment completely cured the lesions within 21 days and Dadmardan ointment within 24 days. In comparison to their effect the combined ointment showed the more effectiveness (100% in 21 days). It may be concluded that the ointment (the combined ointment of Dadmardan, Neem and Ata leaves and Dadmardan ointment) may be used as alternative drugs for the treatment of skin lesions or skin diseases in cattle. Ivomec was highly effective against manage and ectoparasites, Body weight of Ivermectin and Neem treated calves increased on day 28 post treatment. Extensive research work is required to find out the efficacy of lvermectin and neem against ectoparasites and its with drawl periods, pharmacokinetic and toxicological parameter need to be studied. Lvemectin injection and Neem spray remained healthy, no adverse and calves appetite increased, growth and coat color improved rapidly. Whitefields ointment was effective against ring worm and Sulpher ointment was effective against manage but these two ointments are very old and Sulpher ointment is not available in the market so many be replaced by Dadmardan (Cassia alata), Neem (Azadirachta indica) and Ata (Annona reticulate) respectively. ', 'Medicinal plant, cattle, patent drug, skin disease', 'BAURES', 0, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Animal Disease management through Herbal plants', 'Cattle', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress. Volume 20. Proceedings of the Workshop of Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, 07-08 March, 2010. Bangladesh Agricultural University Research System (BAURES), BAU, Mymensingh.'),
