(3851, 'Bangladesh Agricultural University', 'Department of Pharmacology', 'Project', 'Prolong use of three antidiabetic plants, Neem (Azadirachta indica), Garlic (Allium sativum), Nayantara (Catharanthus roseus) and patent drugs (Metformin hydrochloride) in rats.', 'Department of Pharmacology, BAU', 'High', 'Applied', 'Completed', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Diabetes is a chronic condition in which a deficiency of the hormone insulin impairs the bodys ability to metabolize sugars. In this experiment we wanted to establish indigenous system of medicine (herbal therapy) as antidiabetic drugs instead of chemical drugs and rat is used as model of animal. The effects of Nayantara (Catharanthus roseus) leaves, Neem (Azadirachta indica) leaves and Garlic (Allium sativum) seed extract on blood glucose concentration and body weight on Streptozotocin induced diabetic rats were studied in this term effect of Nayantara leaves, Neem leaves and Garlic was also observed during the study. After administration of the patent drug and three herbal preparations all the treated and control groups of rats were closely observed for 90 days of treatment period. All the parameter were studied on day 0 (pre treatment), day 17, day 28, day 42, day 60 and day 90 of treatment period. Blood glucose levels were significantly (p&amp;#706;0.005) reduced on all treated four groups of rats. Similarly, body gain were also increased significantly (p&amp;#706;0.005) in comparison to pretreatment period. Neem and Nayantara leaves. Garlic significantly lowered blood glucose level as patent drug such as patent drug. These herbal preparations also increase body weight gain as patent drug. It is reported that Metformin showed malaise, abdominal pain, fever, diarrhea in some cases. No detectable side effects were observed in case of neem, Nayantara, Garlic extracts during the experiment. The experiment supports the traditional usage of the herbal preparations by Ayurvedic physicians for the control of diabetes but further studies have been suggested to elaborate the mechanisms of antidiabetic effects of these three herbal plants and to observe the side effect and adverse effect of them for taking as antidiabetic drugs in human being.', 'Antidiabetic plants, Neem, Nayantara, patent drugs', 'BAURES', 0, 0, 0, 'Report', '', 0, 'Herbal medicine use', 'Rats', '', '', 'Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress, 07-08 March, 2010. Bangladesh Agricultural Bangladesh Agricultural University Research Progress. Volume 20. Proceedings of the Workshop of University Research System (BAURES), BAU, Mymensingh.'),
