(176, 'Carps fish cultivation for sustainable development.', 'Increasing fish protein production and decreasing protein calories malnutrition of children of poor families by utilizing available ponds in carps fish cultivation. It is also aiming to increase income and create  employment for fishermen folk;', 'Winrock International', 'Fisheries', 'Carp polyculture.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '400000', 'USAID'),
(177, 'Popularization of Aman Rice variety BINASHAIL & BRRI - 22.', 'To disseminate appropriate technology on sustainable crop production;To diversify the crop;To increase gross production as well as income of the farmers; To build the capacity and skill of the farmers;', 'Winrock International', 'Crops', 'Rice production.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '400000', 'USAID'),
(178, 'Transfer of Technology Iratom 24 & BRRI Dhan - 28.', 'Introduction of cultivation of Iratom 24;Increased income of the growers will be ensured;', 'Winrock International', 'Crops', 'Rice production.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '400000', 'USAID'),
(179, 'Pangus with carp mixed culture technology transfer in Bagharpara Thana.', 'To transfer and popularize the pangus with carp mixed culture technology for increased fish production; To grow awareness among the farmers for pangus and carp mixed culture in ponds for optimum production with minimum cost; To help disseminate the pangus and carp mixed culture technology around the project area and the areas beyond and to ensure rational utilization of water resources for the rural poor people; To produce animal protein to improve nutritional status of the farmers as well as other people and to maintain eco-system and improve the environment;', 'Winrock International', 'Fisheries', 'Pangus with carp mixed culture.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', 'Bagherpara, Jessore', '500000', 'USAID'),
(180, 'Pattern based Soil fertility and seed production programme.', 'Increased cropping intensity;Introduce modern rice variety (BRRI-32) and chikpea variety (BARI-2);Farmers can produce their own seed;Improve soil health;Minimize protein deficiency', 'Department of Agricultural Extension', 'Crops', 'Soil health management.', 'Mr. Md. Rezaul Karim', '', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '300000', 'USAID'),
(181, 'Popularizing Soybean Production, Consumption and Soil Health Management.', 'To  meet-up protein deficiency through cultivation and consumption of Soybean;To improve soil health through Soya legume, use of compost and cultivation of Dhaincha;To make mass people aware about techniques of soybean cultivation and cooking process;', 'Department of Agricultural Extension', 'Crops', 'Soil health management.', 'Mr. Md. Fazlul Haque', '', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '300000', 'USAID'),
(182, 'Introducing Intensive Soybean cultivation and Improved Practices of Soil Health Management.', 'To introduce soybean production as one of important cereal crops among the farmers of Noakhali;To familiarise the farmers with intensive soybean cultivation practices through skill development training;To disseminate the improved practices of soil Health Management through Soya legume, use of compost and Dhaincha cultivation;To impart training on the techniques of processing the soybean including its cooking and consumption;To meet up the protein deficiency through increased consumption of arable soya foods;', 'Department of Agricultural Extension', 'Crops', 'Soil health management.', 'Mr. M L Mahmud', '', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '300000', 'USAID'),
(183, 'Soil Health improvement by farmers training and demonstration programme at Shibjanj Thana, Bogra.', 'To increase soil fertility;To ensure better utilization of local resources especially non fertile land;To reduce environmental pollution;To create employment opportunities of targeted beneficiary;To increase food production & sustain crop productivity for the beneficiaries;', 'Department of Agricultural Extension', 'Crops', 'Soil health management.', 'Mr. Md. Abdul Matin', '', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', 'Shibganj, Bogra', '300000', 'USAID'),
(184, 'Transfer of Apiculture technology in  rural poor of Madhaupur Thana.', 'To expand the apiculture among the rural poor and make it a source of income for them;New job opportunity will be created;Poverty will be alleviated;Nutrition status of cultivators would be improved through consumption of honey;The project will contribute to gross national production;', 'Department of Agricultural Extension', 'Apiculture', 'Apiculture.', 'Mr. Md. Ibrahim Khalil', 'DD, Tangail', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', 'Madhupur, Tangail', '300000', 'USAID'),
(185, 'Transfer and popularisation of maize as intercrop production technologies.', 'To popularise maize cultivation among the farmers;To increase maize area and production in the project area;To train farmers and on the modern maize production technologies, post harvest technologies, marketing, use of maize etc.;', 'Department of Agricultural Extension', 'Crops', 'Inter cropping.', 'Mr. Md. Lutfur Rahman', '', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '300000', 'USAID'),
(186, 'Vegetable seed production and preservation technology to destitute women farmers in Kurigram Sadar (selected winter and summer vegetables).', 'Produce quality seeds and make them available at the doorstep of villagers;Empowerment of women and prepare a group of female seed producers;Build network of seed producers to exchange;Increase vegetable production and income of rural families;', 'Department of Agricultural Extension', 'Crops', 'Vegetable production.', 'Mr. Md. Abdur Rouf', '', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', 'Kurigram Sadar', '300000', 'USAID'),
(187, 'Beef cattle fattening technology transfer in Manikganj District.', 'To transfer and popularize the beef cattle fattening technology among the farmers; To increase both production and consumption of beef in the locality; To increase employment and bring socio-economic development through beef fattening technology; To create awareness among the rural poor people towards self-employment opportunities; To ensure the efficient use  of local resources (Straw & molasses) as a cattle feed;', 'Winrock International', 'Livestock', 'Beef fattening.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', 'Manikganj', '300000', 'USAID'),
(188, 'Selection and multiplication of Dwarf type Exotic and Indigenous Variety of Fruits to cultivation in homestead areas.', 'Collection, selection,  multiplication and demonstration of suitable exotic and indigenous variety  of different fruits to cultivate in homestead areas;Train the farmers/GO-NGO personnel about new technology of grafting;Plantation of more trees in less areas and minimization of malnutrition of poor farmers of the villages;Conduct training of DAE/NGO personnel and selected farmers about plantation, intercultural operation, pest management, harvesting, processing and marketing etc.;Set up of demonstration to observe germ plasm performance at Horticulture Centre;', 'Department of Agricultural Extension', 'Crops', 'Fruits cultivation.', 'Mr. S M Qumruzzaman', '', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '300000', 'USAID'),
(189, 'Technology Transfer for polyculture of carps in Narshingdi.', 'To remove protein deficiencies; To increase economic growth of the country;To create employment opportunities;', 'Winrock International', 'Fisheries', 'Carp polyculture.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', 'Narshingdi', '300000', 'USAID'),
(190, 'Transfer of potato production technology from true seed in Nobi Nagar of Brahmanbaria.', 'To reduce the rate of deterioration of potato variety;', 'Winrock International', 'Crops', 'Potato production from TPS.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', 'Nabinagar, B''Baria', '300000', 'USAID'),
(191, 'Demonstration of late jute seed production', '', 'Winrock International', 'Crops', 'Late Jute seed production.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '250000', 'USAID'),
(192, 'Intercropping Soybean with Maize', 'Technology transfer proposal is to demonstrate and transmit this important agro-technology of two cash crop production simultaneously in intercropping technique for reduction of cost of production as well as increase of yield. This will encourage the farmers to have competitive sales of both the grains to counter the imported grains. This will ultimately contribute to the import substitution and nutrition of the country.', 'Winrock International', 'Crops', 'Inter cropping.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '300000', 'USAID'),
(193, 'Transfer of BARI Tomato ? 5 technology.', 'To transfer the technology in the field level for increasing production of tomato ? 5 round the year and to contribute to the fulfillment of national nutrition-demand.', 'Winrock International', 'Crops', 'BARI Tomato production.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '300000', 'USAID'),
(194, 'Intercopping Pulses with Maize.', 'Demonstrate suitability of maize as a base crop in intensifying pulse cultivation and crop diversification;  Demonstrate usefulness of legume pulses as companion crops of maize in saving N fertilizer; Demonstrate advantages of paired-row combinations of maize over other methods of intercropping; Increase yield per unit area through adoption of recommended practices;', 'Winrock International', 'Crops', 'Inter cropping.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '250000', 'USAID'),
(195, 'Technology Transfer for polyculture of carps in Munshiganj.', 'To transfer the fish production for increased fish production. To grow awareness among the farmers for carp poly culture in unutilized and abandoned ponds for optimum production with minimum cost. To help disseminate the carp polyculture technology around the project area and the areas beyond and to ensure rational utilization of water resources for the poor people. To produce animal protein to improve nutritional status of the farmers as well as other people and to maintain eco-system and improve the environment.', 'Winrock International', 'Fisheries', 'Carp polyculture.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', 'Munshiganj', '300000', 'USAID'),
(196, 'Self employment of the rural youth by rearing cockerel on commercial basis.', 'To transfer the technology in the proposed area;To create income & employment opportunity for the poor people; To uplift the nutritional status of the rural poor; To increase meast production and consumption;To increase lucrative economic return;', 'Winrock International', 'Livestock', 'Cockerel rearing.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '500000', 'USAID'),
(197, 'Transfer of vegetable and onion seed production technology in the Char land of Faripur District.', 'To transfer and popularize the vegetable and onion seed production technologies to the farmers through demonstration and training; To teach and farmers practically seed production technologies under farmers situation; To make available vegetable seeds when will reduce vegetable seed import and for year round vegetable;', 'Department of Agricultural Extension', 'Crops', 'Seed production.', 'Mr. Mozammel Haque Hawlader', '', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', 'Charland of Faridpur district', '300000', 'USAID'),
(198, 'Technology Transfer to the Rural Poor Women through Integrated Homestead Farming for household Food security and Income generation.', 'To promote increased cultivation and supply of protein, vegetable and micronutrient rich fruits throughout the year in the project area and improve nutritional status of the (target) people; To create awareness among the rural women about hygenic food habit and improve their knowledge regarding more nutritious food basket to properly meet individual and household requirements. To increase women''s control over resources through their increased participation in economic activities and create awareness among them about appropriate technology for better production and income; To create awareness among target people about biodiversity and conservation and promote environmental friendly cultivation system and ''women friendly development atmosphere in the project area;', 'Department of Agricultural Extension', 'Crops', 'Inter cropping.', 'Mr. Ershad Hossain Khan', '', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '350000', 'USAID'),
(199, 'Technology Transfer for polyculture of carps in Jessore.', 'To introduce the technology among the farmers of the project area; To increase the production of animal protein;To reduce the cost of production of fish;To increase the consumption of protein;To increase the income of farmers;To ensure the integrated utilization of pond dike;To create employment opportunities;', 'Winrock International', 'Fisheries', 'Carp polyculture.', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', 'Jessore', '300000', 'USAID'),
(200, 'An attempt to transfer agricultural technologies to marginal and subsistence farmers in different areas of Bangladesh through partner NGOs', 'To disseminate nine selected agricultural technologies with 270 farm families in different areas of Bangladesh;To improve knowledge and skills of farmers so that they are able to adopt the technologies;To organize 70 field days involving community farmers and group members to further disseminate the potential benefits of these technologies;', 'Winrock International', 'None', 'None', 'Dr. M A Mannan', 'Co-ordinator', '2000-07-01', '2001-06-30', '', '300000', 'USAID');
